{"_id":"00o6rita00gfb6tn","name":"The House of Roses","type":"Folder","folder":null,"sorting":"a","sort":700000,"color":"#b10d18","flags":{"broken-tales":{"folderKey":"the-house-of-roses","translations":{}}}}
{"_id":"0sRUBUKdIfuEapLk","name":"Hanse","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"5Zrq5DSeaUWZGMkj","name":"Hanse - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hanse","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the incarnation of the power of the great Maw. My body \nregenerates thanks to the flesh I eat. My strength and my speed are unbelievable.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 101.","positive":"I am the incarnation of the power of the great Maw. My body \nregenerates thanks to the flesh I eat. My strength and my speed are unbelievable.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Hanse","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1781557626419,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"vxRdfKKXaT668tCt","name":"Gift - Mutant Maw","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hanse","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>As long as they maintain their original appearance, a \nmutant Maw appears in every way as a common child. When they unleash their \npower, the body shifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing a \nlong line of sharp teeth. A mutant is considered to be of a higher OL category \nfor every physical action they perform involving speed, strength, or ferocity. \nA mutant perceives the smell of human flesh, which they find intoxicating, \nand for this reason, every attempt to hide from their sense of smell receives \n1 Penalty. When a mutant begins to devour flesh (human or animal), they \ncannot stop until they have finished it. Once per Scene, when a mutant Maw \ninflicts 1 Wound by devouring fresh meat, they recover 1 Wound they suffered.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 101.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Hanse","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1781557626419,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"9KT4vRJeIJaboTv6","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hanse","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the incarnation of the power of the great Maw. My body \nregenerates thanks to the flesh I eat. My strength and my speed are unbelievable. \nAgenda: Keep capturing new humans to ensure a future for the Maw’s offspring. \nUnlike my sister Gréte, I have no regard for humans and, now that I spared my \nfather to make my sister happy, I just want to protect the stone that came from \nthe sky.\nGift – Mutant Maw: As long as they maintain their original appearance, a \nmutant Maw appears in every way as a common child. When they unleash their \npower, the body shifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing a \nlong line of sharp teeth. A mutant is considered to be of a higher OL category \nfor every physical action they perform involving speed, strength, or ferocity. \nA mutant perceives the smell of human flesh, which they find intoxicating, \nand for this reason, every attempt to hide from their sense of smell receives \n1 Penalty. When a mutant begins to devour flesh (human or animal), they \ncannot stop until they have finished it. Once per Scene, when a mutant Maw \ninflicts 1 Wound by devouring fresh meat, they recover 1 Wound they suffered.\nGift – First Maw: As the firstborn among the Maws, Hanse has learned \nto manipulate the power that he harbors in his body. During a Scene, \nHanse may self-inflict 1 Wound to benefit from one of the following effects: \n1. Superhuman Strength , if he inflicts 1 Wound with an action and \ndoes not devour the target, Hanse can throw it 15 feet away. The target \nwill fall to the ground and suffer 1 additional Wound if they impact an \nobstacle. Hanse can use his strength to throw one enemy into another, in \nwhich case the target can try to dodge the attack with a Defense Check. \n2. Superhuman Speed , Hanse can make an incredible leap of over 30 \nfeet. He does not need any preparation, and he can take another subject with \nhim while moving. 3. Power of the Stone that Came from the Sky , \nHanse can tap into the latent power in his body. Once per Scene, all human \nsubjects in his presence lose 2 Soma or alternatively can resist by taking 1 \nWound. Suffering the last Wound for this effect does not cause death, but a \nloss of consciousness.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 101.","owner":"Hanse","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1781557626419,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"00fisila00bqr0g5","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-hunger-island-hanse-101","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"hunger-island","adventureTitle":"Hunger Island","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":101,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Hunger Island","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the incarnation of the power of the great Maw. My body \nregenerates thanks to the flesh I eat. My strength and my speed are unbelievable. \nAgenda: Keep capturing new humans to ensure a future for the Maw’s offspring. \nUnlike my sister Gréte, I have no regard for humans and, now that I spared my \nfather to make my sister happy, I just want to protect the stone that came from \nthe sky.\nGift – Mutant Maw: As long as they maintain their original appearance, a \nmutant Maw appears in every way as a common child. When they unleash their \npower, the body shifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing a \nlong line of sharp teeth. A mutant is considered to be of a higher OL category \nfor every physical action they perform involving speed, strength, or ferocity. \nA mutant perceives the smell of human flesh, which they find intoxicating, \nand for this reason, every attempt to hide from their sense of smell receives \n1 Penalty. When a mutant begins to devour flesh (human or animal), they \ncannot stop until they have finished it. Once per Scene, when a mutant Maw \ninflicts 1 Wound by devouring fresh meat, they recover 1 Wound they suffered.\nGift – First Maw: As the firstborn among the Maws, Hanse has learned \nto manipulate the power that he harbors in his body. During a Scene, \nHanse may self-inflict 1 Wound to benefit from one of the following effects: \n1. Superhuman Strength , if he inflicts 1 Wound with an action and \ndoes not devour the target, Hanse can throw it 15 feet away. The target \nwill fall to the ground and suffer 1 additional Wound if they impact an \nobstacle. Hanse can use his strength to throw one enemy into another, in \nwhich case the target can try to dodge the attack with a Defense Check. \n2. Superhuman Speed , Hanse can make an incredible leap of over 30 \nfeet. He does not need any preparation, and he can take another subject with \nhim while moving. 3. Power of the Stone that Came from the Sky , \nHanse can tap into the latent power in his body. Once per Scene, all human \nsubjects in his presence lose 2 Soma or alternatively can resist by taking 1 \nWound. Suffering the last Wound for this effect does not cause death, but a \nloss of consciousness.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Keep capturing new humans to ensure a future for the Maw’s offspring. \nUnlike my sister Gréte, I have no regard for humans and, now that I spared my \nfather to make my sister happy, I just want to protect the stone that came from \nthe sky.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":900000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1781557626419,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"1LU78xZ9wRJAgnvb","name":"Crazed Maws","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"uZrSfy4LZCljC0sS","name":"Crazed Maws - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Crazed Maws","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>A mad abomination whose form constantly \nshifts, as they wander in search of living beings to devour.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 102.","positive":"A mad abomination whose form constantly \nshifts, as they wander in search of living beings to devour.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Crazed Maws","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626450,"modifiedTime":1781557626450,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"9ExnJm3hevBKySYl","name":"Gift - Mutant Abomination","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Crazed Maws","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>A Crazed Maw does not \nfeel any pain. For this reason the Wounds it suffers have \nno narrative effect but are only a counter to understand \nwhen the abomination will crumble into a thousand pieces. \nTentacles and arms are constantly born from the body of \na Crazed Maw, and as a result it can act 2 times during \nan Exchange. With one of its actions, a Crazed Maw can \nslam its huge mass to the ground to create a strong tremor. \nAll targets in the immediate vicinity must pass a Defense \nCheck to avoid falling to the ground.\nThreat – The Stone that Came from \nthe Sky</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 102.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Crazed Maws","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626450,"modifiedTime":1781557626450,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"YWPKluzEQTADJDV7","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Crazed Maws","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: A mad abomination whose form constantly \nshifts, as they wander in search of living beings to devour. \nAgenda: Eat every living thing, except other Maws.\nGift – Mutant Abomination: A Crazed Maw does not \nfeel any pain. For this reason the Wounds it suffers have \nno narrative effect but are only a counter to understand \nwhen the abomination will crumble into a thousand pieces. \nTentacles and arms are constantly born from the body of \na Crazed Maw, and as a result it can act 2 times during \nan Exchange. With one of its actions, a Crazed Maw can \nslam its huge mass to the ground to create a strong tremor. \nAll targets in the immediate vicinity must pass a Defense \nCheck to avoid falling to the ground.\nThreat – The Stone that Came from \nthe Sky\nDescriptor: An alien stone, the size of a fist, that thrums \nwith energy. \nGift – Alien Stone: All the powers of the Maws derive \nfrom the stone. With its destruction, the mutations will \ndeteriorate, causing the death of all mutants except Hanse \nand Gréte. The stone has 6 Wounds and has no OL, because \nit cannot interact directly or defend itself. For each Wound \nsuffered, a spark of the power comes out, affecting the one \nwho inflicted the blow. Whoever suffers this effect can \ndecide between losing 2 Soma or suffering 1 Wound. If the \nstone is destroyed or stolen, Hanse will be able to unleash \nall the latent power in him and, by joining with Gréte, give \nlife to the Great Maw.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 102.","owner":"Crazed Maws","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626450,"modifiedTime":1781557626450,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"00fisila00bqr0g5","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-hunger-island-crazed-maws-102","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"hunger-island","adventureTitle":"Hunger Island","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":102,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Hunger Island","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: A mad abomination whose form constantly \nshifts, as they wander in search of living beings to devour. \nAgenda: Eat every living thing, except other Maws.\nGift – Mutant Abomination: A Crazed Maw does not \nfeel any pain. For this reason the Wounds it suffers have \nno narrative effect but are only a counter to understand \nwhen the abomination will crumble into a thousand pieces. \nTentacles and arms are constantly born from the body of \na Crazed Maw, and as a result it can act 2 times during \nan Exchange. With one of its actions, a Crazed Maw can \nslam its huge mass to the ground to create a strong tremor. \nAll targets in the immediate vicinity must pass a Defense \nCheck to avoid falling to the ground.\nThreat – The Stone that Came from \nthe Sky\nDescriptor: An alien stone, the size of a fist, that thrums \nwith energy. \nGift – Alien Stone: All the powers of the Maws derive \nfrom the stone. With its destruction, the mutations will \ndeteriorate, causing the death of all mutants except Hanse \nand Gréte. The stone has 6 Wounds and has no OL, because \nit cannot interact directly or defend itself. For each Wound \nsuffered, a spark of the power comes out, affecting the one \nwho inflicted the blow. Whoever suffers this effect can \ndecide between losing 2 Soma or suffering 1 Wound. If the \nstone is destroyed or stolen, Hanse will be able to unleash \nall the latent power in him and, by joining with Gréte, give \nlife to the Great Maw.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Eat every living thing, except other Maws.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":1000000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626450,"modifiedTime":1781557626450,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"2z7dF091hEgGkk6r","name":"Hedge Labyrinth","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"y0YerOpefrmKzxrI","name":"Hedge Labyrinth - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hedge Labyrinth","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>A large labyrinth of hedges and roses that \nextends throughout the estate garden.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 129.","positive":"A large labyrinth of hedges and roses that \nextends throughout the estate garden.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Hedge Labyrinth","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632122,"modifiedTime":1781557632122,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"r9OL5faa5reaFer6","name":"Gift - Secret Passage","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hedge Labyrinth","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Bellina and Dionysus know a \nseries of secret passages to avoid wasting time in the maze. \nAnyone else might need several hours to negotiate it. \nBellina Cantalupo known as Bella</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 129.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Hedge Labyrinth","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632122,"modifiedTime":1781557632122,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"b2fWt81kExPFvjVD","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Hedge Labyrinth","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A large labyrinth of hedges and roses that \nextends throughout the estate garden. \nGift – Secret Passage: Bellina and Dionysus know a \nseries of secret passages to avoid wasting time in the maze. \nAnyone else might need several hours to negotiate it. \nBellina Cantalupo known as Bella</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 129.","owner":"Hedge Labyrinth","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632122,"modifiedTime":1781557632122,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"00o6rita00gfb6tn","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-hedge-labyrinth-129","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":129,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A large labyrinth of hedges and roses that \nextends throughout the estate garden. \nGift – Secret Passage: Bellina and Dionysus know a \nseries of secret passages to avoid wasting time in the maze. \nAnyone else might need several hours to negotiate it. \nBellina Cantalupo known as Bella</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":1100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632122,"modifiedTime":1781557632122,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"36Z1BHsZ8LEnDMgf","name":"Bruna the Poor Witch","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"t9w3bXeo9QFInlnx","name":"Bruna the Poor Witch - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Bruna the Poor Witch","source":"Bloodwhite's Heart","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a poor old woman to whom life has \noffered only suffering. Sometimes I manifest strange powers, \nbut I have always concealed this ability out of fear of ending \nup at the stake.</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 113.","positive":"I am a poor old woman to whom life has \noffered only suffering. Sometimes I manifest strange powers, \nbut I have always concealed this ability out of fear of ending \nup at the stake.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Bruna the Poor Witch","source":"Bloodwhite's Heart","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628565,"modifiedTime":1781557628565,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7E5eYV8sCaqOXzYE","name":"Gift - Latent Witch","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Bruna the Poor Witch","source":"Bloodwhite's Heart","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Bruna has magic abilities, but \nshe never studied and uses her powers unconsciously. If \nthreatened, Bruna will activate her power and the objects \nin the immediate vicinity will begin to move and then fall \nupon everyone. Acting in the area affected by this power \nconfers 2 Penalties on each Check due to the uncontrolled \nmagic manifestations. If Bruna is killed, she will curse her \nkiller who, for the rest of the Scenario, will receive 1 Penalty \nat each Defense Check. A practitioner of magic or someone \nwho can communicate with spirits can soothe Bruna’s soul \nto undo the curse, but a Position Check will be required</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 113.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Bruna the Poor Witch","source":"Bloodwhite's Heart","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628565,"modifiedTime":1781557628565,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"PcrTASuBExNdGFVp","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Bruna the Poor Witch","source":"Bloodwhite's Heart","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a poor old woman to whom life has \noffered only suffering. Sometimes I manifest strange powers, \nbut I have always concealed this ability out of fear of ending \nup at the stake.\nAgenda: To live in peace, seeking acceptance from the \ninhabitants of Lohr.\nGift – Latent Witch: Bruna has magic abilities, but \nshe never studied and uses her powers unconsciously. If \nthreatened, Bruna will activate her power and the objects \nin the immediate vicinity will begin to move and then fall \nupon everyone. Acting in the area affected by this power \nconfers 2 Penalties on each Check due to the uncontrolled \nmagic manifestations. If Bruna is killed, she will curse her \nkiller who, for the rest of the Scenario, will receive 1 Penalty \nat each Defense Check. A practitioner of magic or someone \nwho can communicate with spirits can soothe Bruna’s soul \nto undo the curse, but a Position Check will be required</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 113.","owner":"Bruna the Poor Witch","source":"Bloodwhite's Heart","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628565,"modifiedTime":1781557628565,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"00o4ut1z01pgdx9e","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-bloodwhites-heart-bruna-the-poor-witch-113","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"bloodwhites-heart","adventureTitle":"Bloodwhite's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":113,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Bloodwhite's Heart","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a poor old woman to whom life has \noffered only suffering. Sometimes I manifest strange powers, \nbut I have always concealed this ability out of fear of ending \nup at the stake.\nAgenda: To live in peace, seeking acceptance from the \ninhabitants of Lohr.\nGift – Latent Witch: Bruna has magic abilities, but \nshe never studied and uses her powers unconsciously. If \nthreatened, Bruna will activate her power and the objects \nin the immediate vicinity will begin to move and then fall \nupon everyone. Acting in the area affected by this power \nconfers 2 Penalties on each Check due to the uncontrolled \nmagic manifestations. If Bruna is killed, she will curse her \nkiller who, for the rest of the Scenario, will receive 1 Penalty \nat each Defense Check. A practitioner of magic or someone \nwho can communicate with spirits can soothe Bruna’s soul \nto undo the curse, but a Position Check will be required</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"To live in peace, seeking acceptance from the \ninhabitants of Lohr.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":1200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628565,"modifiedTime":1781557628565,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"3XANKF9oPVfgjyqp","name":"Bella’s Servants","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"qQkr7ufeWttJa745","name":"Bella’s Servants - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Bella’s Servants","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are young people in the service of Bella \nand we are trained to defend the House \nof Roses.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 127.","positive":"We are young people in the service of Bella \nand we are trained to defend the House \nof Roses.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Bella’s Servants","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629804,"modifiedTime":1781557629804,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Z3zdJYr4H7gsub4l","name":"Gift - For Our Lady","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Bella’s Servants","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Servants are brainwashed \nand totally dependent on Bella. Every attempt to scare or \nmentally manipulate them receives 2 Penalties. If Bella \nis targeted by a threat, once per Exchange, a Servant can \nsacrifice themselves to take the hit in her place. \nThe White Beach</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 127.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Bella’s Servants","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629804,"modifiedTime":1781557629804,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"bVq8bOiq0Uudm4QC","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Bella’s Servants","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are young people in the service of Bella \nand we are trained to defend the House \nof Roses. \nAgenda: Follow all of Bella’s \norders to the letter. \nGift – For Our Lady: The Servants are brainwashed \nand totally dependent on Bella. Every attempt to scare or \nmentally manipulate them receives 2 Penalties. If Bella \nis targeted by a threat, once per Exchange, a Servant can \nsacrifice themselves to take the hit in her place. \nThe White Beach\nDescriptor: A small beach of pebbles and earth hidden \namong the dense vegetation.\nInformation: Docking at the beach without the \nnecessary precautions will attract 1d6+2 Mastiffs.\nThe Forest\nDescriptor: A large wooded area that almost entirely \ncovers Martana Island.\nInformation: The forest is overrun by mastiffs loyal to \nDionysus. Avoiding them requires overcoming the Pack of \nMastiffs Threat. In case of a Failure, 8 Mastiffs will appear \nand surround the intruders. At the center of the forest is \na mass grave where the bodies of Dionysus’ victims are \ndumped. Francesca hides in the pit to escape the hungry \ndogs.\nThreat – Pack of Mastiffs</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 127.","owner":"Bella’s Servants","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629804,"modifiedTime":1781557629804,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"00o6rita00gfb6tn","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-bella-s-servants-127","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":127,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are young people in the service of Bella \nand we are trained to defend the House \nof Roses. \nAgenda: Follow all of Bella’s \norders to the letter. \nGift – For Our Lady: The Servants are brainwashed \nand totally dependent on Bella. Every attempt to scare or \nmentally manipulate them receives 2 Penalties. If Bella \nis targeted by a threat, once per Exchange, a Servant can \nsacrifice themselves to take the hit in her place. \nThe White Beach\nDescriptor: A small beach of pebbles and earth hidden \namong the dense vegetation.\nInformation: Docking at the beach without the \nnecessary precautions will attract 1d6+2 Mastiffs.\nThe Forest\nDescriptor: A large wooded area that almost entirely \ncovers Martana Island.\nInformation: The forest is overrun by mastiffs loyal to \nDionysus. Avoiding them requires overcoming the Pack of \nMastiffs Threat. In case of a Failure, 8 Mastiffs will appear \nand surround the intruders. At the center of the forest is \na mass grave where the bodies of Dionysus’ victims are \ndumped. Francesca hides in the pit to escape the hungry \ndogs.\nThreat – Pack of Mastiffs</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Follow all of Bella’s \norders to the letter.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":1300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629804,"modifiedTime":1781557629804,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"5XEyVW05EwvDvOm5","name":"Aleksandr Pták","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"5dvUDtB0MRrBgfY2","name":"Aleksandr Pták - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Aleksandr Pták","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am divided between who I was before and \nthe spirit who took possession of my body. I have the urge to \nkill, but since my mind is clouded, I don’t always know why.\nSwallow’s</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 173.","positive":"I am divided between who I was before and \nthe spirit who took possession of my body. I have the urge to \nkill, but since my mind is clouded, I don’t always know why.\nSwallow’s","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Aleksandr Pták","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637920,"modifiedTime":1781557637920,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"yD6xEWnvFzBP8SxN","name":"Gift - Swallow’s Flight","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Aleksandr Pták","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Aleksandr can easily climb \nanywhere and perform inhuman leaps. As he does, his OL \nincreases by 1. If he hits someone plunging down from \nabove, he can automatically escape the enemy’s threat range \nwith a long jump.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 173.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Aleksandr Pták","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637920,"modifiedTime":1781557637920,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ruzn4nprCzdQv4w5","name":"Gift - What is Yours is Mine","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Aleksandr Pták","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>As an additional action, \nAleksandr can steal any object in the hands of another \ncharacter with extreme ease. A Hunter can avoid the theft \nby succeeding in a Defense Check. \n \nCernobog Potmešil The Child</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 173.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Aleksandr Pták","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637920,"modifiedTime":1781557637920,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"vExBfULSPvsPz14d","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Aleksandr Pták","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am divided between who I was before and \nthe spirit who took possession of my body. I have the urge to \nkill, but since my mind is clouded, I don’t always know why.\nSwallow’s Agenda: Finding an ally in the people I helped \nin my previous life / Restoring the Prince, my only true love / \nAvenging wrongs suffered. \nAlexandr’s Agenda: Finding peace and freeing myself \nfrom the spirit that possesses me. \nGift – Swallow’s Flight: Aleksandr can easily climb \nanywhere and perform inhuman leaps. As he does, his OL \nincreases by 1. If he hits someone plunging down from \nabove, he can automatically escape the enemy’s threat range \nwith a long jump. \nGift – What is Yours is Mine: As an additional action, \nAleksandr can steal any object in the hands of another \ncharacter with extreme ease. A Hunter can avoid the theft \nby succeeding in a Defense Check. \n \nCernobog Potmešil The Child</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 173.","owner":"Aleksandr Pták","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637920,"modifiedTime":1781557637920,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"01gakz6800ms75vx","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-will-stay-with-you-always-aleksandr-pt-k-173","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-will-stay-with-you-always","adventureTitle":"I Will Stay with You Always","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":173,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Will Stay with You Always","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am divided between who I was before and \nthe spirit who took possession of my body. I have the urge to \nkill, but since my mind is clouded, I don’t always know why.\nSwallow’s Agenda: Finding an ally in the people I helped \nin my previous life / Restoring the Prince, my only true love / \nAvenging wrongs suffered. \nAlexandr’s Agenda: Finding peace and freeing myself \nfrom the spirit that possesses me. \nGift – Swallow’s Flight: Aleksandr can easily climb \nanywhere and perform inhuman leaps. As he does, his OL \nincreases by 1. If he hits someone plunging down from \nabove, he can automatically escape the enemy’s threat range \nwith a long jump. \nGift – What is Yours is Mine: As an additional action, \nAleksandr can steal any object in the hands of another \ncharacter with extreme ease. A Hunter can avoid the theft \nby succeeding in a Defense Check. \n \nCernobog Potmešil The Child</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Finding an ally in the people I helped \nin my previous life / Restoring the Prince, my only true love / \nAvenging wrongs suffered. \nAlexandr’s Agenda: Finding peace and freeing myself \nfrom the spirit that possesses me.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":1400000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637920,"modifiedTime":1781557637920,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"5sf2sa1BL6TPhjQc","name":"Arne the Captain","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"0eTc8DjRFLTptLxG","name":"Arne the Captain - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Arne the Captain","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I once was a military man and I’ve earned the \ncrown’s respect. Now, as a ship’s captain, I serve my country and \nboast about my crew.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 95.","positive":"I once was a military man and I’ve earned the \ncrown’s respect. Now, as a ship’s captain, I serve my country and \nboast about my crew.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Arne the Captain","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626239,"modifiedTime":1781557626239,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"kSIlUR1DSiZL1pYd","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Arne the Captain","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I once was a military man and I’ve earned the \ncrown’s respect. Now, as a ship’s captain, I serve my country and \nboast about my crew. \nAgenda: Do my best to carry out the mission I was entrusted \nwith. However, I won’t put the people under my command at \nrisk.\nSailors</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 95.","owner":"Arne the Captain","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626239,"modifiedTime":1781557626239,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"00fisila00bqr0g5","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-hunger-island-arne-the-captain-95","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"hunger-island","adventureTitle":"Hunger Island","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":95,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Hunger Island","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I once was a military man and I’ve earned the \ncrown’s respect. Now, as a ship’s captain, I serve my country and \nboast about my crew. \nAgenda: Do my best to carry out the mission I was entrusted \nwith. However, I won’t put the people under my command at \nrisk.\nSailors</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Do my best to carry out the mission I was entrusted \nwith. However, I won’t put the people under my command at \nrisk.\nSailors","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":1500000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626239,"modifiedTime":1781557626239,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"7moweb3lakst027s","name":"Mercenary and Researcher of Renowned Fame","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"0NnYYBPAk5H6v41D","name":"Mercenary and Researcher of Renowned Fame - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Mercenary and Researcher of Renowned Fame","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled adventurer and treasure hunter, \nand I have no qualms about doing what it takes to get what \nI want.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 139.","positive":"I am a skilled adventurer and treasure hunter, \nand I have no qualms about doing what it takes to get what \nI want.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Mercenary and Researcher of Renowned Fame","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636228,"modifiedTime":1781557636228,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"sKpjXaf9YwmwXRyQ","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Mercenary and Researcher of Renowned Fame","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled adventurer and treasure hunter, \nand I have no qualms about doing what it takes to get what \nI want. \nAgenda: Escape from Stegeborg while keeping the secret of \nwhat I have done, as well as keeping the treasure I have found \n/ Take advantage of the arrival of the Hunters in Stegeborg to \nappease the fury of Talia. \nGift – Good at Escaping: Accursio is skilled at making \nhimself scarce when things get bad. Increase his OL by 1 \nfor all actions involving fleeing or avoiding a menace. Once \nper Scene, Accursio can move away from a place without \nanyone being able to stop or see him. To do this, however, \nit is necessary that something happens that can attract the</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 139.","owner":"Mercenary and Researcher of Renowned Fame","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636228,"modifiedTime":1781557636228,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"019bylki016ws0df","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-stegeborgs-quiet-mercenary-and-researcher-of-renowned-fame-139","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"stegeborgs-quiet","adventureTitle":"Stegeborg's Quiet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":139,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Stegeborg's Quiet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled adventurer and treasure hunter, \nand I have no qualms about doing what it takes to get what \nI want. \nAgenda: Escape from Stegeborg while keeping the secret of \nwhat I have done, as well as keeping the treasure I have found \n/ Take advantage of the arrival of the Hunters in Stegeborg to \nappease the fury of Talia. \nGift – Good at Escaping: Accursio is skilled at making \nhimself scarce when things get bad. Increase his OL by 1 \nfor all actions involving fleeing or avoiding a menace. Once \nper Scene, Accursio can move away from a place without \nanyone being able to stop or see him. To do this, however, \nit is necessary that something happens that can attract the</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Escape from Stegeborg while keeping the secret of \nwhat I have done, as well as keeping the treasure I have found \n/ Take advantage of the arrival of the Hunters in Stegeborg to \nappease the fury of Talia.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":1600000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636228,"modifiedTime":1781557636228,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"8Sis9tPhtp1ad32h","name":"Seal of the Cauldron Fae","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"5stJ5deOucBcjIpM","name":"Seal of the Cauldron Fae - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Seal of the Cauldron Fae","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>A magic seal capable of manifesting the magic \nof the Cauldron Fae.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 84.","positive":"A magic seal capable of manifesting the magic \nof the Cauldron Fae.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Seal of the Cauldron Fae","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"UAVWcUxmwrzuV8do","name":"Gift - Seals Everywhere","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Seal of the Cauldron Fae","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>At least one Seal of the \nCauldron Fae is present in all the Places of the Scenario. \nWhoever possesses the Gang Seal or Personal Seal Gift \ncan activate the effect of the Seal of the Cauldron Fae as an \nadditional action; this allows them to teleport to another \nplace featuring a Seal. The Seals are invisible to the human \neye and can be used only by those who have a tattooed eye \non their hand, placing said tattoo in front of the right eye. \nThose who use magic can detect the presence of a Seal, but \nthe Seal of Disbelief Scenario Gift is necessary to activate it. \nNote: Some Places feature more than one Seal to grant \nthe Lost Boys more narrative options in case the Hunters \nmanage to impede access to a Seal or negate the Gift. \nGeorge Carnarvon</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 84.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Seal of the Cauldron Fae","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"LqWk519l7dKB1wcr","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Seal of the Cauldron Fae","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A magic seal capable of manifesting the magic \nof the Cauldron Fae.\nGift – Seals Everywhere: At least one Seal of the \nCauldron Fae is present in all the Places of the Scenario. \nWhoever possesses the Gang Seal or Personal Seal Gift \ncan activate the effect of the Seal of the Cauldron Fae as an \nadditional action; this allows them to teleport to another \nplace featuring a Seal. The Seals are invisible to the human \neye and can be used only by those who have a tattooed eye \non their hand, placing said tattoo in front of the right eye. \nThose who use magic can detect the presence of a Seal, but \nthe Seal of Disbelief Scenario Gift is necessary to activate it. \nNote: Some Places feature more than one Seal to grant \nthe Lost Boys more narrative options in case the Hunters \nmanage to impede access to a Seal or negate the Gift. \nGeorge Carnarvon</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 84.","owner":"Seal of the Cauldron Fae","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"014did82003r90kn","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-dont-believe-seal-of-the-cauldron-fae-84","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","adventureTitle":"I Don't Believe","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":84,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Don't Believe","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A magic seal capable of manifesting the magic \nof the Cauldron Fae.\nGift – Seals Everywhere: At least one Seal of the \nCauldron Fae is present in all the Places of the Scenario. \nWhoever possesses the Gang Seal or Personal Seal Gift \ncan activate the effect of the Seal of the Cauldron Fae as an \nadditional action; this allows them to teleport to another \nplace featuring a Seal. The Seals are invisible to the human \neye and can be used only by those who have a tattooed eye \non their hand, placing said tattoo in front of the right eye. \nThose who use magic can detect the presence of a Seal, but \nthe Seal of Disbelief Scenario Gift is necessary to activate it. \nNote: Some Places feature more than one Seal to grant \nthe Lost Boys more narrative options in case the Hunters \nmanage to impede access to a Seal or negate the Gift. \nGeorge Carnarvon</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":1700000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Axj5S4ZXdBNtMwqW","name":"Althea the Agent of the Order","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"pL6kMfOGjgmCpXRg","name":"Althea the Agent of the Order - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Althea the Agent of the Order","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a nun in the service of the Order and, \ndespite my ecclesiastical background, I have skills as a spy and \na fighter. The Order entrusts me with high-risk tasks because \nit has confidence in my unwavering faith and ruthlessness.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 99.","positive":"I am a nun in the service of the Order and, \ndespite my ecclesiastical background, I have skills as a spy and \na fighter. The Order entrusts me with high-risk tasks because \nit has confidence in my unwavering faith and ruthlessness.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Althea the Agent of the Order","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626372,"modifiedTime":1781557626372,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"07CVUpiT6lpSeQc1","name":"Gift - Agent of the Order","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Althea the Agent of the Order","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Althea is talented and trained to support the Hunters. Althea can spend her action to \nsupport a Hunter’s action and give them 1 Additional \nSuccess in any Check.\nThe Mist Roads</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 99.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Althea the Agent of the Order","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626372,"modifiedTime":1781557626372,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"PuGh6ZUoD7IritPw","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Althea the Agent of the Order","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a nun in the service of the Order and, \ndespite my ecclesiastical background, I have skills as a spy and \na fighter. The Order entrusts me with high-risk tasks because \nit has confidence in my unwavering faith and ruthlessness.\nAgenda: Solve the mystery of the Maws and provide support \nto the Hunters of the Order.\nGift – Agent of the Order: Althea is talented and trained to support the Hunters. Althea can spend her action to \nsupport a Hunter’s action and give them 1 Additional \nSuccess in any Check.\nThe Mist Roads\nDescriptor: All the communication routes between Vík í \nMýrdal and the nearby villages are surrounded by a dense, \ndark fog that does not allow you to see more than a few feet \nahead.\nFor each trip on the Mist Roads, you can choose or roll for \na Threat/encounter with an NPC.\n1-2: A crevasse created by the eruption of Laki has \nopened up, barring the way.\nThreat – Crevasse in the Mist \nDescriptor: A crevasse eighteen feet deep, hidden by the \ndense mist.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 99.","owner":"Althea the Agent of the Order","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626372,"modifiedTime":1781557626372,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"00fisila00bqr0g5","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-hunger-island-althea-the-agent-of-the-order-99","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"hunger-island","adventureTitle":"Hunger Island","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":99,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Hunger Island","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a nun in the service of the Order and, \ndespite my ecclesiastical background, I have skills as a spy and \na fighter. The Order entrusts me with high-risk tasks because \nit has confidence in my unwavering faith and ruthlessness.\nAgenda: Solve the mystery of the Maws and provide support \nto the Hunters of the Order.\nGift – Agent of the Order: Althea is talented and trained to support the Hunters. Althea can spend her action to \nsupport a Hunter’s action and give them 1 Additional \nSuccess in any Check.\nThe Mist Roads\nDescriptor: All the communication routes between Vík í \nMýrdal and the nearby villages are surrounded by a dense, \ndark fog that does not allow you to see more than a few feet \nahead.\nFor each trip on the Mist Roads, you can choose or roll for \na Threat/encounter with an NPC.\n1-2: A crevasse created by the eruption of Laki has \nopened up, barring the way.\nThreat – Crevasse in the Mist \nDescriptor: A crevasse eighteen feet deep, hidden by the \ndense mist.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Solve the mystery of the Maws and provide support \nto the Hunters of the Order.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":1800000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626372,"modifiedTime":1781557626372,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"BhqIT5i6j4eEMU4N","name":"Talia the Sleeper","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"OTY9HDlIiuOJdzWZ","name":"Talia the Sleeper - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Talia the Sleeper","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young girl put to sleep for eternity by the \nmagic of Carabosse. The whole castle responds to my will and, \nthanks to my powers, I can see and hear everything.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 143.","positive":"I am a young girl put to sleep for eternity by the \nmagic of Carabosse. The whole castle responds to my will and, \nthanks to my powers, I can see and hear everything.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Talia the Sleeper","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636357,"modifiedTime":1781557636357,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Lxg22KcLMcAKSRAE","name":"Gift - Sleeping Spirit","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Talia the Sleeper","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Talia can literally manipulate the \nentire castle as she pleases. During each Exchange, she can \nperform up to 3 of the following actions. 1. Manipulate: \nMove or reshape an object of the castle into something else; \n2. Attack: Throw and move objects to inflict 1 Wound; \n3. Reject: Prevent people from moving, entering, or \nleaving by manipulating objects, or even the castle itself. \nTalia cannot speak, but she can use Manipulate to write or \ncompose rudimentary messages through objects. Talia can \nconcentrate all 3 actions into one with devastating effects. It \ncan collapse an entire wing of the castle or open a deep well \nin the ground. The effects of this action are wide-ranging and, \nat the discretion of the Storyteller, may remove one or more \nHunters who fail a Defense Check from the Scene.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 143.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Talia the Sleeper","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636357,"modifiedTime":1781557636357,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"UyCa5tnOggHju3kZ","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Talia the Sleeper","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young girl put to sleep for eternity by the \nmagic of Carabosse. The whole castle responds to my will and, \nthanks to my powers, I can see and hear everything.\nAgenda: Revenge myself on Accursio, who betrayed my trust \nthe way so many others have / Finding peace through death, or \nassimilating everything I can with my power.\nGift – Sleeping Spirit: Talia can literally manipulate the \nentire castle as she pleases. During each Exchange, she can \nperform up to 3 of the following actions. 1. Manipulate: \nMove or reshape an object of the castle into something else; \n2. Attack: Throw and move objects to inflict 1 Wound; \n3. Reject: Prevent people from moving, entering, or \nleaving by manipulating objects, or even the castle itself. \nTalia cannot speak, but she can use Manipulate to write or \ncompose rudimentary messages through objects. Talia can \nconcentrate all 3 actions into one with devastating effects. It \ncan collapse an entire wing of the castle or open a deep well \nin the ground. The effects of this action are wide-ranging and, \nat the discretion of the Storyteller, may remove one or more \nHunters who fail a Defense Check from the Scene.\nInformation: Next to Talia’s sleeping body, one can find her \ndiary, written with a pen manipulated by her hair. It tells the \nSleeper’s whole sad story.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 143.","owner":"Talia the Sleeper","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636357,"modifiedTime":1781557636357,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"019bylki016ws0df","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-stegeborgs-quiet-talia-the-sleeper-143","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"stegeborgs-quiet","adventureTitle":"Stegeborg's Quiet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":143,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Stegeborg's Quiet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young girl put to sleep for eternity by the \nmagic of Carabosse. The whole castle responds to my will and, \nthanks to my powers, I can see and hear everything.\nAgenda: Revenge myself on Accursio, who betrayed my trust \nthe way so many others have / Finding peace through death, or \nassimilating everything I can with my power.\nGift – Sleeping Spirit: Talia can literally manipulate the \nentire castle as she pleases. During each Exchange, she can \nperform up to 3 of the following actions. 1. Manipulate: \nMove or reshape an object of the castle into something else; \n2. Attack: Throw and move objects to inflict 1 Wound; \n3. Reject: Prevent people from moving, entering, or \nleaving by manipulating objects, or even the castle itself. \nTalia cannot speak, but she can use Manipulate to write or \ncompose rudimentary messages through objects. Talia can \nconcentrate all 3 actions into one with devastating effects. It \ncan collapse an entire wing of the castle or open a deep well \nin the ground. The effects of this action are wide-ranging and, \nat the discretion of the Storyteller, may remove one or more \nHunters who fail a Defense Check from the Scene.\nInformation: Next to Talia’s sleeping body, one can find her \ndiary, written with a pen manipulated by her hair. It tells the \nSleeper’s whole sad story.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Revenge myself on Accursio, who betrayed my trust \nthe way so many others have / Finding peace through death, or \nassimilating everything I can with my power.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":1900000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636357,"modifiedTime":1781557636357,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"E4thHxU24DMKBcjx","name":"The Count Azul of Vigo","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Q1DzS1sL8qI1CnKr","name":"The Count Azul of Vigo - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Count Azul of Vigo","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a rich and bored nobleman who \ncares only about social position.</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 154.","positive":"I am a rich and bored nobleman who \ncares only about social position.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Count Azul of Vigo","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636919,"modifiedTime":1781557636919,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"smQSNiZvsGwpWh9T","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Count Azul of Vigo","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a rich and bored nobleman who \ncares only about social position. \nAgenda: To waste time between parties and \npleasures, leaving the burden of leadership to my wife \nPrincesca.\nCinder Known to all as \nPrincesca of Vigo</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 154.","owner":"The Count Azul of Vigo","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636919,"modifiedTime":1781557636919,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"01x05lkv00q27p8a","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-in-your-eyes-with-your-feet-the-count-azul-of-vigo-154","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"in-your-eyes-with-your-feet","adventureTitle":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":154,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a rich and bored nobleman who \ncares only about social position. \nAgenda: To waste time between parties and \npleasures, leaving the burden of leadership to my wife \nPrincesca.\nCinder Known to all as \nPrincesca of Vigo</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"To waste time between parties and \npleasures, leaving the burden of leadership to my wife \nPrincesca.\nCinder Known to all as \nPrincesca of Vigo","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":2000000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636919,"modifiedTime":1781557636919,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"EOhiwVbwk3tBSATI","name":"Ostromir Malý","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"ePo5hRRBbPhlrnKt","name":"Ostromir Malý - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Ostromir Malý","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I rule Prague on behalf of Empress Maria \nTheresa and, after the failed siege, I hold the city’s fate in the \npalm of my hand. The recent murders are complicating my \nlife, though so far the noble families support my authority.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 166.","positive":"I rule Prague on behalf of Empress Maria \nTheresa and, after the failed siege, I hold the city’s fate in the \npalm of my hand. The recent murders are complicating my \nlife, though so far the noble families support my authority.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Ostromir Malý","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637466,"modifiedTime":1781557637466,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"I4qCtyJFoBBeYaMR","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Ostromir Malý","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I rule Prague on behalf of Empress Maria \nTheresa and, after the failed siege, I hold the city’s fate in the \npalm of my hand. The recent murders are complicating my \nlife, though so far the noble families support my authority.\nAgenda: Capture the assassin who is causing panic among \nthe nobles / Avoid a popular uprising.\nBeáta Czernin the Noblewoman</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 166.","owner":"Ostromir Malý","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637466,"modifiedTime":1781557637466,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"01gakz6800ms75vx","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-will-stay-with-you-always-ostromir-mal-166","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-will-stay-with-you-always","adventureTitle":"I Will Stay with You Always","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":166,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Will Stay with You Always","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I rule Prague on behalf of Empress Maria \nTheresa and, after the failed siege, I hold the city’s fate in the \npalm of my hand. The recent murders are complicating my \nlife, though so far the noble families support my authority.\nAgenda: Capture the assassin who is causing panic among \nthe nobles / Avoid a popular uprising.\nBeáta Czernin the Noblewoman</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Capture the assassin who is causing panic among \nthe nobles / Avoid a popular uprising.\nBeáta Czernin the Noblewoman","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":2100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637466,"modifiedTime":1781