{"_id":"FaMGvGQBVQr3gyS9","name":"Nature Rises Up","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"v7gpNO9TWLz7EYan","name":"Nature Rises Up - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Nature Rises Up","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Navigating inside the lair without the consent of the Cauldron Fae \nexposes the intruders to the ire of the many plants. Ivy tentacles and pollen mists rise to \nblock those who walk without their lady’s approval.\nMtyrya the Fairy also called the \nCauldron Fae</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 85.","positive":"Navigating inside the lair without the consent of the Cauldron Fae \nexposes the intruders to the ire of the many plants. Ivy tentacles and pollen mists rise to \nblock those who walk without their lady’s approval.\nMtyrya the Fairy also called the \nCauldron Fae","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Nature Rises Up","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625700,"modifiedTime":1781557625700,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"nWKNO1L19tKkpH2u","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Nature Rises Up","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: Navigating inside the lair without the consent of the Cauldron Fae \nexposes the intruders to the ire of the many plants. Ivy tentacles and pollen mists rise to \nblock those who walk without their lady’s approval.\nMtyrya the Fairy also called the \nCauldron Fae</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 85.","owner":"Nature Rises Up","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625700,"modifiedTime":1781557625700,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"014did82003r90kn","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-dont-believe-nature-rises-up-85","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","adventureTitle":"I Don't Believe","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":85,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Don't Believe","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: Navigating inside the lair without the consent of the Cauldron Fae \nexposes the intruders to the ire of the many plants. Ivy tentacles and pollen mists rise to \nblock those who walk without their lady’s approval.\nMtyrya the Fairy also called the \nCauldron Fae</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":2200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625700,"modifiedTime":1781557625700,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"FaUuRuYnM40gvpT8","name":"Francisca and Marta the Vengeful Sisters","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"xnsQsB5RLk0eom5r","name":"Francisca and Marta the Vengeful Sisters - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Francisca and Marta the Vengeful Sisters","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are two poor sisters sewn together in one \nbody. We move with perfect coordination and cooperate \neffortlessly, each aiding the other against any danger.</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 157.","positive":"We are two poor sisters sewn together in one \nbody. We move with perfect coordination and cooperate \neffortlessly, each aiding the other against any danger.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Francisca and Marta the Vengeful Sisters","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637117,"modifiedTime":1781557637117,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"V4dZzI201IN4xNQD","name":"Gift - The Razor-sharp Glass Slippers","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Francisca and Marta the Vengeful Sisters","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Thanks to \nthe magical slippers the Kind Mother gave them, at every \nstep Francisca and Marta can click the glass heels and create \na resonance that generates a state of confusion in subjects \nwithin forty feet. When a Hunter acts under the influence \nof the Slippers, they must perform a Defense Check against</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 157.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Francisca and Marta the Vengeful Sisters","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637117,"modifiedTime":1781557637117,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"RafpHmj6TC7QMIc8","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Francisca and Marta the Vengeful Sisters","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are two poor sisters sewn together in one \nbody. We move with perfect coordination and cooperate \neffortlessly, each aiding the other against any danger. \nAgenda: Discredit Princesca and reveal to everyone that \nshe is Cinder, our despised sister.\nGift – The Razor-sharp Glass Slippers: Thanks to \nthe magical slippers the Kind Mother gave them, at every \nstep Francisca and Marta can click the glass heels and create \na resonance that generates a state of confusion in subjects \nwithin forty feet. When a Hunter acts under the influence \nof the Slippers, they must perform a Defense Check against</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 157.","owner":"Francisca and Marta the Vengeful Sisters","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637117,"modifiedTime":1781557637117,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"01x05lkv00q27p8a","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-in-your-eyes-with-your-feet-francisca-and-marta-the-vengeful-sisters-157","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"in-your-eyes-with-your-feet","adventureTitle":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":157,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are two poor sisters sewn together in one \nbody. We move with perfect coordination and cooperate \neffortlessly, each aiding the other against any danger. \nAgenda: Discredit Princesca and reveal to everyone that \nshe is Cinder, our despised sister.\nGift – The Razor-sharp Glass Slippers: Thanks to \nthe magical slippers the Kind Mother gave them, at every \nstep Francisca and Marta can click the glass heels and create \na resonance that generates a state of confusion in subjects \nwithin forty feet. When a Hunter acts under the influence \nof the Slippers, they must perform a Defense Check against</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Discredit Princesca and reveal to everyone that \nshe is Cinder, our despised sister.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":2300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637117,"modifiedTime":1781557637117,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"FxfgNMMiWALQdDwe","name":"Pietro Gonsalva Regent of Capodimonte","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"kUxdiLNGAGDAIHCW","name":"Pietro Gonsalva Regent of Capodimonte - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Pietro Gonsalva Regent of Capodimonte","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a rich and powerful nobleman, and I have \nmanaged to ingratiate myself with the Papal State. I love being \nin charge, but over time I’ve learned to trust those who are more \nexperienced than I am.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 125.","positive":"I am a rich and powerful nobleman, and I have \nmanaged to ingratiate myself with the Papal State. I love being \nin charge, but over time I’ve learned to trust those who are more \nexperienced than I am.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Pietro Gonsalva Regent of Capodimonte","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629741,"modifiedTime":1781557629741,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"1s0t1KveqH0bavht","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Pietro Gonsalva Regent of Capodimonte","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a rich and powerful nobleman, and I have \nmanaged to ingratiate myself with the Papal State. I love being \nin charge, but over time I’ve learned to trust those who are more \nexperienced than I am.\nAgenda: Preserve the House of Roses because it is the first \nplace where Dionysus appears to be restrained / Not to lose the \nadvantageous agreements made with the Church.\nInformation from the conversation with Pietro: \nThe Regent of Capodimonte will welcome the Hunters with \nall honors, praising their importance to the Church and for \nhumanity’ salvation. Pietro is sincerely respectful of the work \nof the Order. \n ◆ Pietro will say that the island was once a monastery and \nthat, thanks to the efforts of his son Dionysus, it has now \nreturned to a renewed splendor.\n ◆ Martana Island has become a place of worship, where \npeople can take refuge and contemplate God.\n ◆ Pietro cares a lot about the House of Roses because \nhis son Dionysus is suffering from a rare disease that \ncovers his whole body with hair and, unfortunately, his \nmonstrous aspect is not accepted by society. To Pietro, it</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 125.","owner":"Pietro Gonsalva Regent of Capodimonte","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629741,"modifiedTime":1781557629741,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"00o6rita00gfb6tn","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-pietro-gonsalva-regent-of-capodimonte-125","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":125,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a rich and powerful nobleman, and I have \nmanaged to ingratiate myself with the Papal State. I love being \nin charge, but over time I’ve learned to trust those who are more \nexperienced than I am.\nAgenda: Preserve the House of Roses because it is the first \nplace where Dionysus appears to be restrained / Not to lose the \nadvantageous agreements made with the Church.\nInformation from the conversation with Pietro: \nThe Regent of Capodimonte will welcome the Hunters with \nall honors, praising their importance to the Church and for \nhumanity’ salvation. Pietro is sincerely respectful of the work \nof the Order. \n ◆ Pietro will say that the island was once a monastery and \nthat, thanks to the efforts of his son Dionysus, it has now \nreturned to a renewed splendor.\n ◆ Martana Island has become a place of worship, where \npeople can take refuge and contemplate God.\n ◆ Pietro cares a lot about the House of Roses because \nhis son Dionysus is suffering from a rare disease that \ncovers his whole body with hair and, unfortunately, his \nmonstrous aspect is not accepted by society. To Pietro, it</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Preserve the House of Roses because it is the first \nplace where Dionysus appears to be restrained / Not to lose the \nadvantageous agreements made with the Church.\nInformation from the conversation with Pietro: \nThe Regent of Capodimonte will welcome the Hunters with \nall honors, praising their importance to the Church and for \nhumanity’ salvation. Pietro is sincerely respectful of the work \nof the Order. \n ◆ Pietro will say that the island was once a monastery and \nthat, thanks to the efforts of his son Dionysus, it has now \nreturned to a renewed splendor.\n ◆ Martana Island has become a place of worship, where \npeople can take refuge and contemplate God.\n ◆ Pietro cares a lot about the House of Roses because \nhis son Dionysus is suffering from a rare disease that \ncovers his whole body with hair and, unfortunately, his \nmonstrous aspect is not accepted by society. To Pietro, it","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":2400000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629741,"modifiedTime":1781557629741,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"IbkEWPGQlm3LQ22J","name":"Cernobog Potmešil The Child","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"1yKSugmpoEPv8lzy","name":"Cernobog Potmešil The Child - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Cernobog Potmešil The Child","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The rubies I received allowed me to recover \nfrom the fever that had plagued me and, thanks to them, I \nam now strong and healthy, but at what price? I feel anger \nand resentment towards those who live on the shoulders of \nthe poor people of Prague.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 173.","positive":"The rubies I received allowed me to recover \nfrom the fever that had plagued me and, thanks to them, I \nam now strong and healthy, but at what price? I feel anger \nand resentment towards those who live on the shoulders of \nthe poor people of Prague.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Cernobog Potmešil The Child","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637921,"modifiedTime":1781557637921,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"HWMnvrryHnhwQJpr","name":"Gift - The Ruby of Hate","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Cernobog Potmešil The Child","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Černobog uses one of the two \nrubies he obtained from the Swallow as bait to achieve \nhis goals. When he distracts someone with the ruby, he \nprevents the use of a Gift for the duration of the Scene. If \nthe ruby is crushed, Černobog suffers 1 Wound.\nPrague Castle\nRead aloud to the Hunters: On the evening of the party, \nyou are greeted in the majestic ballroom of Prague Castle. \nA cascade of crystal chandeliers illuminates white arches \nfinished with gold, while large mirrors magnify the already \nremarkable size of the room, full of people dressed elegantly. \nYou hear your name announced aloud, and everyone seems \nintrigued by your presence. Ostromir introduces you to the \nvarious families of the city, but despite the superficially happy \natmosphere, the tension is palpable.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 173.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Cernobog Potmešil The Child","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637921,"modifiedTime":1781557637921,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"qZ9tSKaElkIDaOa5","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Cernobog Potmešil The Child","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: The rubies I received allowed me to recover \nfrom the fever that had plagued me and, thanks to them, I \nam now strong and healthy, but at what price? I feel anger \nand resentment towards those who live on the shoulders of \nthe poor people of Prague. \nAgenda: Avenge my struggling mother / Make sure the rich \npay for their crimes.\nGift - The Ruby of Hate: Černobog uses one of the two \nrubies he obtained from the Swallow as bait to achieve \nhis goals. When he distracts someone with the ruby, he \nprevents the use of a Gift for the duration of the Scene. If \nthe ruby is crushed, Černobog suffers 1 Wound.\nPrague Castle\nRead aloud to the Hunters: On the evening of the party, \nyou are greeted in the majestic ballroom of Prague Castle. \nA cascade of crystal chandeliers illuminates white arches \nfinished with gold, while large mirrors magnify the already \nremarkable size of the room, full of people dressed elegantly. \nYou hear your name announced aloud, and everyone seems \nintrigued by your presence. Ostromir introduces you to the \nvarious families of the city, but despite the superficially happy \natmosphere, the tension is palpable. \nDescriptor: The great and magnificent Prague Castle.\nWhen the ball is at its busiest, a wall will be violently \ndestroyed by a large creature of flesh and metal crashing \n^^</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 173.","owner":"Cernobog Potmešil The Child","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637921,"modifiedTime":1781557637921,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"01gakz6800ms75vx","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-will-stay-with-you-always-cernobog-potme-il-the-child-173","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-will-stay-with-you-always","adventureTitle":"I Will Stay with You Always","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":173,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Will Stay with You Always","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: The rubies I received allowed me to recover \nfrom the fever that had plagued me and, thanks to them, I \nam now strong and healthy, but at what price? I feel anger \nand resentment towards those who live on the shoulders of \nthe poor people of Prague. \nAgenda: Avenge my struggling mother / Make sure the rich \npay for their crimes.\nGift - The Ruby of Hate: Černobog uses one of the two \nrubies he obtained from the Swallow as bait to achieve \nhis goals. When he distracts someone with the ruby, he \nprevents the use of a Gift for the duration of the Scene. If \nthe ruby is crushed, Černobog suffers 1 Wound.\nPrague Castle\nRead aloud to the Hunters: On the evening of the party, \nyou are greeted in the majestic ballroom of Prague Castle. \nA cascade of crystal chandeliers illuminates white arches \nfinished with gold, while large mirrors magnify the already \nremarkable size of the room, full of people dressed elegantly. \nYou hear your name announced aloud, and everyone seems \nintrigued by your presence. Ostromir introduces you to the \nvarious families of the city, but despite the superficially happy \natmosphere, the tension is palpable. \nDescriptor: The great and magnificent Prague Castle.\nWhen the ball is at its busiest, a wall will be violently \ndestroyed by a large creature of flesh and metal crashing \n^^</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Avenge my struggling mother / Make sure the rich \npay for their crimes.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":2500000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637921,"modifiedTime":1781557637921,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"IzC7Qbc2FXzmUU2L","name":"Lisbet","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Pmf2llejd0ACr2pu","name":"Lisbet - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lisbet","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young widow and I settled in the village \nto start anew. I have experienced many misfortunes in my life, \nwhich have forced me to become stubborn and strong-willed. \nHowever, I’ve managed to stay kind and generous.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 143.","positive":"I am a young widow and I settled in the village \nto start anew. I have experienced many misfortunes in my life, \nwhich have forced me to become stubborn and strong-willed. \nHowever, I’ve managed to stay kind and generous.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Lisbet","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636357,"modifiedTime":1781557636357,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ReitLbLs1fJwDcs1","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lisbet","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a young widow and I settled in the village \nto start anew. I have experienced many misfortunes in my life, \nwhich have forced me to become stubborn and strong-willed. \nHowever, I’ve managed to stay kind and generous.\nAgenda: To save all the prisoners by convincing Talia to do \nthe right thing. \nThe Dungeons\nDescriptor: A series of tunnels and galleries full of barred \ndoors leading to the treasure room.\nTalia the Sleeper</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 143.","owner":"Lisbet","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636357,"modifiedTime":1781557636357,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"019bylki016ws0df","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-stegeborgs-quiet-lisbet-143","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"stegeborgs-quiet","adventureTitle":"Stegeborg's Quiet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":143,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Stegeborg's Quiet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a young widow and I settled in the village \nto start anew. I have experienced many misfortunes in my life, \nwhich have forced me to become stubborn and strong-willed. \nHowever, I’ve managed to stay kind and generous.\nAgenda: To save all the prisoners by convincing Talia to do \nthe right thing. \nThe Dungeons\nDescriptor: A series of tunnels and galleries full of barred \ndoors leading to the treasure room.\nTalia the Sleeper</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To save all the prisoners by convincing Talia to do \nthe right thing. \nThe Dungeons\nDescriptor: A series of tunnels and galleries full of barred \ndoors leading to the treasure room.\nTalia the Sleeper","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":2600000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636357,"modifiedTime":1781557636357,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"IzG9GpTHpv1ztm4Z","name":"Georg Slanina the Helper","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"1xjq9hLrCvQTcFZa","name":"Georg Slanina the Helper - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Georg Slanina the Helper","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I work very hard. I like to drink, and when I \ndo, I become a beast.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 168.","positive":"I work very hard. I like to drink, and when I \ndo, I become a beast.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Georg Slanina the Helper","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637733,"modifiedTime":1781557637733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"lQRpeiMk94WkCxJf","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Georg Slanina the Helper","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I work very hard. I like to drink, and when I \ndo, I become a beast. \nAgenda: Supporting my daughter, who now has to sell \nmatches on the street / Understanding why Konstantin fired \nme.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 168.","owner":"Georg Slanina the Helper","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637733,"modifiedTime":1781557637733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"01gakz6800ms75vx","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-will-stay-with-you-always-georg-slanina-the-helper-168","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-will-stay-with-you-always","adventureTitle":"I Will Stay with You Always","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":168,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Will Stay with You Always","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I work very hard. I like to drink, and when I \ndo, I become a beast. \nAgenda: Supporting my daughter, who now has to sell \nmatches on the street / Understanding why Konstantin fired \nme.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Supporting my daughter, who now has to sell \nmatches on the street / Understanding why Konstantin fired \nme.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":2700000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637733,"modifiedTime":1781557637733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"JWJCA3Pc9ABKVllm","name":"Akim the Tamer","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"mxuRidMcVy91cYIH","name":"Akim the Tamer - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Akim the Tamer","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a brave and skilled \ntamer. The tiger Tasha and the bear \nBerto are both dear to me, as they obey \nmy every command.</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 158.","positive":"I am a brave and skilled \ntamer. The tiger Tasha and the bear \nBerto are both dear to me, as they obey \nmy every command.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Akim the Tamer","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637149,"modifiedTime":1781557637149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"VyTAIyfjwtqMHqhI","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Akim the Tamer","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a brave and skilled \ntamer. The tiger Tasha and the bear \nBerto are both dear to me, as they obey \nmy every command.\nAgenda: Perform and amaze the \naudience with my animals / Prevent \nanyone from harming Tasha and \nBerto, whom I consider as my children.\nScenario Events\nIn this Scenario, there are six Events. As a Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the \nHunters.\nIf the Hunters keep Princesca informed of the \ninvestigation: the clever woman will quickly understand \nthat someone is framing her and will send Eduardo and \nFelipe to deal with the Kind Mother. If the Hunters don’t do \nsomething, the old witch won’t escape her fate. \nIf the Hunters defeat Francisca and Marta: the two \nsisters will tell them everything they know, imploring the \nHunters to help expose Cinder.\nIf the Hunters unmask Cinder: The Countess will \nuse the power of her magic to escape and run to the Kind \nMother for her help. Once she regains her voice thanks to \nCinder’s use of Wish, the Kind Mother will assist Cinder \nto eliminate the Hunters and then take her time making \nCinder pay. \nIf the Hunters understand who the Kind Mother \nreally is: The witch will offer her aid in exchange for her \nlife and will seek their help in regaining her voice. \nIf the Hunters seek the support of Azul: The Count \nwill pretend to be a fool and will even avoid taking measures \nagainst Cinder once she has been unmasked. The man is \nso willfully ignorant that he will ban the Hunters from the \ncity in order to keep his wife where she is, managing all the \nresponsibilities so he can lead a life of laziness. \nIf the Hunters trap Cinder during the anniversary \nparty: The woman will use magic to take control of Tasha \nand Berto, sending them against the Hunters. Akim will \nhinder the Hunters if they try to harm his beloved animals. \nCinder will try to escape to the Kind Mother by taking \nadvantage of the chaos. \nTasha the Tiger</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 158.","owner":"Akim the Tamer","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637149,"modifiedTime":1781557637149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"01x05lkv00q27p8a","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-in-your-eyes-with-your-feet-akim-the-tamer-158","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"in-your-eyes-with-your-feet","adventureTitle":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":158,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a brave and skilled \ntamer. The tiger Tasha and the bear \nBerto are both dear to me, as they obey \nmy every command.\nAgenda: Perform and amaze the \naudience with my animals / Prevent \nanyone from harming Tasha and \nBerto, whom I consider as my children.\nScenario Events\nIn this Scenario, there are six Events. As a Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the \nHunters.\nIf the Hunters keep Princesca informed of the \ninvestigation: the clever woman will quickly understand \nthat someone is framing her and will send Eduardo and \nFelipe to deal with the Kind Mother. If the Hunters don’t do \nsomething, the old witch won’t escape her fate. \nIf the Hunters defeat Francisca and Marta: the two \nsisters will tell them everything they know, imploring the \nHunters to help expose Cinder.\nIf the Hunters unmask Cinder: The Countess will \nuse the power of her magic to escape and run to the Kind \nMother for her help. Once she regains her voice thanks to \nCinder’s use of Wish, the Kind Mother will assist Cinder \nto eliminate the Hunters and then take her time making \nCinder pay. \nIf the Hunters understand who the Kind Mother \nreally is: The witch will offer her aid in exchange for her \nlife and will seek their help in regaining her voice. \nIf the Hunters seek the support of Azul: The Count \nwill pretend to be a fool and will even avoid taking measures \nagainst Cinder once she has been unmasked. The man is \nso willfully ignorant that he will ban the Hunters from the \ncity in order to keep his wife where she is, managing all the \nresponsibilities so he can lead a life of laziness. \nIf the Hunters trap Cinder during the anniversary \nparty: The woman will use magic to take control of Tasha \nand Berto, sending them against the Hunters. Akim will \nhinder the Hunters if they try to harm his beloved animals. \nCinder will try to escape to the Kind Mother by taking \nadvantage of the chaos. \nTasha the Tiger</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Perform and amaze the \naudience with my animals / Prevent \nanyone from harming Tasha and \nBerto, whom I consider as my children.\nScenario Events\nIn this Scenario, there are six Events. As a Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the \nHunters.\nIf the Hunters keep Princesca informed of the \ninvestigation: the clever woman will quickly understand \nthat someone is framing her and will send Eduardo and \nFelipe to deal with the Kind Mother. If the Hunters don’t do \nsomething, the old witch won’t escape her fate. \nIf the Hunters defeat Francisca and Marta: the two \nsisters will tell them everything they know, imploring the \nHunters to help expose Cinder.\nIf the Hunters unmask Cinder: The Countess will \nuse the power of her magic to escape and run to the Kind \nMother for her help. Once she regains her voice thanks to \nCinder’s use of Wish, the Kind Mother will assist Cinder \nto eliminate the Hunters and then take her time making \nCinder pay. \nIf the Hunters understand who the Kind Mother \nreally is: The witch will offer her aid in exchange for her \nlife and will seek their help in regaining her voice. \nIf the Hunters seek the support of Azul: The Count \nwill pretend to be a fool and will even avoid taking measures \nagainst Cinder once she has been unmasked. The man is \nso willfully ignorant that he will ban the Hunters from the \ncity in order to keep his wife where she is, managing all the \nresponsibilities so he can lead a life of laziness. \nIf the Hunters trap Cinder during the anniversary \nparty: The woman will use magic to take control of Tasha \nand Berto, sending them against the Hunters. Akim will \nhinder the Hunters if they try to harm his beloved animals. \nCinder will try to escape to the Kind Mother by taking \nadvantage of the chaos. \nTasha the Tiger","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":2800000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637149,"modifiedTime":1781557637149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"JjhywroInzrid2j7","name":"The Doves","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"txCqaVKbLWh90dN3","name":"The Doves - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Doves","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are two doves enslaved by the power of \nCinder. Magic has permanently broken our will and we \ndefend our mistress from all danger.</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 155.","positive":"We are two doves enslaved by the power of \nCinder. Magic has permanently broken our will and we \ndefend our mistress from all danger.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Doves","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637013,"modifiedTime":1781557637013,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"BRdjHVbvlE5SsdHy","name":"Gift - Go for the Eyes","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Doves","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Doves are skilled at hitting \nthe enemies’ weak spots. When a Dove manages to inflict a \nWound, it inflicts 1 additional Wound. In case of a positive \nOutcome in a Defense Check, once per Scene, the Dove’s \nattack will still inflict 1 Wound. This Gift cannot be used \nmore than once against the same target \nduring the Scenario.\nThe Port of Vigo</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 155.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Doves","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637013,"modifiedTime":1781557637013,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"2HtGmSl6Sr0H2Xua","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Doves","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are two doves enslaved by the power of \nCinder. Magic has permanently broken our will and we \ndefend our mistress from all danger. \nGift – Go for the Eyes: The Doves are skilled at hitting \nthe enemies’ weak spots. When a Dove manages to inflict a \nWound, it inflicts 1 additional Wound. In case of a positive \nOutcome in a Defense Check, once per Scene, the Dove’s \nattack will still inflict 1 Wound. This Gift cannot be used \nmore than once against the same target \nduring the Scenario.\nThe Port of Vigo\nDescriptor: The great city’s port where ships from all over \nthe world are docked. The alleys in front of the port are a \ncrossroads of taverns, shops, and leisure houses. Even in the \nmiddle of the night, there’s always life in the harbor. \nInformation: The Old Spinner resides in a small house \nin the eastern part of the pier, while the last corpse was \nfound in the western area.\nEast of the pier: The Hunters will be able to meet the \nKind Mother, who will present herself as an old silent \nseamstress. Cinder knows that the spinner is the Kind \nMother, but gives no sign that she knows. The old witch \nwill communicate with the Hunters with some difficulty \nand give them a brooch she found near the alley where \nshe saw the two cloaked silhouettes pass. The brooch bears \nthe coat of arms of the Di Bello family: the Kind Mother \nherself will give directions to the Di Bello house, located in \nthe upper quarters of the city. The old witch will not follow \nthe Hunters, as she does not want to be seen by Francisca \nand Marta.\nWest of the pier: The Hunters will find Eduardo and \nFelipe, two guards at the service of the Count of Vigo, \nguarding the crime scene. The body of the young prostitute \n(known as Estella) was moved to the icebox of an old fish \nwarehouse nearby.\n ◆ The two guards will tell the Hunters that no one has \nclaimed her body. She is most likely one of the many \npoor people just trying to get by. \n ◆ Examining Estella’s body will confirm the removal \nof all facial skin, performed with insane care. A very</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 155.","owner":"The Doves","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637013,"modifiedTime":1781557637013,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"01x05lkv00q27p8a","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-in-your-eyes-with-your-feet-the-doves-155","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"in-your-eyes-with-your-feet","adventureTitle":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":155,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are two doves enslaved by the power of \nCinder. Magic has permanently broken our will and we \ndefend our mistress from all danger. \nGift – Go for the Eyes: The Doves are skilled at hitting \nthe enemies’ weak spots. When a Dove manages to inflict a \nWound, it inflicts 1 additional Wound. In case of a positive \nOutcome in a Defense Check, once per Scene, the Dove’s \nattack will still inflict 1 Wound. This Gift cannot be used \nmore than once against the same target \nduring the Scenario.\nThe Port of Vigo\nDescriptor: The great city’s port where ships from all over \nthe world are docked. The alleys in front of the port are a \ncrossroads of taverns, shops, and leisure houses. Even in the \nmiddle of the night, there’s always life in the harbor. \nInformation: The Old Spinner resides in a small house \nin the eastern part of the pier, while the last corpse was \nfound in the western area.\nEast of the pier: The Hunters will be able to meet the \nKind Mother, who will present herself as an old silent \nseamstress. Cinder knows that the spinner is the Kind \nMother, but gives no sign that she knows. The old witch \nwill communicate with the Hunters with some difficulty \nand give them a brooch she found near the alley where \nshe saw the two cloaked silhouettes pass. The brooch bears \nthe coat of arms of the Di Bello family: the Kind Mother \nherself will give directions to the Di Bello house, located in \nthe upper quarters of the city. The old witch will not follow \nthe Hunters, as she does not want to be seen by Francisca \nand Marta.\nWest of the pier: The Hunters will find Eduardo and \nFelipe, two guards at the service of the Count of Vigo, \nguarding the crime scene. The body of the young prostitute \n(known as Estella) was moved to the icebox of an old fish \nwarehouse nearby.\n ◆ The two guards will tell the Hunters that no one has \nclaimed her body. She is most likely one of the many \npoor people just trying to get by. \n ◆ Examining Estella’s body will confirm the removal \nof all facial skin, performed with insane care. A very</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":2900000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637013,"modifiedTime":1781557637013,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"KAi3KmZt2mF0k7Es","name":"George Carnarvon","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"PSoO96E8aCTIrGHA","name":"George Carnarvon - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"George Carnarvon","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the head of the Carnarvon family and my \nservice to the Crown has brought me a great deal of influence. \nI fear the occult and magic. I can’t sleep due to worry over my \ndaughter’s abduction.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 84.","positive":"I am the head of the Carnarvon family and my \nservice to the Crown has brought me a great deal of influence. \nI fear the occult and magic. I can’t sleep due to worry over my \ndaughter’s abduction.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"George Carnarvon","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Ig92uT0R44Z3jPPj","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"George Carnarvon","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the head of the Carnarvon family and my \nservice to the Crown has brought me a great deal of influence. \nI fear the occult and magic. I can’t sleep due to worry over my \ndaughter’s abduction.\nAgenda: Stop the gang of rebels that plagues London, but \nmore than anything else find my beloved daughter Gwendolyn.\nCarnarvon House\nDescriptor: A rich and large mansion in the heart of \nLondon.\nJoanna called Nana the Servant</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 84.","owner":"George Carnarvon","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"014did82003r90kn","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-dont-believe-george-carnarvon-84","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","adventureTitle":"I Don't Believe","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":84,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Don't Believe","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the head of the Carnarvon family and my \nservice to the Crown has brought me a great deal of influence. \nI fear the occult and magic. I can’t sleep due to worry over my \ndaughter’s abduction.\nAgenda: Stop the gang of rebels that plagues London, but \nmore than anything else find my beloved daughter Gwendolyn.\nCarnarvon House\nDescriptor: A rich and large mansion in the heart of \nLondon.\nJoanna called Nana the Servant</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Stop the gang of rebels that plagues London, but \nmore than anything else find my beloved daughter Gwendolyn.\nCarnarvon House\nDescriptor: A rich and large mansion in the heart of \nLondon.\nJoanna called Nana the Servant","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":3000000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId"