{"_id":"MDneQMpkrawIQYAi","name":"Georg the Survivor","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"753psErBEub0wng1","name":"Georg the Survivor - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Georg the Survivor","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I’m a poor laborer without a family. I once was \nliving in the streets.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 138.","positive":"I’m a poor laborer without a family. I once was \nliving in the streets.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Georg the Survivor","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636197,"modifiedTime":1781557636197,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"tbpoIN3rcjAf7XrS","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Georg the Survivor","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I’m a poor laborer without a family. I once was \nliving in the streets.\nAgenda: Escape from Stegeborg as soon as possible, so I can \nleave what I saw behind me and start a new life.\nThe Quiet Guards</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 138.","owner":"Georg the Survivor","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636197,"modifiedTime":1781557636197,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"019bylki016ws0df","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-stegeborgs-quiet-georg-the-survivor-138","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"stegeborgs-quiet","adventureTitle":"Stegeborg's Quiet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":138,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Stegeborg's Quiet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I’m a poor laborer without a family. I once was \nliving in the streets.\nAgenda: Escape from Stegeborg as soon as possible, so I can \nleave what I saw behind me and start a new life.\nThe Quiet Guards</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Escape from Stegeborg as soon as possible, so I can \nleave what I saw behind me and start a new life.\nThe Quiet Guards","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":3200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636197,"modifiedTime":1781557636197,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"MSlkQ7k9UhlLPZe3","name":"Dioniso Gonsalva called the Beast","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"nEkmJsqQzbqfy7oT","name":"Dioniso Gonsalva called the Beast - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dioniso Gonsalva called the Beast","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young man afflicted by a curse \nthat turned me into a fierce beast. Only Bella’s scent \nkeeps my incredible ferocity in check.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 130.","positive":"I am a young man afflicted by a curse \nthat turned me into a fierce beast. Only Bella’s scent \nkeeps my incredible ferocity in check.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Dioniso Gonsalva called the Beast","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632137,"modifiedTime":1781557632137,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"F5yC9R5kmhjoPuYO","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dioniso Gonsalva called the Beast","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young man afflicted by a curse \nthat turned me into a fierce beast. Only Bella’s scent \nkeeps my incredible ferocity in check.\nAgenda: I would like to live alone with Bella \nin this paradise, and I only tolerate the House \nof Roses for the sake of my love for her / I \nwould like to show the full extent of my love \nto Bella, but until she gives herself to me, I \nwill have to take my frustration out on \nher handmaids.\nGift – The Beast: Dionysus can \nact twice during an Exchange. When \nmoving, Dionysus can jump up to thirty \nfeet and easily destroy any obstacle. \nWhen acting to save Bella, Dionysus \nincreases his Opposition Level by 1.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 130.","owner":"Dioniso Gonsalva called the Beast","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632137,"modifiedTime":1781557632137,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"00o6rita00gfb6tn","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-dioniso-gonsalva-called-the-beast-130","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":130,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young man afflicted by a curse \nthat turned me into a fierce beast. Only Bella’s scent \nkeeps my incredible ferocity in check.\nAgenda: I would like to live alone with Bella \nin this paradise, and I only tolerate the House \nof Roses for the sake of my love for her / I \nwould like to show the full extent of my love \nto Bella, but until she gives herself to me, I \nwill have to take my frustration out on \nher handmaids.\nGift – The Beast: Dionysus can \nact twice during an Exchange. When \nmoving, Dionysus can jump up to thirty \nfeet and easily destroy any obstacle. \nWhen acting to save Bella, Dionysus \nincreases his Opposition Level by 1.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I would like to live alone with Bella \nin this paradise, and I only tolerate the House \nof Roses for the sake of my love for her / I \nwould like to show the full extent of my love \nto Bella, but until she gives herself to me, I \nwill have to take my frustration out on \nher handmaids.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":3300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632137,"modifiedTime":1781557632137,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"PthHXRiJUYJdGSzL","name":"The Gang of the Lost Boys","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"E6k4gyKMgC8447Os","name":"The Gang of the Lost Boys - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Gang of the Lost Boys","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are young rebels who have lost everything \nand are ready to die for our leader Pietrik.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 88.","positive":"We are young rebels who have lost everything \nand are ready to die for our leader Pietrik.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Gang of the Lost Boys","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625775,"modifiedTime":1781557625775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Igapo7f1Bp9Yv7LV","name":"Gift - Gang Seal","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Gang of the Lost Boys","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Each gang member has a tattooed eye \non their right hand that allows them to see and use the Seals \nof the Cauldron Fae scattered throughout London.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 88.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Gang of the Lost Boys","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625775,"modifiedTime":1781557625775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"CmMngv5O4K7k0yCq","name":"Gift - Rioter","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Gang of the Lost Boys","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Each gang member increases his OL by \n1 when acting with the support of at least one teammate. \nEach member has a magic berry that they can throw which \nwill explode on contact, inflicting 1 Wound on all targets \nwithin several feet. A Defense Check allows a target to leap \naway from the blast zone. \nKensington Gardens</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 88.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Gang of the Lost Boys","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625775,"modifiedTime":1781557625775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"i8FwIcX5aAi3sOoY","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Gang of the Lost Boys","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are young rebels who have lost everything \nand are ready to die for our leader Pietrik.\nAgenda: To help Pietrik in his plan for the destruction of \nLondon. \nGift – Gang Seal: Each gang member has a tattooed eye \non their right hand that allows them to see and use the Seals \nof the Cauldron Fae scattered throughout London.\nGift – Rioter: Each gang member increases his OL by \n1 when acting with the support of at least one teammate. \nEach member has a magic berry that they can throw which \nwill explode on contact, inflicting 1 Wound on all targets \nwithin several feet. A Defense Check allows a target to leap \naway from the blast zone. \nKensington Gardens\nDescriptor: A large green area in the heart of London. \nAccess to the gardens is prohibited due to ongoing \nmaintenance work. \nInformation: The Kensington Gardens have been long \nabandoned because the Cauldron Fae uses her magic to \ncreate unending problems for the gardeners. No one has \nentered the gardens for over a year and Pietrik has used an \nold gardeners’ house as a prison to keep Gwendolyn locked \nup. The girl hasn’t tried to escape and hopes, so far in vain, \nto convince Pietrik to give up on his destructive plans. \nIt is possible to descend through a well in \nthe eastern part of the park to access the \nCauldron Fae’s Lair. \nSeals: The Gardens are literally full of \nSeals.\nGwendolyn</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 88.","owner":"The Gang of the Lost Boys","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625775,"modifiedTime":1781557625775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"014did82003r90kn","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-dont-believe-the-gang-of-the-lost-boys-88","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","adventureTitle":"I Don't Believe","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":88,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Don't Believe","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are young rebels who have lost everything \nand are ready to die for our leader Pietrik.\nAgenda: To help Pietrik in his plan for the destruction of \nLondon. \nGift – Gang Seal: Each gang member has a tattooed eye \non their right hand that allows them to see and use the Seals \nof the Cauldron Fae scattered throughout London.\nGift – Rioter: Each gang member increases his OL by \n1 when acting with the support of at least one teammate. \nEach member has a magic berry that they can throw which \nwill explode on contact, inflicting 1 Wound on all targets \nwithin several feet. A Defense Check allows a target to leap \naway from the blast zone. \nKensington Gardens\nDescriptor: A large green area in the heart of London. \nAccess to the gardens is prohibited due to ongoing \nmaintenance work. \nInformation: The Kensington Gardens have been long \nabandoned because the Cauldron Fae uses her magic to \ncreate unending problems for the gardeners. No one has \nentered the gardens for over a year and Pietrik has used an \nold gardeners’ house as a prison to keep Gwendolyn locked \nup. The girl hasn’t tried to escape and hopes, so far in vain, \nto convince Pietrik to give up on his destructive plans. \nIt is possible to descend through a well in \nthe eastern part of the park to access the \nCauldron Fae’s Lair. \nSeals: The Gardens are literally full of \nSeals.\nGwendolyn</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"To help Pietrik in his plan for the destruction of \nLondon.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":3400000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625775,"modifiedTime":1781557625775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"S3fURzRdz5ipCa6j","name":"Abel the Young Lover","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"pJAvRNB6Moi8x64b","name":"Abel the Young Lover - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Abel the Young Lover","source":"Bloodwhite's Heart","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young baker who has always been in \nlove with Bianca.</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 112.","positive":"I am a young baker who has always been in \nlove with Bianca.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Abel the Young Lover","source":"Bloodwhite's Heart","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628486,"modifiedTime":1781557628486,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"xZ16QXDaMmes9FY8","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Abel the Young Lover","source":"Bloodwhite's Heart","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a young baker who has always been in \nlove with Bianca.\nAgenda: To find Bianca, as I cannot believe that she has \nabandoned Lohr, nor that her parents would let her go so \neasily.\nSvenn’s House\nDescriptor: A beautiful manor house, now converted \ninto a museum of hunting trophies.\nInformation: Svenn will greet the Hunters \nwith kindness, boasting that he is the man the \nKarenmann family trusts the most. Svenn will tell \nthem of the doubts he has about Old Bruna and \nof the fact that some secrets related to the death \nof Ottone could be hidden in the woman’s house. \nSvenn will advise the Hunters to act with caution, \nso as not to alarm the inhabitants of Lohr, but he \nwill make himself available to distract the woman, \ndriving her away from home with an excuse.</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 112.","owner":"Abel the Young Lover","source":"Bloodwhite's Heart","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628486,"modifiedTime":1781557628486,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"00o4ut1z01pgdx9e","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-bloodwhites-heart-abel-the-young-lover-112","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"bloodwhites-heart","adventureTitle":"Bloodwhite's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":112,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Bloodwhite's Heart","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a young baker who has always been in \nlove with Bianca.\nAgenda: To find Bianca, as I cannot believe that she has \nabandoned Lohr, nor that her parents would let her go so \neasily.\nSvenn’s House\nDescriptor: A beautiful manor house, now converted \ninto a museum of hunting trophies.\nInformation: Svenn will greet the Hunters \nwith kindness, boasting that he is the man the \nKarenmann family trusts the most. Svenn will tell \nthem of the doubts he has about Old Bruna and \nof the fact that some secrets related to the death \nof Ottone could be hidden in the woman’s house. \nSvenn will advise the Hunters to act with caution, \nso as not to alarm the inhabitants of Lohr, but he \nwill make himself available to distract the woman, \ndriving her away from home with an excuse.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"To find Bianca, as I cannot believe that she has \nabandoned Lohr, nor that her parents would let her go so \neasily.\nSvenn’s House\nDescriptor: A beautiful manor house, now converted \ninto a museum of hunting trophies.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":3500000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628486,"modifiedTime":1781557628486,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"TYiUc3rDgAsvl9ql","name":"The Maws","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"3xz1HbsCKa17aLDo","name":"The Maws - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Maws","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are a new people, children of the great \nMaw. Our bodies regenerate thanks to the flesh we eat. Our \nstrength and speed are incredible.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 97.","positive":"We are a new people, children of the great \nMaw. Our bodies regenerate thanks to the flesh we eat. Our \nstrength and speed are incredible.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Maws","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626309,"modifiedTime":1781557626309,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"z9gpQYAKbQqby9cg","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Maws","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are a new people, children of the great \nMaw. Our bodies regenerate thanks to the flesh we eat. Our \nstrength and speed are incredible. \nAgenda: We obey Gréte and Hanse, they are the firstborns, \nthey know the right path / Satiate our infinite hunger, even at \nthe cost of disobeying the firstborns.\nGift – Mutant Maw: As long as they maintain their \noriginal appearance, a mutant Maw appears in every way as \na common child. When they unleash their power, the body \nshifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing \na long line of sharp teeth. A mutant is considered to be of a \nhigher OL category for every physical action they perform \ninvolving speed, strength, or ferocity. A mutant perceives \nthe smell of human flesh, which they find intoxicating, and \nfor this reason every attempt to hide from their sense of \nsmell receives 1 Penalty. When a mutant begins to devour \nflesh (human or animal), they cannot stop until they have \nfinished it. Once per Scene, when a mutant Maw inflicts \n1 Wound by devouring fresh meat, they recover 1 Wound \nthey suffered.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 97.","owner":"The Maws","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626309,"modifiedTime":1781557626309,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"00fisila00bqr0g5","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-hunger-island-the-maws-97","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"hunger-island","adventureTitle":"Hunger Island","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":97,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Hunger Island","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are a new people, children of the great \nMaw. Our bodies regenerate thanks to the flesh we eat. Our \nstrength and speed are incredible. \nAgenda: We obey Gréte and Hanse, they are the firstborns, \nthey know the right path / Satiate our infinite hunger, even at \nthe cost of disobeying the firstborns.\nGift – Mutant Maw: As long as they maintain their \noriginal appearance, a mutant Maw appears in every way as \na common child. When they unleash their power, the body \nshifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing \na long line of sharp teeth. A mutant is considered to be of a \nhigher OL category for every physical action they perform \ninvolving speed, strength, or ferocity. A mutant perceives \nthe smell of human flesh, which they find intoxicating, and \nfor this reason every attempt to hide from their sense of \nsmell receives 1 Penalty. When a mutant begins to devour \nflesh (human or animal), they cannot stop until they have \nfinished it. Once per Scene, when a mutant Maw inflicts \n1 Wound by devouring fresh meat, they recover 1 Wound \nthey suffered.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"We obey Gréte and Hanse, they are the firstborns, \nthey know the right path / Satiate our infinite hunger, even at \nthe cost of disobeying the firstborns.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":3600000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626309,"modifiedTime":1781557626309,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"URi5ONWolZT4U8MV","name":"Dionysus’ Mastiffs","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"y3BoedlEwO8OQFOT","name":"Dionysus’ Mastiffs - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dionysus’ Mastiffs","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are big and fierce mastiffs loyal to our \nleader, Dionysus.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128.","positive":"We are big and fierce mastiffs loyal to our \nleader, Dionysus.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Dionysus’ Mastiffs","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"1HKiPajEOltlavKu","name":"Gift - Pack","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dionysus’ Mastiffs","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Any action taken while surrounded by 2 \nor more Mastiffs receives 1 Penalty. A Mastiff can use its \naction to howl and alert Dionysus, who will arrive within \n2 Exchanges.\nFrancesca Cantalupo</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Dionysus’ Mastiffs","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"U7alNb0sLTD3bTx5","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dionysus’ Mastiffs","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are big and fierce mastiffs loyal to our \nleader, Dionysus.\nAgenda: Hunt down any intruders arriving on the island.\nGift – Pack: Any action taken while surrounded by 2 \nor more Mastiffs receives 1 Penalty. A Mastiff can use its \naction to howl and alert Dionysus, who will arrive within \n2 Exchanges.\nFrancesca Cantalupo</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128.","owner":"Dionysus’ Mastiffs","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"00o6rita00gfb6tn","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-dionysus-mastiffs-128","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":128,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are big and fierce mastiffs loyal to our \nleader, Dionysus.\nAgenda: Hunt down any intruders arriving on the island.\nGift – Pack: Any action taken while surrounded by 2 \nor more Mastiffs receives 1 Penalty. A Mastiff can use its \naction to howl and alert Dionysus, who will arrive within \n2 Exchanges.\nFrancesca Cantalupo</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Hunt down any intruders arriving on the island.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":3700000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"UwJ9K9me766rPKkG","name":"Bianca Karenmann","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"B4jFoLwr2RmuVxB5","name":"Bianca Karenmann - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Bianca Karenmann","source":"Bloodwhite's Heart","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I’m a sweet young girl and I just want to live in \npeace. The power of the curse makes me strong and resilient. \nIt also gives me the power to make living beings explode from \nwithin.</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 117.","positive":"I’m a sweet young girl and I just want to live in \npeace. The power of the curse makes me strong and resilient. \nIt also gives me the power to make living beings explode from \nwithin.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Bianca Karenmann","source":"Bloodwhite's Heart","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628721,"modifiedTime":1781557628721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"P2UVH5puSyrie5rW","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Bianca Karenmann","source":"Bloodwhite's Heart","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I’m a sweet young girl and I just want to live in \npeace. The power of the curse makes me strong and resilient. \nIt also gives me the power to make living beings explode from \nwithin.\nAgenda: I want what’s best for the whole village of Lohr, even \nif it means sacrificing myself.\nGift – The Curse of Bloodwhite: Thanks to the power of \nthe curse, Bianca is stronger and more resilient than normal. \nFor this reason, at the end of each Scene she recovers 1 \nWound. This effect even allows Bianca to return from \ndeath. Bianca’s power can detonate the body of living \nbeings and, once per Exchange, her action can inflict \n1 automatic Wound to a target. No Defense Check is \nallowed.</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 117.","owner":"Bianca Karenmann","source":"Bloodwhite's Heart","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628721,"modifiedTime":1781557628721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"00o4ut1z01pgdx9e","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-bloodwhites-heart-bianca-karenmann-117","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"bloodwhites-heart","adventureTitle":"Bloodwhite's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":117,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Bloodwhite's Heart","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I’m a sweet young girl and I just want to live in \npeace. The power of the curse makes me strong and resilient. \nIt also gives me the power to make living beings explode from \nwithin.\nAgenda: I want what’s best for the whole village of Lohr, even \nif it means sacrificing myself.\nGift – The Curse of Bloodwhite: Thanks to the power of \nthe curse, Bianca is stronger and more resilient than normal. \nFor this reason, at the end of each Scene she recovers 1 \nWound. This effect even allows Bianca to return from \ndeath. Bianca’s power can detonate the body of living \nbeings and, once per Exchange, her action can inflict \n1 automatic Wound to a target. No Defense Check is \nallowed.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"I want what’s best for the whole village of Lohr, even \nif it means sacrificing myself.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":3800000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628721,"modifiedTime":1781557628721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"VzJj6uGlV9WJt1Nd","name":"Eduardo and Felipe","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"g7kDmSX2ZYYQfBaX","name":"Eduardo and Felipe - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Eduardo and Felipe","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are two guards who are content to leave \nthinking to other people. We do as we’re told while doing as \nlittle as possible. \nThe Di Bello Family \nHouse\nDescriptor: A large, abandoned villa in the bourgeois \ndistricts of Vigo.</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 156.","positive":"We are two guards who are content to leave \nthinking to other people. We do as we’re told while doing as \nlittle as possible. \nThe Di Bello Family \nHouse\nDescriptor: A large, abandoned villa in the bourgeois \ndistricts of Vigo.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Eduardo and Felipe","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637071,"modifiedTime":1781557637071,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Pho3DT6zVuNtQVj3","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Eduardo and Felipe","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are two guards who are content to leave \nthinking to other people. We do as we’re told while doing as \nlittle as possible. \nThe Di Bello Family \nHouse\nDescriptor: A large, abandoned villa in the bourgeois \ndistricts of Vigo.\nInformation: Francisca and Marta live in the house \ntheir mother abandoned. The two sisters traveled around \nthe world for a long time, but it was in mystical Prague \nthey underwent the strange rite that sewed their bodies \ntogether. Now, the two women act as one creature, each \nwearing on her foot one of the glass slippers that the Kind \nMother gave them. Francisca and Marta will be hostile to \nthe Hunters until they discover their identity. At that point,</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 156.","owner":"Eduardo and Felipe","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637071,"modifiedTime":1781557637071,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"01x05lkv00q27p8a","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-in-your-eyes-with-your-feet-eduardo-and-felipe-156","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"in-your-eyes-with-your-feet","adventureTitle":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":156,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are two guards who are content to leave \nthinking to other people. We do as we’re told while doing as \nlittle as possible. \nThe Di Bello Family \nHouse\nDescriptor: A large, abandoned villa in the bourgeois \ndistricts of Vigo.\nInformation: Francisca and Marta live in the house \ntheir mother abandoned. The two sisters traveled around \nthe world for a long time, but it was in mystical Prague \nthey underwent the strange rite that sewed their bodies \ntogether. Now, the two women act as one creature, each \nwearing on her foot one of the glass slippers that the Kind \nMother gave them. Francisca and Marta will be hostile to \nthe Hunters until they discover their identity. At that point,</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":3900000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637071,"modifiedTime":1781557637071,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"WERs78LDIHfbhvvp","name":"Svenn the Skilled Hunter","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Silaool8thDbBCPd","name":"Svenn the Skilled Hunter - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Svenn the Skilled Hunter","source":"Bloodwhite's Heart","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled huntsman and I boast of all the \nprey I have bagged in my long career. I’m a man of the world \nand I’m used to handling every situation without too many \nscruples.</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 113.","positive":"I am a skilled huntsman and I boast of all the \nprey I have bagged in my long career. I’m a man of the world \nand I’m used to handling every situation without too many \nscruples.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Svenn the Skilled Hunter","source":"Bloodwhite's Heart","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628565,"modifiedTime":1781557628565,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"CfmyexPWOB6buiQA","name":"Gift - The Solver","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Svenn the Skilled Hunter","source":"Bloodwhite's Heart","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Svenn takes great care of solving and \nfixing all the problems of those who offer him a job. Against \nany attempt at mind control, gathering information, or \ntrying to intimidate him, Svenn’s OL is Hard 7. \nBruna’s House</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 113.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Svenn the Skilled Hunter","source":"Bloodwhite's Heart","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628565,"modifiedTime":1781557628565,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"0jAV0kjUIvUtX7MR","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Svenn the Skilled Hunter","source":"Bloodwhite's Heart","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled huntsman and I boast of all the \nprey I have bagged in my long career. I’m a man of the world \nand I’m used to handling every situation without too many \nscruples.\nAgenda: To make Bruna take the blame to divert attention \nfrom Bianca / Pretend to help the Hunters to make sure they \nclose the case as quickly as possible.\nGift – The Solver: Svenn takes great care of solving and \nfixing all the problems of those who offer him a job. Against \nany attempt at mind control, gathering information, or \ntrying to intimidate him, Svenn’s OL is Hard 7. \nBruna’s House\nDescriptor: A small old house with a \ngarden full of medicinal plants.\nInformation: Bruna lives alone since \nher husband’s death. Anyone who \nknows herbs will understand that \nthe woman has good botanical \nknowledge. Under the bed, \nSvenn hid a bag with a book of \nblasphemous rituals and a lock \nof blond hair that belonged to \nOttone.\nBruna the Poor Witch</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 113.","owner":"Svenn the Skilled Hunter","source":"Bloodwhite's Heart","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628565,"modifiedTime":1781557628565,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"00o4ut1z01pgdx9e","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-bloodwhites-heart-svenn-the-skilled-hunter-113","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"bloodwhites-heart","adventureTitle":"Bloodwhite's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":113,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Bloodwhite's Heart","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled huntsman and I boast of all the \nprey I have bagged in my long career. I’m a man of the world \nand I’m used to handling every situation without too many \nscruples.\nAgenda: To make Bruna take the blame to divert attention \nfrom Bianca / Pretend to help the Hunters to make sure they \nclose the case as quickly as possible.\nGift – The Solver: Svenn takes great care of solving and \nfixing all the problems of those who offer him a job. Against \nany attempt at mind control, gathering information, or \ntrying to intimidate him, Svenn’s OL is Hard 7. \nBruna’s House\nDescriptor: A small old house with a \ngarden full of medicinal plants.\nInformation: Bruna lives alone since \nher husband’s death. Anyone who \nknows herbs will understand that \nthe woman has good botanical \nknowledge. Under the bed, \nSvenn hid a bag with a book of \nblasphemous rituals and a lock \nof blond hair that belonged to \nOttone.\nBruna the Poor Witch</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To make Bruna take the blame to divert attention \nfrom Bianca / Pretend to help the Hunters to make sure they \nclose the case as quickly as possible.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":4000000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628565,"modifiedTime":1781557628565,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"XNJjucfR3Pvv7jAW","name":"Alexandra the Mother","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"JRTjGNGreb3z8UqR","name":"Alexandra the Mother - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alexandra the Mother","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a monster, deformed in body and mind. \nThe curse that keeps me alive means that I cannot forget \nwhat I have done. Now, with my misshapen mouth, I can \nonly grunt and whine, preventing me from imploring the \nforgiveness of my daughter.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 142.","positive":"I am a monster, deformed in body and mind. \nThe curse that keeps me alive means that I cannot forget \nwhat I have done. Now, with my misshapen mouth, I can \nonly grunt and whine, preventing me from imploring the \nforgiveness of my daughter.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Alexandra the Mother","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636337,"modifiedTime":1781557636337,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"X6BnZpqksgmuVFZL","name":"Gift - Deformed Orc","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alexandra the Mother","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Alexandra is a huge monster with \nherculean strength. She can act twice during an Exchange, \nbut not consecutively. The curse makes Alexandra resistant \nto magic. Any action using magic that involves her receives \n1 Penalty.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 142.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Alexandra the Mother","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636337,"modifiedTime":1781557636337,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"S4Sf0i6CdeX0VoPo","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alexandra the Mother","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (5 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a monster, deformed in body and mind. \nThe curse that keeps me alive means that I cannot forget \nwhat I have done. Now, with my misshapen mouth, I can \nonly grunt and whine, preventing me from imploring the \nforgiveness of my daughter.\nAgenda: After more than fifty years of a cursed existence, \nI have come to understand the damage my sins have done. \nUnable to beg for her forgiveness, I show my daughter how \nmuch I regret the past by doing anything she asks of me.\nGift – Deformed Orc: Alexandra is a huge monster with \nherculean strength. She can act twice during an Exchange, \nbut not consecutively. The curse makes Alexandra resistant \nto magic. Any action using magic that involves her receives \n1 Penalty.\nInformation: Upon her death, Alexandra’s body \nwill reverse to that of a gorgeous middle-aged woman. \nAlexandra is the only one, besides Accursio, who has a key \nto the Dungeons.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 142.","owner":"Alexandra the Mother","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636338,"modifiedTime":1781557636338,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"019bylki016ws0df","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-stegeborgs-quiet-alexandra-the-mother-142","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"stegeborgs-quiet","adventureTitle":"Stegeborg's Quiet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":142,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Stegeborg's Quiet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (5 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a monster, deformed in body and mind. \nThe curse that keeps me alive means that I cannot forget \nwhat I have done. Now, with my misshapen mouth, I can \nonly grunt and whine, preventing me from imploring the \nforgiveness of my daughter.\nAgenda: After more than fifty years of a cursed existence, \nI have come to understand the damage my sins have done. \nUnable to beg for her forgiveness, I show my daughter how \nmuch I regret the past by doing anything she asks of me.\nGift – Deformed Orc: Alexandra is a huge monster with \nherculean strength. She can act twice during an Exchange, \nbut not consecutively. The curse makes Alexandra resistant \nto magic. Any action using magic that involves her receives \n1 Penalty.\nInformation: Upon her death, Alexandra’s body \nwill reverse to that of a gorgeous middle-aged woman. \nAlexandra is the only one, besides Accursio, who has a key \nto the Dungeons.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":5},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"After more than fifty years of a cursed existence, \nI have come to understand the damage my sins have done. \nUnable to beg for her forgiveness, I show my daughter how \nmuch I regret the past by doing anything she asks of me.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":4100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636338,"modifiedTime":1781557636338,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"XPKGOCVwuWfgjRqr","name":"Berto the Bear","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"iInoOXu3yScnWPUB","name":"Berto the Bear - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Berto the Bear","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a strong and massive trained \nbear.</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 158.","positive":"I am a strong and massive trained \nbear.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Berto the Bear","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637149,"modifiedTime":1781557637149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"smeRW1vCHocIMIka","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Berto the Bear","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a strong and massive trained \nbear.</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 158.","owner":"Berto the Bear","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637149,"modifiedTime":1781557637149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"01x05lkv00q27p8a","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-in-your-eyes-with-your-feet-berto-the-bear-158","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"in-your-eyes-with-your-feet","adventureTitle":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":158,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a strong and massive trained \nbear.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":4200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637149,"modifiedTime":1781557637149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"XlLWIGkRCJ4NcRJ0","name":"Pietrik","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"jY0Hestx4CSH76E1","name":"Pietrik - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Pietrik","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young rebel and I fight the creeping industrialization of London with \nall my strength.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 87.","positive":"I am a young rebel and I fight the creeping industrialization of London with \nall my strength.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Pietrik","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625744,"modifiedTime":1781557625744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"XuLguQgtNmtIjNCP","name":"Gift - The Needle of Living Shadows","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Pietrik","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Thanks to the power of the magic needle \nthe Cauldron Fae gave him, once per Scene Pietrik can separate the shadow from \nhis body and make it act like an NPC with its own profile. The shadow has 1 \nWound and can slip through the smallest crack.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 87.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Pietrik","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625744,"modifiedTime":1781557625744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"zgyMKjdlKgZkYyHg","name":"Gift - Personal Seal","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Pietrik","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Pietrik has the Seal of Disbelief tattooed on the palm \nof his hand, so once per Scene, he can activate the Gift The Magic of Disbelief \n(page 84). As with the Gang Seal Gift (page 87), Pietrik can activate any \nSeal present in London. \nThe Skullem Factory</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 87.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Pietrik","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625744,"modifiedTime":1781557625744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"yLoQGQAiQbFfzXqg","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Pietrik","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young rebel and I fight the creeping industrialization of London with \nall my strength.\nAgenda: Destroy all the factories to avenge my sister’s death / Convince Gwendolyn to \njoin my gang because I have fallen in love with her. \nGift – The Needle of Living Shadows: Thanks to the power of the magic needle \nthe Cauldron Fae gave him, once per Scene Pietrik can separate the shadow from \nhis body and make it act like an NPC with its own profile. The shadow has 1 \nWound and can slip through the smallest crack. \nGift – Personal Seal: Pietrik has the Seal of Disbelief tattooed on the palm \nof his hand, so once per Scene, he can activate the Gift The Magic of Disbelief \n(page 84). As with the Gang Seal Gift (page 87), Pietrik can activate any \nSeal present in London. \nThe Skullem Factory\nDescriptor: A large shipyard in which metal components for ships are \nbeing assembled.\nInformation: Inside the factory, there are two large industrial \novens for metal welding. The goal of the Lost Boys is to blow \nthem up by throwing the magic berries that Pietrik has given \nout into them. The raid will take place at night and involves 10 \nLost Boys, in addition to Pietrik. \nSeals: The only Seal in the area of the Skullem Factory is \nlocated in the alley at the back of the building.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 87.","owner":"Pietrik","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625744,"modifiedTime":1781557625744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"014did82003r90kn","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-dont-believe-pietrik-87","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","adventureTitle":"I Don't Believe","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":87,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Don't Believe","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young rebel and I fight the creeping industrialization of London with \nall my strength.\nAgenda: Destroy all the factories to avenge my sister’s death / Convince Gwendolyn to \njoin my gang because I have fallen in love with her. \nGift – The Needle of Living Shadows: Thanks to the power of the magic needle \nthe Cauldron Fae gave him, once per Scene Pietrik can separate the shadow from \nhis body and make it act like an NPC with its own profile. The shadow has 1 \nWound and can slip through the smallest crack. \nGift – Personal Seal: Pietrik has the Seal of Disbelief tattooed on the palm \nof his hand, so once per Scene, he can activate the Gift The Magic of Disbelief \n(page 84). As with the Gang Seal Gift (page 87), Pietrik can activate any \nSeal present in London. \nThe Skullem Factory\nDescriptor: A large shipyard in which metal components for ships are \nbeing assembled.\nInformation: Inside the factory, there are two large industrial \novens for metal welding. The goal of the Lost Boys is to blow \nthem up by throwing the magic berries that Pietrik has given \nout into them. The raid will take place at night and involves 10 \nLost Boys, in addition to Pietrik. \nSeals: The only Seal in the area of the Skullem Factory is \nlocated in the alley at the back of the building.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Destroy all the factories to avenge my sister’s death / Convince Gwendolyn to \njoin my gang because I have fallen in love with her.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":4300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625744,"modifiedTime":1781557625744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"XpSypIhKHdJvmhrg","name":"Mtyrya the Fairy also called the Cauldron Fae","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"vzANKQeXKtmk6IQZ","name":"Mtyrya the Fairy also called the Cauldron Fae - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Mtyrya the Fairy also called the Cauldron Fae","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an ancient fairy bound to nature. I hate humans and modernity. Thanks \nto my power, anything others believe to be impossible, I can make possible.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 85.","positive":"I am an ancient fairy bound to nature. I hate humans and modernity. Thanks \nto my power, anything others believe to be impossible, I can make possible.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Mtyrya the Fairy also called the Cauldron Fae","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625700,"modifiedTime":1781557625700,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"h80U6Xnf4KmuzdGW","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Mtyrya the Fairy also called the Cauldron Fae","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an ancient fairy bound to nature. I hate humans and modernity. Thanks \nto my power, anything others believe to be impossible, I can make possible.\nAgenda: Prevent humans from covering my beloved land with dirty, stinking factories / Save \nPietrik from the punishment I plan to inflict upon London.\nGift – The Magic of Disbelief: As an action, the Cauldron Fae can formulate a magic \nsentence including the fragment I don’t believe and make its effect concrete. For example, \n“I don’t believe in gravity” would allow her to fly, while “I don’t believe the Hunters of the \nOrder exist” would allow her to hurt the Hunters in an attempt to make them disappear. \nIf the statement does not have offensive effects, the duration of the power is generally for \nthe entire Scene. If, on the other hand, the effect is likely to harm a target, it will inflict \n1 Wound without the possibility of attempting a Defense Check. Those who use magic can \ntry to counteract the Magic of Disbelief, and preventing Mtyrya from speaking words would \nautomatically cancel the Gift’s effect.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 85.","owner":"Mtyrya the Fairy also called the Cauldron Fae","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625700,"modifiedTime":1781557625700,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"014did82003r90kn","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-dont-believe-mtyrya-the-fairy-also-called-the-cauldron-fae-85","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","adventureTitle":"I Don't Believe","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":85,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Don't Believe","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an ancient fairy bound to nature. I hate humans and modernity. Thanks \nto my power, anything others believe to be impossible, I can make possible.\nAgenda: Prevent humans from covering my beloved land with dirty, stinking factories / Save \nPietrik from the punishment I plan to inflict upon London.\nGift – The Magic of Disbelief: As an action, the Cauldron Fae can formulate a magic \nsentence including the fragment I don’t believe and make its effect concrete. For example, \n“I don’t believe in gravity” would allow her to fly, while “I don’t believe the Hunters of the \nOrder exist” would allow her to hurt the Hunters in an attempt to make them disappear. \nIf the statement does not have offensive effects, the duration of the power is generally for \nthe entire Scene. If, on the other hand, the effect is likely to harm a target, it will inflict \n1 Wound without the possibility of attempting a Defense Check. Those who use magic can \ntry to counteract the Magic of Disbelief, and preventing Mtyrya from speaking words would \nautomatically cancel the Gift’s effect.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Prevent humans from covering my beloved land with dirty, stinking factories / Save \nPietrik from the punishment I plan to inflict upon London.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":4400000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625700,"modifiedTime":1781557625700,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"YGXVCaLUGypKyAbF","name":"Father Cristoforo","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"qblMo68mazYndcf9","name":"Father Cristoforo - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Father Cristoforo","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a humble provincial priest and I have \nbeen responsible for the religious education of the Gonsalvas \nfor years.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 126.","positive":"I am a humble provincial priest and I have \nbeen responsible for the religious education of the Gonsalvas \nfor years.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Father Cristoforo","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629772,"modifiedTime":1781557629772,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"fzJSK0zg8qrD0xbN","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Father Cristoforo","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a humble provincial priest and I have \nbeen responsible for the religious education of the Gonsalvas \nfor years. \nAgenda: I have reason to believe that the House of Roses is \na place of blasphemy and damnation, so I want the Church \nto investigate.\nInformation from the conversation with \nCristoforo: The humble priest will welcome the Hunters \nin the small church of San Carlo. The man will show \nreverence to the work of the Order and will seem aware of \nwho the Hunters really are.\n ◆ Cristoforo will say that the island once was a \nmonastery where the residents dedicated themselves to \nblasphemous rites. The Church intervened by putting \nthem all at the stake.\n ◆ Martana Island is a name on the lips of many young \npeople, who tell of a place of feasts and pleasures far \nfrom the severe but holy eye of God. Many young women \ngo out of their way to get to sail to the island. \n ◆ Cristoforo taught the ways of God to the unfortunate \nDionysus, being troubled by the savagery that the young \nman struggled to control. \n ◆ At the end of the interview, it will be clear to the Hunters \nthat Cristoforo does not really know what is happening on \nthe island, but he is firmly convinced that it is nothing good.\n ◆ Trying not to be overheard by prying ears, Cristoforo will \ntell the Hunters that a couple of faithful friends have a small \nboat and can take the Hunters to the island at night, landing \non a little-used beach. \nMartana Island\nDescriptor: A small island in the center of Lake Bolsena. Covered \nmostly by dense vegetation, the island includes a sanctuary, a \nsmall pier, and a mansion recently built by the Gonsalvas.\nThere are five locations available on the island:\n ◆ The Pier: Where all ships arriving from Capodimonte dock. \nThe pier is under the control of Bella and her worshippers. \nIf the Hunters accept Pietro Gonsalva’s transportation offer, \nthey will arrive there in the late afternoon.\n ◆ The White Beach: A small beach of rocks and earth to the \neast of the island. It is located on the opposite side of the \nisland from the few inhabited places. If the Hunters accept \nFather Cristoforo’s offer of transportation, they will reach \nthe beach at night.\n ◆ The Sanctuary: All the young people who have become \nprisoners of the House of Roses live here.\n ◆ The Mansion: The House of Roses is a sumptuous villa that \nDionysus had built for Bella.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 126.","owner":"Father Cristoforo","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629772,"modifiedTime":1781557629772,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"00o6rita00gfb6tn","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-father-cristoforo-126","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":126,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a humble provincial priest and I have \nbeen responsible for the religious education of the Gonsalvas \nfor years. \nAgenda: I have reason to believe that the House of Roses is \na place of blasphemy and damnation, so I want the Church \nto investigate.\nInformation from the conversation with \nCristoforo: The humble priest will welcome the Hunters \nin the small church of San Carlo. The man will show \nreverence to the work of the Order and will seem aware of \nwho the Hunters really are.\n ◆ Cristoforo will say that the island once was a \nmonastery where the residents dedicated themselves to \nblasphemous rites. The Church intervened by putting \nthem all at the stake.\n ◆ Martana Island is a name on the lips of many young \npeople, who tell of a place of feasts and pleasures far \nfrom the severe but holy eye of God. Many young women \ngo out of their way to get to sail to the island. \n ◆ Cristoforo taught the ways of God to the unfortunate \nDionysus, being troubled by the savagery that the young \nman struggled to control. \n ◆ At the end of the interview, it will be clear to the Hunters \nthat Cristoforo does not really know what is happening on \nthe island, but he is firmly convinced that it is nothing good.\n ◆ Trying not to be overheard by prying ears, Cristoforo will \ntell the Hunters that a couple of faithful friends have a small \nboat and can take the Hunters to the island at night, landing \non a little-used beach. \nMartana Island\nDescriptor: A small island in the center of Lake Bolsena. Covered \nmostly by dense vegetation, the island includes a sanctuary, a \nsmall pier, and a mansion recently built by the Gonsalvas.\nThere are five locations available on the island:\n ◆ The Pier: Where all ships arriving from Capodimonte dock. \nThe pier is under the control of Bella and her worshippers. \nIf the Hunters accept Pietro Gonsalva’s transportation offer, \nthey will arrive there in the late afternoon.\n ◆ The White Beach: A small beach of rocks and earth to the \neast of the island. It is located on the opposite side of the \nisland from the few inhabited places. If the Hunters accept \nFather Cristoforo’s offer of transportation, they will reach \nthe beach at night.\n ◆ The Sanctuary: All the young people who have become \nprisoners of the House of Roses live here.\n ◆ The Mansion: The House of Roses is a sumptuous villa that \nDionysus had built for Bella.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"I have reason to believe that the House of Roses is \na place of blasphemy and damnation, so I want the Church \nto investigate.\nInformation from the conversation with \nCristoforo: The humble priest will welcome the Hunters \nin the small church of San Carlo. The man will show \nreverence to the work of the Order and will seem aware of \nwho the Hunters really are.\n ◆ Cristoforo will say that the island once was a \nmonastery where the residents dedicated themselves to \nblasphemous rites. The Church intervened by putting \nthem all at the stake.\n ◆ Martana Island is a name on the lips of many young \npeople, who tell of a place of feasts and pleasures far \nfrom the severe but holy eye of God. Many young women \ngo out of their way to get to sail to the island. \n ◆ Cristoforo taught the ways of God to the unfortunate \nDionysus, being troubled by the savagery that the young \nman struggled to control. \n ◆ At the end of the interview, it will be clear to the Hunters \nthat Cristoforo does not really know what is happening on \nthe island, but he is firmly convinced that it is nothing good.\n ◆ Trying not to be overheard by prying ears, Cristoforo will \ntell the Hunters that a couple of faithful friends have a small \nboat and can take the Hunters to the island at night, landing \non a little-used beach. \nMartana Island\nDescriptor: A small island in the center of Lake Bolsena. Covered \nmostly by dense vegetation, the island includes a sanctuary, a \nsmall pier, and a mansion recently built by the Gonsalvas.\nThere are five locations available on the island:\n ◆ The Pier: Where all ships arriving from Capodimonte dock. \nThe pier is under the control of Bella and her worshippers. \nIf the Hunters accept Pietro Gonsalva’s transportation offer, \nthey will arrive there in the late afternoon.\n ◆ The White Beach: A small beach of rocks and earth to the \neast of the island. It is located on the opposite side of the \nisland from the few inhabited places. If the Hunters accept \nFather Cristoforo’s offer of transportation, they will reach \nthe beach at night.\n ◆ The Sanctuary: All the young people who have become \nprisoners of the House of Roses live here.\n ◆ The Mansion: The House of Roses is a sumptuous villa that \nDionysus had built for Bella.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":4500000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629772,"modifiedTime":1781557629772,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"YwnmImWpaqtQKbmb","name":"Bella’s Handmaids","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"eZO5HGpVvrpPB1pp","name":"Bella’s Handmaids - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Bella’s Handmaids","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are young girls loyal to our lady. We are \nready to have a good time – anytime.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128.","positive":"We are young girls loyal to our lady. We are \nready to have a good time – anytime.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Bella’s Handmaids","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"CrITrc1MmQfR5YSv","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Bella’s Handmaids","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are young girls loyal to our lady. We are \nready to have a good time – anytime.\nAgenda: We have tasted happiness in the House of Roses \nand we will not allow anyone to take us back to our former, \nmiserable lives.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128.","owner":"Bella’s Handmaids","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"00o6rita00gfb6tn","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-bella-s-handmaids-128","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":128,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are young girls loyal to our lady. We are \nready to have a good time – anytime.\nAgenda: We have tasted happiness in the House of Roses \nand we will not allow anyone to take us back to our former, \nmiserable lives.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"We have tasted happiness in the House of Roses \nand we will not allow anyone to take us back to our former, \nmiserable lives.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":4600000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"a4tN8nbbmkfHjcXj","name":"Princesca of Vigo","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"sxgGlpRsthsr7y7Z","name":"Princesca of Vigo - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Princesca of Vigo","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am Cinder and, thanks to \nmagic, I pretend to be the attractive and kind \nPrincesca. Thanks to the power of the Kind \nMother, I control the entire city. I am cold and \ndetermined and I won’t let anyone stand in \nmy way.</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 154.","positive":"I am Cinder and, thanks to \nmagic, I pretend to be the attractive and kind \nPrincesca. Thanks to the power of the Kind \nMother, I control the entire city. I am cold and \ndetermined and I won’t let anyone stand in \nmy way.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Princesca of Vigo","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636919,"modifiedTime":1781557636919,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Pi1xkCoEcYzZypUq","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Princesca of Vigo","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC \n(3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am Cinder and, thanks to \nmagic, I pretend to be the attractive and kind \nPrincesca. Thanks to the power of the Kind \nMother, I control the entire city. I am cold and \ndetermined and I won’t let anyone stand in \nmy way. \nAgenda: Gain wealth and power by \nmanipulating my stupid husband / Solving \nthe mystery of the new killer who behaves \nexactly as I did ten years ago. \nGift – Kind Magic: Cinder is able \nto use the magic that the Kind Mother taught her. As an action, Cinder \ncan cast one of the following spells. \n1. Animal Servants: A group of \nanimals (up to 6 subjects) blindly \nobeys the will of Cinder, even per -\nforming suicidal actions. Cinder \nhas used this power many times \non a pair of doves until they \nhave been completely enslaved \n(see The Doves on page 154); \n2. Transmutation: An ob -\nject or a portion of the environment mutates to be transformed into something else. \nThe mutation lasts through-</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 154.","owner":"Princesca of Vigo","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636919,"modifiedTime":1781557636919,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"01x05lkv00q27p8a","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-in-your-eyes-with-your-feet-princesca-of-vigo-154","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"in-your-eyes-with-your-feet","adventureTitle":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":154,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC \n(3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am Cinder and, thanks to \nmagic, I pretend to be the attractive and kind \nPrincesca. Thanks to the power of the Kind \nMother, I control the entire city. I am cold and \ndetermined and I won’t let anyone stand in \nmy way. \nAgenda: Gain wealth and power by \nmanipulating my stupid husband / Solving \nthe mystery of the new killer who behaves \nexactly as I did ten years ago. \nGift – Kind Magic: Cinder is able \nto use the magic that the Kind Mother taught her. As an action, Cinder \ncan cast one of the following spells. \n1. Animal Servants: A group of \nanimals (up to 6 subjects) blindly \nobeys the will of Cinder, even per -\nforming suicidal actions. Cinder \nhas used this power many times \non a pair of doves until they \nhave been completely enslaved \n(see The Doves on page 154); \n2. Transmutation: An ob -\nject or a portion of the environment mutates to be transformed into something else. \nThe mutation lasts through-</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Gain wealth and power by \nmanipulating my stupid husband / Solving \nthe mystery of the new killer who behaves \nexactly as I did ten years ago.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":4700000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636919,"modifiedTime":1781557636919,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"cExnTGYOM4HyjllW","name":"Konstantin Svoboda the Alchemist","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"CPUpieqhBt6JK0cH","name":"Konstantin Svoboda the Alchemist - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Konstantin Svoboda the Alchemist","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am one of the most prominent alchemists in \nPrague. My brilliant experiments could easily backfire on me.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 167.","positive":"I am one of the most prominent alchemists in \nPrague. My brilliant experiments could easily backfire on me.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Konstantin Svoboda the Alchemist","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637513,"modifiedTime":1781557637513,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"QMrpL9mGKDn5Ytwq","name":"Gift - The Secrets of Metal","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Konstantin Svoboda the Alchemist","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Konstantin knows arcane \nwords that allow him to control metal. Any action against \nhim involving a metal weapon or bludgeoning tool receives \n1 Penalty. Starting from moderate amounts of raw materials, \nKonstantin can also forge various metal objects with \nunusual properties. The Storyteller must create a Descriptor \nthat outlines this property (for example: The alloy of this \ndagger violently repels other metals).</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 167.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Konstantin Svoboda the Alchemist","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637513,"modifiedTime":1781557637513,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"r2pZOPZTbuMXMIyu","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Konstantin Svoboda the Alchemist","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am one of the most prominent alchemists in \nPrague. My brilliant experiments could easily backfire on me. \nAgenda: Create a Golem thanks to my alchemical studies \nand prove that no noble title or institutional position can \npossibly compare to my alchemical knowledge. \nGift – The Secrets of Metal: Konstantin knows arcane \nwords that allow him to control metal. Any action against \nhim involving a metal weapon or bludgeoning tool receives \n1 Penalty. Starting from moderate amounts of raw materials, \nKonstantin can also forge various metal objects with \nunusual properties. The Storyteller must create a Descriptor \nthat outlines this property (for example: The alloy of this \ndagger violently repels other metals). \nGift – The Secrets of Flesh: Once per Scene, when a \nmetallic body is in the vicinity of warm flesh, whether it’s still \nattached to the body or only recently removed, Konstantin \ncan utter some arcane words, forcing the two elements to \nmerge. The procedure causes 1 immediate Wound, and 1 \nadditional Wound during the painful medical procedure \nnecessary to untangle flesh and metal.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 167.","owner":"Konstantin Svoboda the Alchemist","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637513,"modifiedTime":1781557637513,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"01gakz6800ms75vx","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-will-stay-with-you-always-konstantin-svoboda-the-alchemist-167","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-will-stay-with-you-always","adventureTitle":"I Will Stay with You Always","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":167,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Will Stay with You Always","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am one of the most prominent alchemists in \nPrague. My brilliant experiments could easily backfire on me. \nAgenda: Create a Golem thanks to my alchemical studies \nand prove that no noble title or institutional position can \npossibly compare to my alchemical knowledge. \nGift – The Secrets of Metal: Konstantin knows arcane \nwords that allow him to control metal. Any action against \nhim involving a metal weapon or bludgeoning tool receives \n1 Penalty. Starting from moderate amounts of raw materials, \nKonstantin can also forge various metal objects with \nunusual properties. The Storyteller must create a Descriptor \nthat outlines this property (for example: The alloy of this \ndagger violently repels other metals). \nGift – The Secrets of Flesh: Once per Scene, when a \nmetallic body is in the vicinity of warm flesh, whether it’s still \nattached to the body or only recently removed, Konstantin \ncan utter some arcane words, forcing the two elements to \nmerge. The procedure causes 1 immediate Wound, and 1 \nadditional Wound during the painful medical procedure \nnecessary to untangle flesh and metal.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Create a Golem thanks to my alchemical studies \nand prove that no noble title or institutional position can \npossibly compare to my alchemical knowledge.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":4800000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637513,"modifiedTime":1781557637513,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"dJyeQkZti2sYRcVz","name":"Tasha the Tiger","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Mo7GBOjHIeAFJnD7","name":"Tasha the Tiger - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Tasha the Tiger","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a fast and \naggressive, though trained, tiger.\nBerto the Bear</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 158.","positive":"I am a fast and \naggressive, though trained, tiger.\nBerto the Bear","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Tasha the Tiger","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637149,"modifiedTime":1781557637149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"8XMWL1rYW26DOWct","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Tasha the Tiger","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor \nNPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a fast and \naggressive, though trained, tiger.\nBerto the Bear</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 158.","owner":"Tasha the Tiger","source":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637149,"modifiedTime":1781557637149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"01x05lkv00q27p8a","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-in-your-eyes-with-your-feet-tasha-the-tiger-158","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"in-your-eyes-with-your-feet","adventureTitle":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":158,"role":"Scenario Actor"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Scenario Actor","notes":"<p>– Minor \nNPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a fast and \naggressive, though trained, tiger.\nBerto the Bear</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":4900000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637149,"modifiedTime":1781557637149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"dkxYuUu36dRYwqUF","name":"Director of the Theater","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"KPmiwJFNSdXaLFEW","name":"Director of the Theater - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Director of the Theater","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the young and ambitious assistant of \nGabriel Černý. Our differences were known.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 171.","positive":"I am the young and ambitious assistant of \nGabriel Černý. Our differences were known.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Director of the Theater","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637827,"modifiedTime":1781557637827,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"fFoCmcc81sMthtDo","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Director of the Theater","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the young and ambitious assistant of \nGabriel Černý. Our differences were known. \nAgenda: Make sure I am not blamed for the murder / \nMake sure it doesn’t turn out that I facilitated the murder. \nThe Circus of the Azure Sun\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Just outside the walls of \nPrague, a battered blue and white tent stands in a muddy \nfield. Some smaller tents are surrounded by wooden wagons, \nwhile a secondary tent connected to the larger one acts as \na shelter from the weather for animals. There is a strange \nsilence, as if the field had been abandoned, except for a \nsubdued metallic sound coming from the animal tent.\nDescriptor: A dilapidated tent in the middle of a muddy \nfield. Wooden carriages and abandoned animal cages.\nThe camp is not actually abandoned, and at several hours \nof the day it’s possible to see a young boy hanging around \nthe tents (Černobog). Konstantin spends every free \nmoment in the animal tent, where he is assembling the \nPrince, while the main tent is mostly empty, except for the \npresence of a huge nest made up of brushes and mud built \na few meters from the ground, and accessible only through \nthe stairs or the ropes of the acrobats. \nInformation: Entering the Circus of the Azure Sun \nwithout being seen by Černobog is difficult but, once \ninside, Hunters can access some or all of the following \ninformation:\n ◆ There is a large basin containing human remains, \nstill wearing some uniforms of the Circus of the \nAzure Sun. These are the artists who did not leave the \ncircus after the acquisition of Černobog, now simple \nspare parts for the Prince. It will be possible to find a \nhacksaw nearby. \n ◆ On a desk you can find an invitation to the dance at \nPrague Castle, under the name Konstantin Svoboda. \nOn another sheet there seems to be a rudimentary \nmap of the city, with a path traced (the one Konstantin \nplans to use to get the Prince to the Castle). \n ◆ The nest, suspended in the center of the tent, is made \nup of mud and branches and is extremely similar to \nthat of a swallow. It’s big enough to accommodate a \nhuman being. This is where Alexandr rests when he’s \nnot out murdering someone. \n ◆ Approaching the circus at night, the Hunters will be \nable to see strange lights coming from the animal tent: \nKonstantin is in fact finalizing the preparations before \nactivating the Prince.\nRefer to the Events section of the Scenario to better manage \nthe situation. \n^</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 171.","owner":"Director of the Theater","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637827,"modifiedTime":1781557637827,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"01gakz6800ms75vx","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-will-stay-with-you-always-director-of-the-theater-171","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-will-stay-with-you-always","adventureTitle":"I Will Stay with You Always","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":171,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Will Stay with You Always","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the young and ambitious assistant of \nGabriel Černý. Our differences were known. \nAgenda: Make sure I am not blamed for the murder / \nMake sure it doesn’t turn out that I facilitated the murder. \nThe Circus of the Azure Sun\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Just outside the walls of \nPrague, a battered blue and white tent stands in a muddy \nfield. Some smaller tents are surrounded by wooden wagons, \nwhile a secondary tent connected to the larger one acts as \na shelter from the weather for animals. There is a strange \nsilence, as if the field had been abandoned, except for a \nsubdued metallic sound coming from the animal tent.\nDescriptor: A dilapidated tent in the middle of a muddy \nfield. Wooden carriages and abandoned animal cages.\nThe camp is not actually abandoned, and at several hours \nof the day it’s possible to see a young boy hanging around \nthe tents (Černobog). Konstantin spends every free \nmoment in the animal tent, where he is assembling the \nPrince, while the main tent is mostly empty, except for the \npresence of a huge nest made up of brushes and mud built \na few meters from the ground, and accessible only through \nthe stairs or the ropes of the acrobats. \nInformation: Entering the Circus of the Azure Sun \nwithout being seen by Černobog is difficult but, once \ninside, Hunters can access some or all of the following \ninformation:\n ◆ There is a large basin containing human remains, \nstill wearing some uniforms of the Circus of the \nAzure Sun. These are the artists who did not leave the \ncircus after the acquisition of Černobog, now simple \nspare parts for the Prince. It will be possible to find a \nhacksaw nearby. \n ◆ On a desk you can find an invitation to the dance at \nPrague Castle, under the name Konstantin Svoboda. \nOn another sheet there seems to be a rudimentary \nmap of the city, with a path traced (the one Konstantin \nplans to use to get the Prince to the Castle). \n ◆ The nest, suspended in the center of the tent, is made \nup of mud and branches and is extremely similar to \nthat of a swallow. It’s big enough to accommodate a \nhuman being. This is where Alexandr rests when he’s \nnot out murdering someone. \n ◆ Approaching the circus at night, the Hunters will be \nable to see strange lights coming from the animal tent: \nKonstantin is in fact finalizing the preparations before \nactivating the Prince.\nRefer to the Events section of the Scenario to better manage \nthe situation. \n^</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Make sure I am not blamed for the murder / \nMake sure it doesn’t turn out that I facilitated the murder. \nThe Circus of the Azure Sun\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Just outside the walls of \nPrague, a battered blue and white tent stands in a muddy \nfield. Some smaller tents are surrounded by wooden wagons, \nwhile a secondary tent connected to the larger one acts as \na shelter from the weather for animals. There is a strange \nsilence, as if the field had been abandoned, except for a \nsubdued metallic sound coming from the animal tent.\nDescriptor: A dilapidated tent in the middle of a muddy \nfield. Wooden carriages and abandoned animal cages.\nThe camp is not actually abandoned, and at several hours \nof the day it’s possible to see a young boy hanging around \nthe tents (Černobog). Konstantin spends every free \nmoment in the animal tent, where he is assembling the \nPrince, while the main tent is mostly empty, except for the \npresence of a huge nest made up of brushes and mud built \na few meters from the ground, and accessible only through \nthe stairs or the ropes of the acrobats.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":5000000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637827,"modifiedTime":1781557637827,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"dodxEP8aviLbmldH","name":"The Food of the Gods","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"ElOXsSj7ahBcS3Oz","name":"The Food of the Gods - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Food of the Gods","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>All the food in the Sanctuary is tainted with a \npowerful drug that loosens one’s inhibitions.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128.","positive":"All the food in the Sanctuary is tainted with a \npowerful drug that loosens one’s inhibitions.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Food of the Gods","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"LFDklJZfp4EYWMYZ","name":"Gift - The Drug of the True Self","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Food of the Gods","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Whoever eats food \ntreated with this powerful drug loses all inhibition. Anyone \nwho fails the Defense Check to resist the effect receives 2 \nDrug Tokens. During a Scene, the Storyteller can spend 1 \nDrug Token to activate one of the following effects. 1. The \nTrue Self: Immediately activates the Hunter’s Dark Ego \nwithout them suffering the Wound generated by not using \nthe Activator. 2. Dulled Senses: The Storyteller decides \nwhat type of Outcome the Hunter is aiming for after they \nhave declared an action. \nBella’s Handmaids</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Food of the Gods","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"OQV6s2UCVhZpLWiV","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Food of the Gods","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: All the food in the Sanctuary is tainted with a \npowerful drug that loosens one’s inhibitions.\nGift – The Drug of the True Self: Whoever eats food \ntreated with this powerful drug loses all inhibition. Anyone \nwho fails the Defense Check to resist the effect receives 2 \nDrug Tokens. During a Scene, the Storyteller can spend 1 \nDrug Token to activate one of the following effects. 1. The \nTrue Self: Immediately activates the Hunter’s Dark Ego \nwithout them suffering the Wound generated by not using \nthe Activator. 2. Dulled Senses: The Storyteller decides \nwhat type of Outcome the Hunter is aiming for after they \nhave declared an action. \nBella’s Handmaids</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128.","owner":"The Food of the Gods","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"00o6rita00gfb6tn","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-the-food-of-the-gods-128","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":128,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: All the food in the Sanctuary is tainted with a \npowerful drug that loosens one’s inhibitions.\nGift – The Drug of the True Self: Whoever eats food \ntreated with this powerful drug loses all inhibition. Anyone \nwho fails the Defense Check to resist the effect receives 2 \nDrug Tokens. During a Scene, the Storyteller can spend 1 \nDrug Token to activate one of the following effects. 1. The \nTrue Self: Immediately activates the Hunter’s Dark Ego \nwithout them suffering the Wound generated by not using \nthe Activator. 2. Dulled Senses: The Storyteller decides \nwhat type of Outcome the Hunter is aiming for after they \nhave declared an action. \nBella’s Handmaids</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":5100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"f68iqkEfz2pFZdQj","name":"Basil the Survivor","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"IdorBfLfppY6vCXN","name":"Basil the Survivor - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Basil the Survivor","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a coward only concerned with making \nends meet.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 86.","positive":"I am a coward only concerned with making \nends meet.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Basil the Survivor","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625729,"modifiedTime":1781557625729,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"AgBweE1XwW4xxm6a","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Basil the Survivor","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a coward only concerned with making \nends meet. \nAgenda: To get back on my feet and escape from London, \naway from rebels and magic.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 86.","owner":"Basil the Survivor","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625729,"modifiedTime":1781557625729,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"014did82003r90kn","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-dont-believe-basil-the-survivor-86","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","adventureTitle":"I Don't Believe","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":86,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Don't Believe","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a coward only concerned with making \nends meet. \nAgenda: To get back on my feet and escape from London, \naway from rebels and magic.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"To get back on my feet and escape from London, \naway from rebels and magic.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":5200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625729,"modifiedTime":1781557625729,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"fAeubWQlsAkoppa2","name":"Gwendolyn","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"7ojmkbYhxPLdB5t2","name":"Gwendolyn - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Gwendolyn","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the young heir of \nthe Carnarvon family, but I dream \nof a life of travel and freedom, \nexploring the world. I am good at \ntelling stories, and that is how I \ngot closer to Pietrik.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 88.","positive":"I am the young heir of \nthe Carnarvon family, but I dream \nof a life of travel and freedom, \nexploring the world. I am good at \ntelling stories, and that is how I \ngot closer to Pietrik.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Gwendolyn","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625775,"modifiedTime":1781557625775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"h8ARL1pXNi4FsWmm","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Gwendolyn","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the young heir of \nthe Carnarvon family, but I dream \nof a life of travel and freedom, \nexploring the world. I am good at \ntelling stories, and that is how I \ngot closer to Pietrik.\nAgenda: To convince Pietrik \nto desist from his revenge. \nI understand how much \npain his heart holds and \nI would like to welcome \nhim into my family to \ngive him a different \nfuture.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 88.","owner":"Gwendolyn","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625775,"modifiedTime":1781557625775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"014did82003r90kn","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-dont-believe-gwendolyn-88","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","adventureTitle":"I Don't Believe","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":88,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Don't Believe","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the young heir of \nthe Carnarvon family, but I dream \nof a life of travel and freedom, \nexploring the world. I am good at \ntelling stories, and that is how I \ngot closer to Pietrik.\nAgenda: To convince Pietrik \nto desist from his revenge. \nI understand how much \npain his heart holds and \nI would like to welcome \nhim into my family to \ngive him a different \nfuture.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"To convince Pietrik \nto desist from his revenge. \nI understand how much \npain his heart holds and \nI would like to welcome \nhim into my family to \ngive him a different \nfuture.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":5300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625775,"modifiedTime":1781557625775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"gZhFNSOgQvktKjb8","name":"Beáta Czernin the Noblewoman","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"FHi9LSBsYap1JvTC","name":"Beáta Czernin the Noblewoman - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Beáta Czernin the Noblewoman","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am part of the city’s elite and I take advantage \nof it. Sometimes, my vanity and arrogance unexpectedly \ncause annoyances.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 166.","positive":"I am part of the city’s elite and I take advantage \nof it. Sometimes, my vanity and arrogance unexpectedly \ncause annoyances.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Beáta Czernin the Noblewoman","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637466,"modifiedTime":1781557637466,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"dkPxp1besOCsGRLY","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Beáta Czernin the Noblewoman","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am part of the city’s elite and I take advantage \nof it. Sometimes, my vanity and arrogance unexpectedly \ncause annoyances. \nAgenda: Distancing myself from my late lover Danek in the \neyes of my husband and family / Finding out which monster \nmay have murdered him in this way.\nThe Alchemical \nLaboratory\nRead aloud to the Hunters: You reach the workshop \nfrom a small staircase on one side of Haštalská, the street \nin Prague that runs alongside the Church of St. Castulus. A \nstone corridor leads you to what looks like the entrance to \na cell, protected by a wooden door reinforced by large iron \nbars. Konstantin pulls out a large key that he hangs on his \nneck and makes his way inside the laboratory, where the \nsoft light of lanterns hanging on the wall illuminates a cold \nspace similar to a tomb. Built of red brick and furnished with \nwooden tables and benches, the workshop houses hundreds \nof stills, bottles, and parchments abandoned on dusty shelves. \nDried plants and other esoteric trinkets hang from the ceiling. \nIn the center of the room is a forge, which Konstantin uses \nto process minerals of various kinds, while in the corner an \nelegant wooden desk is covered with paperwork, inks, and \npens for writing. What strikes you most is the almost total \ndevastation of a wing of the laboratory, now a pile of rubble, \nglass, and split wooden boards. On the ground, a dry puddle \nof god-knows-what emits a nauseating stench. Konstantin</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 166.","owner":"Beáta Czernin the Noblewoman","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637466,"modifiedTime":1781557637466,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"01gakz6800ms75vx","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-will-stay-with-you-always-be-ta-czernin-the-noblewoman-166","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-will-stay-with-you-always","adventureTitle":"I Will Stay with You Always","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":166,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Will Stay with You Always","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am part of the city’s elite and I take advantage \nof it. Sometimes, my vanity and arrogance unexpectedly \ncause annoyances. \nAgenda: Distancing myself from my late lover Danek in the \neyes of my husband and family / Finding out which monster \nmay have murdered him in this way.\nThe Alchemical \nLaboratory\nRead aloud to the Hunters: You reach the workshop \nfrom a small staircase on one side of Haštalská, the street \nin Prague that runs alongside the Church of St. Castulus. A \nstone corridor leads you to what looks like the entrance to \na cell, protected by a wooden door reinforced by large iron \nbars. Konstantin pulls out a large key that he hangs on his \nneck and makes his way inside the laboratory, where the \nsoft light of lanterns hanging on the wall illuminates a cold \nspace similar to a tomb. Built of red brick and furnished with \nwooden tables and benches, the workshop houses hundreds \nof stills, bottles, and parchments abandoned on dusty shelves. \nDried plants and other esoteric trinkets hang from the ceiling. \nIn the center of the room is a forge, which Konstantin uses \nto process minerals of various kinds, while in the corner an \nelegant wooden desk is covered with paperwork, inks, and \npens for writing. What strikes you most is the almost total \ndevastation of a wing of the laboratory, now a pile of rubble, \nglass, and split wooden boards. On the ground, a dry puddle \nof god-knows-what emits a nauseating stench. Konstantin</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Distancing myself from my late lover Danek in the \neyes of my husband and family / Finding out which monster \nmay have murdered him in this way.\nThe Alchemical \nLaboratory\nRead aloud to the Hunters: You reach the workshop \nfrom a small staircase on one side of Haštalská, the street \nin Prague that runs alongside the Church of St. Castulus. A \nstone corridor leads you to what looks like the entrance to \na cell, protected by a wooden door reinforced by large iron \nbars. Konstantin pulls out a large key that he hangs on his \nneck and makes his way inside the laboratory, where the \nsoft light of lanterns hanging on the wall illuminates a cold \nspace similar to a tomb. Built of red brick and furnished with \nwooden tables and benches, the workshop houses hundreds \nof stills, bottles, and parchments abandoned on dusty shelves. \nDried plants and other esoteric trinkets hang from the ceiling. \nIn the center of the room is a forge, which Konstantin uses \nto process minerals of various kinds, while in the corner an \nelegant wooden desk is covered with paperwork, inks, and \npens for writing. What strikes you most is the almost total \ndevastation of a wing of the laboratory, now a pile of rubble, \nglass, and split wooden boards. On the ground, a dry puddle \nof god-knows-what emits a nauseating stench. Konstantin","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":5400000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637466,"modifiedTime":1781557637466,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"hpwNpiYcdbzVqyln","name":"Gréte","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"VIla8J2Kh6M6fjaF","name":"Gréte - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Gréte","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the incarnation of \nthe power of the great Maw. My body \nregenerates thanks to the flesh I eat, my strength and my \nspeed are unbelievable.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 96.","positive":"I am the incarnation of \nthe power of the great Maw. My body \nregenerates thanks to the flesh I eat, my strength and my \nspeed are unbelievable.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Gréte","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626262,"modifiedTime":1781557626262,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"OQcPYZe7Ufp4D1aq","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Gréte","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC \n(4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the incarnation of \nthe power of the great Maw. My body \nregenerates thanks to the flesh I eat, my strength and my \nspeed are unbelievable. \nAgenda: Keep capturing new humans to ensure a future \nfor the Maw’s offspring. Unlike my brother Hanse, I still have \na shred of humanity and I wouldn’t want to devour anyone \nindiscriminately / I want to convince my friend Ina to become \na Maw.\nGift – Mutant Maw: As long as they maintain their \noriginal appearance, a mutant Maw appears in every way as \na common child. When they unleash their power, the body \nshifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing a</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 96.","owner":"Gréte","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626262,"modifiedTime":1781557626262,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"00fisila00bqr0g5","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-hunger-island-gr-te-96","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"hunger-island","adventureTitle":"Hunger Island","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":96,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Hunger Island","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC \n(4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the incarnation of \nthe power of the great Maw. My body \nregenerates thanks to the flesh I eat, my strength and my \nspeed are unbelievable. \nAgenda: Keep capturing new humans to ensure a future \nfor the Maw’s offspring. Unlike my brother Hanse, I still have \na shred of humanity and I wouldn’t want to devour anyone \nindiscriminately / I want to convince my friend Ina to become \na Maw.\nGift – Mutant Maw: As long as they maintain their \noriginal appearance, a mutant Maw appears in every way as \na common child. When they unleash their power, the body \nshifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing a</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Keep capturing new humans to ensure a future \nfor the Maw’s offspring. Unlike my brother Hanse, I still have \na shred of humanity and I wouldn’t want to devour anyone \nindiscriminately / I want to convince my friend Ina to become \na Maw.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":5500000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626262,"modifiedTime":1781557626262,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"jtZTDUpXa8swDWBI","name":"Francesca Cantalupo","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"wXKAutPMQt3g6ENk","name":"Francesca Cantalupo - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Francesca Cantalupo","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am Bellina’s sister, the eldest of three.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128.","positive":"I am Bellina’s sister, the eldest of three.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Francesca Cantalupo","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"U5EySmYTUS4HVjtr","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Francesca Cantalupo","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am Bellina’s sister, the eldest of three.\nAgenda: Flee the island to return to my father / Avenge \nLetizia’s death and punish Bellina for always being a selfish, \njealous child.\nThe Sanctuary\nDescriptor: An ancient monastery converted into a small \npleasure town. \nInformation: 20 Handmaids and 10 Servants are \nalways present in the Sanctuary. All the inhabitants of the \nSanctuary live surrounded by food and pleasures of the \nflesh, in a state of constant and perverse ecstasy. Bella adds \ndrugs to both food and drinks so that the inhabitants of the \nSanctuary lose their inhibitions.\nThreat – The Food of the Gods</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128.","owner":"Francesca Cantalupo","source":"The House of Roses","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"00o6rita00gfb6tn","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-francesca-cantalupo-128","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":128,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am Bellina’s sister, the eldest of three.\nAgenda: Flee the island to return to my father / Avenge \nLetizia’s death and punish Bellina for always being a selfish, \njealous child.\nThe Sanctuary\nDescriptor: An ancient monastery converted into a small \npleasure town. \nInformation: 20 Handmaids and 10 Servants are \nalways present in the Sanctuary. All the inhabitants of the \nSanctuary live surrounded by food and pleasures of the \nflesh, in a state of constant and perverse ecstasy. Bella adds \ndrugs to both food and drinks so that the inhabitants of the \nSanctuary lose their inhibitions.\nThreat – The Food of the Gods</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Flee the island to return to my father / Avenge \nLetizia’s death and punish Bellina for always being a selfish, \njealous child.\nThe Sanctuary\nDescriptor: An ancient monastery converted into a small \npleasure town.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":5600000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"jx3IEo5q5hDiyR6v","name":"The Quiet Guards","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Gch41TwU0rKT3sjz","name":"The Quiet Guards - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Quiet Guards","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are the poor inhabitants of the village, fused \nwith some of the castle’s furnishings. Our transformations \nhave driven us to madness and we blindly obey the will of \nTalia.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 138.","positive":"We are the poor inhabitants of the village, fused \nwith some of the castle’s furnishings. Our transformations \nhave driven us to madness and we blindly obey the will of \nTalia.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Quiet Guards","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636197,"modifiedTime":1781557636197,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"TQ8GE8X6XZ6rmTTO","name":"Gift - Quiet Guards","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Quiet Guards","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>A Quiet Guard no longer possesses \na mind and acts as an object under the control of Talia. That \nis why they cannot be mentally manipulated or frightened \nin any way. Each Quiet Guard is a human body fused with a \npart of the castle. Roll a die or choose a mutation.\n1. Tools: The Guard’s arms are an agglomeration of tools, \nsuch as shears and hammers. When attacking, the Guard is</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 138.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Quiet Guards","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636197,"modifiedTime":1781557636197,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"5L0LXdcl2xkaDdXE","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Quiet Guards","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are the poor inhabitants of the village, fused \nwith some of the castle’s furnishings. Our transformations \nhave driven us to madness and we blindly obey the will of \nTalia.\nGift – Quiet Guards: A Quiet Guard no longer possesses \na mind and acts as an object under the control of Talia. That \nis why they cannot be mentally manipulated or frightened \nin any way. Each Quiet Guard is a human body fused with a \npart of the castle. Roll a die or choose a mutation.\n1. Tools: The Guard’s arms are an agglomeration of tools, \nsuch as shears and hammers. When attacking, the Guard is</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 138.","owner":"The Quiet Guards","source":"Stegeborg's Quiet","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636197,"modifiedTime":1781557636197,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"019bylki016ws0df","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-stegeborgs-quiet-the-quiet-guards-138","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"stegeborgs-quiet","adventureTitle":"Stegeborg's Quiet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":138,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Stegeborg's Quiet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are the poor inhabitants of the village, fused \nwith some of the castle’s furnishings. Our transformations \nhave driven us to madness and we blindly obey the will of \nTalia.\nGift – Quiet Guards: A Quiet Guard no longer possesses \na mind and acts as an object under the control of Talia. That \nis why they cannot be mentally manipulated or frightened \nin any way. Each Quiet Guard is a human body fused with a \npart of the castle. Roll a die or choose a mutation.\n1. Tools: The Guard’s arms are an agglomeration of tools, \nsuch as shears and hammers. When attacking, the Guard is</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":5700000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636197,"modifiedTime":1781557636197,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"kRU4D9NcqLqeHvQw","name":"Berend the Crazed Captain","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"GWRKVEgFAcvei4Lv","name":"Berend the Crazed Captain - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Berend the Crazed Captain","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the captain of the previous expedition \nand the only one left of my crew. I learned to survive by \nmasking my smell with the stench of rotten fish.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 98.","positive":"I am the captain of the previous expedition \nand the only one left of my crew. I learned to survive by \nmasking my smell with the stench of rotten fish.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Berend the Crazed Captain","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626341,"modifiedTime":1781557626341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"eSvDH8Y6SEV8Rpa7","name":"Gift - Stinking Survivor","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Berend the Crazed Captain","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Berend managed to avoid \nbeing devoured by the Maws, but what he saw happen \nto his companions scarred his mind forever. The man \nconstantly covers himself with rotten fish because he has \ndiscovered the stench conceals him from the Maws. \nBerend will never be targeted by a Maw unless he \ntakes direct action against them. As long as he \nis at the port of Vík í Mýrdal, Berend can move \nwith great skill through the alleys and take \nany companions anywhere in the city without \nattracting the attention of the Maws. Each \ntime he uses this ability, he rolls 1 die: on 5 \nor 6, Berend convinces himself that he has \nseen other survivors and makes noise in an \nattempt to get their attention. It will be \nclear to those that accompany him that \nthe whole situation is nothing \nmore than a figment \nof the poor man’s \ndistressed mind.\nVík í Mýrdal’s Lighthouse</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 98.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Berend the Crazed Captain","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626341,"modifiedTime":1781557626341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"88W9OnIhVgHmj4XK","name":"Gift - Safe Haven from the Maws","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Berend the Crazed Captain","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>The stacks of rotten \nfish that Berend and Althea constantly throw at the foot of \nthe lighthouse keep the Maws away. The Maws lose all trace \nof someone who takes refuge in the lighthouse. While near \nthe lighthouse, Maws reduce their Opposition Level by 1.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 98.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Berend the Crazed Captain","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626341,"modifiedTime":1781557626341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"e4NNxQ9WEguSBwfj","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Berend the Crazed Captain","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the captain of the previous expedition \nand the only one left of my crew. I learned to survive by \nmasking my smell with the stench of rotten fish.\nAgenda: Wait for someone to come from the mainland to \nsave me.\nGift – Stinking Survivor: Berend managed to avoid \nbeing devoured by the Maws, but what he saw happen \nto his companions scarred his mind forever. The man \nconstantly covers himself with rotten fish because he has \ndiscovered the stench conceals him from the Maws. \nBerend will never be targeted by a Maw unless he \ntakes direct action against them. As long as he \nis at the port of Vík í Mýrdal, Berend can move \nwith great skill through the alleys and take \nany companions anywhere in the city without \nattracting the attention of the Maws. Each \ntime he uses this ability, he rolls 1 die: on 5 \nor 6, Berend convinces himself that he has \nseen other survivors and makes noise in an \nattempt to get their attention. It will be \nclear to those that accompany him that \nthe whole situation is nothing \nmore than a figment \nof the poor man’s \ndistressed mind.\nVík í Mýrdal’s Lighthouse\nDescriptor: An old lighthouse in the oldest part of the port \nof Vík í Mýrdal. Crates of fish have been broken open and \nspilled around the lighthouse, their contents left to rot in the \nsun. Now, the air reeks in a nauseating way.\nGift – Safe Haven from the Maws: The stacks of rotten \nfish that Berend and Althea constantly throw at the foot of \nthe lighthouse keep the Maws away. The Maws lose all trace \nof someone who takes refuge in the lighthouse. While near \nthe lighthouse, Maws reduce their Opposition Level by 1.\nInformation: Althea will have a great deal of information \nfor the Hunters. She has been trapped for a month now, and \nhas taken the opportunity to study the Maws in depth.\n ◆ The Maws look like children mutated by something. \nThey are strong, fast, and seem to follow the smell of \nhuman flesh.\n ◆ Some desperate people fleeing from the village of Hosn \nhave told them of two “leaders” of the Maws, brother \nand sister, who apparently are smarter and more \npowerful than the others.\n ◆ After overhearing Maws talking to each other, Althea \nrealized that the volcano is a sacred place for those \nstrange beings that humans must not enter.\n ◆ Both the village and the volcano are two days’ walk \nfrom Vík í Mýrdal, but in different directions.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 98.","owner":"Berend the Crazed Captain","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626341,"modifiedTime":1781557626341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"00fisila00bqr0g5","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-hunger-island-berend-the-crazed-captain-98","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"hunger-island","adventureTitle":"Hunger Island","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":98,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Hunger Island","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the captain of the previous expedition \nand the only one left of my crew. I learned to survive by \nmasking my smell with the stench of rotten fish.\nAgenda: Wait for someone to come from the mainland to \nsave me.\nGift – Stinking Survivor: Berend managed to avoid \nbeing devoured by the Maws, but what he saw happen \nto his companions scarred his mind forever. The man \nconstantly covers himself with rotten fish because he has \ndiscovered the stench conceals him from the Maws. \nBerend will never be targeted by a Maw unless he \ntakes direct action against them. As long as he \nis at the port of Vík í Mýrdal, Berend can move \nwith great skill through the alleys and take \nany companions anywhere in the city without \nattracting the attention of the Maws. Each \ntime he uses this ability, he rolls 1 die: on 5 \nor 6, Berend convinces himself that he has \nseen other survivors and makes noise in an \nattempt to get their attention. It will be \nclear to those that accompany him that \nthe whole situation is nothing \nmore than a figment \nof the poor man’s \ndistressed mind.\nVík í Mýrdal’s Lighthouse\nDescriptor: An old lighthouse in the oldest part of the port \nof Vík í Mýrdal. Crates of fish have been broken open and \nspilled around the lighthouse, their contents left to rot in the \nsun. Now, the air reeks in a nauseating way.\nGift – Safe Haven from the Maws: The stacks of rotten \nfish that Berend and Althea constantly throw at the foot of \nthe lighthouse keep the Maws away. The Maws lose all trace \nof someone who takes refuge in the lighthouse. While near \nthe lighthouse, Maws reduce their Opposition Level by 1.\nInformation: Althea will have a great deal of information \nfor the Hunters. She has been trapped for a month now, and \nhas taken the opportunity to study the Maws in depth.\n ◆ The Maws look like children mutated by something. \nThey are strong, fast, and seem to follow the smell of \nhuman flesh.\n ◆ Some desperate people fleeing from the village of Hosn \nhave told them of two “leaders” of the Maws, brother \nand sister, who apparently are smarter and more \npowerful than the others.\n ◆ After overhearing Maws talking to each other, Althea \nrealized that the volcano is a sacred place for those \nstrange beings that humans must not enter.\n ◆ Both the village and the volcano are two days’ walk \nfrom Vík í Mýrdal, but in different directions.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Wait for someone to come from the mainland to \nsave me.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":5800000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626341,"modifiedTime":1781557626341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"mKAuXdCBRpdu6J27","name":"Sailors","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"KT5EPAdOnV8ctDgN","name":"Sailors - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Sailors","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are sailors under Captain Arne’s orders. We \nare skilled sea wolves, more comfortable at sea than on land.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 95.","positive":"We are sailors under Captain Arne’s orders. We \nare skilled sea wolves, more comfortable at sea than on land.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Sailors","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626239,"modifiedTime":1781557626239,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"bWx5wygaQpw9Vhoz","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Sailors","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are sailors under Captain Arne’s orders. We \nare skilled sea wolves, more comfortable at sea than on land.\nAgenda: Execute Arne’s orders and avoid in any way having to \nface the supernatural.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 95.","owner":"Sailors","source":"Hunger Island","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626239,"modifiedTime":1781557626239,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"00fisila00bqr0g5","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-hunger-island-sailors-95","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"hunger-island","adventureTitle":"Hunger Island","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":95,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Hunger Island","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are sailors under Captain Arne’s orders. We \nare skilled sea wolves, more comfortable at sea than on land.\nAgenda: Execute Arne’s orders and avoid in any way having to \nface the supernatural.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Execute Arne’s orders and avoid in any way having to \nface the supernatural.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":5900000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626239,"modifiedTime":1781557626239,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"n3jxoVxBqZM9xIJi","name":"Joanna called Nana the Servant","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"AHjDuOwvEUpocvFL","name":"Joanna called Nana the Servant - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Joanna called Nana the Servant","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I have been Lady Gwendolyn’s trusted personal \nservant for over ten years. I saw the young heir grow up and I \nam as fond of her as if she were my own daughter.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 84.","positive":"I have been Lady Gwendolyn’s trusted personal \nservant for over ten years. I saw the young heir grow up and I \nam as fond of her as if she were my own daughter.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Joanna called Nana the Servant","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"q0DMED0up3bhWf9E","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Joanna called Nana the Servant","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I have been Lady Gwendolyn’s trusted personal \nservant for over ten years. I saw the young heir grow up and I \nam as fond of her as if she were my own daughter.\nInformation: Joanna will tell the Hunters that she often \nheard Gwendolyn chatting with a boy in her room, but \nwhen she came in to figure out who it was, she never found \nanyone. Gwendolyn has always avoided revealing the boy’s \nidentity, convincing Nana that he was some noble son of \na good family in the city. Searching Gwendolyn’s room, \nthe Hunters will find some poppy petals under the bed. \nNana will say that those flowers can only be found in the \nKensington Gardens in London.\nSeals: There is only one Seal in the Carnarvon villa, \ninscribed on the east wall of Gwendolyn’s room.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 84.","owner":"Joanna called Nana the Servant","source":"I Don't Believe","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"014did82003r90kn","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-dont-believe-joanna-called-nana-the-servant-84","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","adventureTitle":"I Don't Believe","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":84,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Don't Believe","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I have been Lady Gwendolyn’s trusted personal \nservant for over ten years. I saw the young heir grow up and I \nam as fond of her as if she were my own daughter.\nInformation: Joanna will tell the Hunters that she often \nheard Gwendolyn chatting with a boy in her room, but \nwhen she came in to figure out who it was, she never found \nanyone. Gwendolyn has always avoided revealing the boy’s \nidentity, convincing Nana that he was some noble son of \na good family in the city. Searching Gwendolyn’s room, \nthe Hunters will find some poppy petals under the bed. \nNana will say that those flowers can only be found in the \nKensington Gardens in London.\nSeals: There is only one Seal in the Carnarvon villa, \ninscribed on the east wall of Gwendolyn’s room.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":6000000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"uXiM3h3PQA4Ao1oD","name":"Karl and Elsa Karenmann","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Gw3FR42K16bZ0SFH","name":"Karl and Elsa Karenmann - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Karl and Elsa Karenmann","source":"Bloodwhite's Heart","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>We are two loving parents who only want what’s \nbest for Bianca. We have great wealth and allies throughout \nLohr.</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 111.","positive":"We are two loving parents who only want what’s \nbest for Bianca. We have great wealth and allies throughout \nLohr.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"Karl and Elsa Karenmann","source":"Bloodwhite's Heart","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628470,"modifiedTime":1781557628470,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"UKvi5szDeR5KnvGg","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Karl and Elsa Karenmann","source":"Bloodwhite's Heart","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are two loving parents who only want what’s \nbest for Bianca. We have great wealth and allies throughout \nLohr.\nAgenda: To have Ottone’s death case closed as soon as possible, \nplacing the blame on Bruna / Protect Bianca from a world that \ncould not accept her for what she is.\nKarenmann Palace\nDescriptor: A large and magnificent palace that contrasts \nwith the humble appearance of the rest of Lohr’s dwellings.\nDuring the interview, the Hunters will realize that the palace \nis full of paintings depicting the Karenmann family. In many \npaintings, a beautiful girl with long black hair, snow-white \nskin, and a pure and innocent look can be seen. From the \npaintings the great love that unites Elsa and Karl to their \ndaughter Bianca is clear.\nThe Village of Lohr\nDescriptor: A small village that is experiencing new prosperity \nthanks to the Karenmann family.\nThe Hunters may hear some rumors while exploring the \nvillage. Choose or roll 1 die:</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 111.","owner":"Karl and Elsa Karenmann","source":"Bloodwhite's Heart","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628470,"modifiedTime":1781557628470,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"00o4ut1z01pgdx9e","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-bloodwhites-heart-karl-and-elsa-karenmann-111","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"bloodwhites-heart","adventureTitle":"Bloodwhite's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":111,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Bloodwhite's Heart","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are two loving parents who only want what’s \nbest for Bianca. We have great wealth and allies throughout \nLohr.\nAgenda: To have Ottone’s death case closed as soon as possible, \nplacing the blame on Bruna / Protect Bianca from a world that \ncould not accept her for what she is.\nKarenmann Palace\nDescriptor: A large and magnificent palace that contrasts \nwith the humble appearance of the rest of Lohr’s dwellings.\nDuring the interview, the Hunters will realize that the palace \nis full of paintings depicting the Karenmann family. In many \npaintings, a beautiful girl with long black hair, snow-white \nskin, and a pure and innocent look can be seen. From the \npaintings the great love that unites Elsa and Karl to their \ndaughter Bianca is clear.\nThe Village of Lohr\nDescriptor: A small village that is experiencing new prosperity \nthanks to the Karenmann family.\nThe Hunters may hear some rumors while exploring the \nvillage. Choose or roll 1 die:</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To have Ottone’s death case closed as soon as possible, \nplacing the blame on Bruna / Protect Bianca from a world that \ncould not accept her for what she is.\nKarenmann Palace\nDescriptor: A large and magnificent palace that contrasts \nwith the humble appearance of the rest of Lohr’s dwellings.\nDuring the interview, the Hunters will realize that the palace \nis full of paintings depicting the Karenmann family. In many \npaintings, a beautiful girl with long black hair, snow-white \nskin, and a pure and innocent look can be seen. From the \npaintings the great love that unites Elsa and Karl to their \ndaughter Bianca is clear.\nThe Village of Lohr\nDescriptor: A small village that is experiencing new prosperity \nthanks to the Karenmann family.\nThe Hunters may hear some rumors while exploring the \nvillage. Choose or roll 1 die:","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":6100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628470,"modifiedTime":1781557628470,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"zdfOXbmT8p4Femcw","name":"The Prince","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"g7qnLrczUCVHVcSO","name":"The Prince - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Prince","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a Golem of blood \nand flesh. There is only hatred in my \nbroken heart.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 172.","positive":"I am a Golem of blood \nand flesh. There is only hatred in my \nbroken heart.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false,"owner":"The Prince","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637842,"modifiedTime":1781557637842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"KeYGTGNdtjOLEUv9","name":"Gift - Broken Heart","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Prince","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Once per Scene, the Prince can \nemit a freezing scream of pain that affects all living beings \nin the area, causing 1 Penalty to any action against him.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 172.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The Prince","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637842,"modifiedTime":1781557637842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"op3EcTxHv05yMVMf","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Prince","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"}},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(6 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a Golem of blood \nand flesh. There is only hatred in my \nbroken heart. \nAgenda: Killing and tearing apart the ungrateful \npeople of Prague / I prefer to take my revenge on the \nrich and powerful above all others. \nGift – Broken Heart: Once per Scene, the Prince can \nemit a freezing scream of pain that affects all living beings \nin the area, causing 1 Penalty to any action against him. \nGift – Tornado of Blades: The Prince’s body is \ncomposed of arms, legs, and heads held together by a \nmetal structure. Any limb that can hold a blade \ndoes. The Prince can start spinning, hitting \neach opponent on his way in a single \nattack, inflicting 1 Wound on anyone \nwho fails a Defense Check.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 172.","owner":"The Prince","source":"I Will Stay with You Always","category":"threat"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637842,"modifiedTime":1781557637842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"01gakz6800ms75vx","flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-will-stay-with-you-always-the-prince-172","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-will-stay-with-you-always","adventureTitle":"I Will Stay with You Always","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":172,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Will Stay with You Always","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(6 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a Golem of blood \nand flesh. There is only hatred in my \nbroken heart. \nAgenda: Killing and tearing apart the ungrateful \npeople of Prague / I prefer to take my revenge on the \nrich and powerful above all others. \nGift – Broken Heart: Once per Scene, the Prince can \nemit a freezing scream of pain that affects all living beings \nin the area, causing 1 Penalty to any action against him. \nGift – Tornado of Blades: The Prince’s body is \ncomposed of arms, legs, and heads held together by a \nmetal structure. Any limb that can hold a blade \ndoes. The Prince can start spinning, hitting \neach opponent on his way in a single \nattack, inflicting 1 Wound on anyone \nwho fails a Defense Check.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":6},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Killing and tearing apart the ungrateful \npeople of Prague / I prefer to take my revenge on the \nrich and powerful above all others.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":6200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637842,"modifiedTime":1781557637842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"fNNTZY406AHBWQbo","name":"Anastazia the Sorrowful Spirit","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/ghost.svg","items":[{"_id":"D2QxTWBsUniuLDoc","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Anastazia the Sorrowful Spirit","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a restless spirit, bound to the memory of my granddaughter. My condition as a spirit does not allow me to communicate with the living except through dreams, whispers, and visions.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor-principal.anastazia-the-sorrowful-spirit","owner":"Anastazia the Sorrowful Spirit","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"I am a restless spirit, bound to the memory of my granddaughter. My condition as a spirit does not allow me to communicate with the living except through dreams, whispers, and visions.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056760,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Wd1qNFj0p965ADlX","name":"Spirit","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Anastazia the Sorrowful Spirit","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>Anastazia is a spirit and can only be damaged by magic. She may appear in a dream to a target, who may resist with a Defense Check or accept contact voluntarily. The target suffers 1 Wound from stress but will receive from Anastazia a vision of a present or past event with a barely whispered phrase.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"don1.anastazia-the-sorrowful-spirit","owner":"Anastazia the Sorrowful Spirit","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056760,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"js8Oi1QJDE87Xt8g","name":"Loving Grandmother","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Anastazia the Sorrowful Spirit","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>Anastazia always follows Iskra and protects her from danger. Thanks to her strong will, she can interact with the material world by moving objects and manipulating the environment, even inflicting a Wound on a target. If a subject is likely to help save her granddaughter, Anastazia will simply fill their mind with memories of her.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"don2.anastazia-the-sorrowful-spirit","owner":"Anastazia the Sorrowful Spirit","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"SGY01ijY2YAU13Df","flags":{"broken-tales":{"legacyBackup":"Broken Ones.db","legacySlug":"anastazia-the-sorrowful-spirit","source":"E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","collection":"The Broken Ones","role":"Scenario Actor","needsSpanishTranslation":true}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Legacy Broken One","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Broken One","notes":"<p>Anastazia is a restless spirit, bound to the memory of her granddaughter Iskra. She can no longer speak directly to the living, only through dreams, whispers, and visions.</p><p>Agenda: Preventing further harm to Iskra and finding a way to save my granddaughter’s soul.</p><p>Notes: Anastazia is incorporeal. The Storyteller may allow her to manifest for narrative effect.</p>","background":"Anastazia is a restless spirit, bound to the memory of her granddaughter Iskra. She can no longer speak directly to the living, only through dreams, whispers, and visions."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":3,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Preventing further harm to Iskra and finding a way to save my granddaughter’s soul.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":6300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"MaHwFVWAbz7KM6im","name":"Iskra the Young Wolf","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"asM4e09i0tHm7GvV","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Iskra the Young Wolf","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>When I am calm, I still look like a small and helpless child and, thanks to this, adults tend to underestimate me. I struggle to behave like a normal child, but I can’t keep my wolfish side leashed forever.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor-principal.iskra-the-young-wolf","owner":"Iskra the Young Wolf","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"When I am calm, I still look like a small and helpless child and, thanks to this, adults tend to underestimate me. I struggle to behave like a normal child, but I can’t keep my wolfish side leashed forever.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Uga41phiEfgM3QLA","name":"Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Iskra the Young Wolf","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>I perform my best when I’m cooperating with my hunting companions. I quickly learn the strengths and weaknesses of the pack. I follow every order of anyone I consider more important than me within the pack, without hesitation or remorse.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor1.iskra-the-young-wolf","owner":"Iskra the Young Wolf","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"I perform my best when I’m cooperating with my hunting companions. I quickly learn the strengths and weaknesses of the pack. I follow every order of anyone I consider more important than me within the pack, without hesitation or remorse.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Xaz55QqMTKU3vMpS","name":"Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Iskra the Young Wolf","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a wolf child and I defend myself with fangs and claws. My sense of smell is infallible. I’m young and I know little about the world, so I am easily intimidated when I face something I don’t know.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor2.iskra-the-young-wolf","owner":"Iskra the Young Wolf","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"I am a wolf child and I defend myself with fangs and claws. My sense of smell is infallible. I’m young and I know little about the world, so I am easily intimidated when I face something I don’t know.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"lrkqG2EzrxrpSYVH","name":"The Red Hood","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Iskra the Young Wolf","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>You can spend 1 Soma to look exactly like a common child. Create a Descriptor that contains one of the words Pretty, Small, or Sweet. As long as you maintain your disguise, no adult will notice you or consider you a potential danger. Receive 2 Additional Successes to the first action you take when you decide to drop your disguise and reveal who you are.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"don1.iskra-the-young-wolf","owner":"Iskra the Young Wolf","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"bw0cB6u1zrhbMnHO","name":"Pack","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Iskra the Young Wolf","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>When you coordinate and act with one or more of your teammates against a common threat, you both get 1 Additional Success for your Position Check. At the end of the Scene, if you have resolved a significant issue thanks to the collaboration with your companions, you recover 1 Soma.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"don2.iskra-the-young-wolf","owner":"Iskra the Young Wolf","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"5oJ5HIYXiDlWxM6m","name":"Dark Ego - The Young Wolf","type":"darkEgo","img":"icons/svg/terror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Iskra the Young Wolf","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>Unleash your feral side, ready to bite anyone who opposes your pack. If you get an Outcome with an Increment on a Position Check, you can spend the Increment to take an additional action immediately. You can also inflict 1 Wound on yourself to perform an additional action after your normal action. You can’t perform more than 3 actions per Exchange. You may spend 1 Soma to memorize the smell of a person you are interacting with. You will always recognize them and it will be easy for you to follow their tracks even after a long time.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"darkego.iskra-the-young-wolf","owner":"Iskra the Young Wolf","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","trigger":"Give free rein to your feral side or fulfill a task for your pack with your wolf skills.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":600000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"9RSFyPzcN4zSFCHd","name":"Equipment","type":"equipment","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/equipment-bag.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Iskra the Young Wolf","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>A red cape of fine workmanship embroidered with the coat of arms of the Order, a wolf mask carved in wood, a broken clay doll (a memento of one of my few happy memories of my mother), a fang from the leader of my old pack, and a rag doll depicting a well-dressed girl — a gift from my beloved grandmother.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"equipment.iskra-the-young-wolf","owner":"Iskra the Young Wolf","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones"},"sort":700000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"SGY01ijY2YAU13Df","flags":{"broken-tales":{"legacyBackup":"Broken Ones.db","legacySlug":"iskra-the-young-wolf","source":"E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","collection":"The Broken Ones","role":"Scenario Actor","needsSpanishTranslation":true}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Legacy Broken One","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Broken One","notes":"<p>I was abandoned by my mother in a large forest and survived by joining a pack of werewolves. After a year of honing my predatory skills, I tracked down the woman I once called 'Mother' and sank my fangs into her throat. My pack was dismantled by a group of Hunters and the Order captured me. After another year of education and training, I finally found in the Order my new pack and made the Hunters my trusted hunting companions. I serve the Order with strength and dedication, happy to do everything the alpha Hunter asks of me.</p>","background":"I was abandoned by my mother in a large forest and survived by joining a pack of werewolves. After a year of honing my predatory skills, I tracked down the woman I once called 'Mother' and sank my fangs into her throat. My pack was dismantled by a group of Hunters and the Order captured me. After another year of education and training, I finally found in the Order my new pack and made the Hunters my trusted hunting companions. I serve the Order with strength and dedication, happy to do everything the alpha Hunter asks of me."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":6,"max":6},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":6400000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"KRFuvtferUrbzPGy","name":"Red-Hood Iskra","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/blood.svg","items":[{"_id":"GLYMSl2bIdXLAQep","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Red-Hood Iskra","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>I possess the strength and agility of a wolf. I hide my face with a rudimentary wooden mask that I made with my own hands. I wear a threadbare red cape, the last gift of my mother.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor-principal.red-hood-iskra","owner":"Red-Hood Iskra","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"I possess the strength and agility of a wolf. I hide my face with a rudimentary wooden mask that I made with my own hands. I wear a threadbare red cape, the last gift of my mother.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"188eqyIfsy0oFAq9","name":"Wolf's Blood","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Red-Hood Iskra","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>Iskra is moved by animalistic fury that allows her to act twice in the course of an exchange.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"don1.red-hood-iskra","owner":"Red-Hood Iskra","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"EhTm0kNy1ZuNBds3","name":"The Senses of a Wolf","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Red-Hood Iskra","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>Iskra's sense of smell has become infallible. The little girl will always be able to identify someone if she knows their scent, ignoring all kinds of disguise and even magic.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"don2.red-hood-iskra","owner":"Red-Hood Iskra","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"SGY01ijY2YAU13Df","flags":{"broken-tales":{"legacyBackup":"Broken Ones.db","legacySlug":"red-hood-iskra","source":"E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","collection":"The Broken Ones","role":"Scenario Actor","needsSpanishTranslation":true}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Legacy Broken One","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Broken One","notes":"<p>Agenda: To unleash her animalistic fury on Elizaveta and anyone who defends her. Taking revenge on my mother has become an obsession for me.</p>","background":""},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To unleash her animalistic fury on Elizaveta and anyone who defends her. Taking revenge on my mother has become an obsession for me.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":6500000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"1RYwHBFQgGrr63mQ","name":"The God Under the Mine","type":"threat","img":"icons/creatures/abilities/mouth-teeth-long-red.webp","items":[{"_id":"UcTCp2NKxPCi1GvL","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The God Under the Mine","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a creature as old as the world, trapped beneath the bedrock</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor-principal.the-god-under-the-mine","owner":"The God Under the Mine","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"I am a creature as old as the world, trapped beneath the bedrock","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"OeMWJVvDRzpDUmdV","name":"Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The God Under the Mine","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>Millennia of inactivity have made me catatonic and there is nothing that can really wake me up</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor1.the-god-under-the-mine","owner":"The God Under the Mine","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"Millennia of inactivity have made me catatonic and there is nothing that can really wake me up","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"DQI6beP8SN2wWISW","name":"Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The God Under the Mine","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>Only pain can stir me even slightly</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor2.the-god-under-the-mine","owner":"The God Under the Mine","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"Only pain can stir me even slightly","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"eleU1zUaK4mqvbTL","name":"The Head of the God","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The God Under the Mine","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>Only the enormous head of the God emerges from the rock, and pieces of meat can be obtained from it. When he suffers 1 Wound, the God emits a loud grunt that sends everyone flying (a Defense Check can avoid this). As an additional effect of the grunt, the God's fetid breath taints the air, granting 1 Penalty to the next action of all affected subjects, excluding Arthur. When reduced to 0 Wounds, the God falls into a deep sleep to fully regenerate in the following Scene.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"don1.the-god-under-the-mine","owner":"The God Under the Mine","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"SGY01ijY2YAU13Df","flags":{"broken-tales":{"legacyBackup":"Broken Ones.db","legacySlug":"the-god-under-the-mine","source":"E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","collection":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","needsSpanishTranslation":true}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Legacy Broken One","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>An ancient god-like creature, a huge pig-like being embedded in the rock below Whitehaven. It has been trapped for millennia, and its long inactivity has made it catatonic - there is nothing that can truly wake it. Only pain can stir it slightly. The mine collapse caused by its stirring left Arthur Browne trapped underground, where he discovered the God's head protruding from the north wall of a natural cave. Arthur found that the God's flesh regenerates quickly and confers incredible powers when eaten, including the ability to transform into monstrous pig-headed forms. The God's flesh is now being distributed by Frank Browne through the slaughterhouse, mixed with common meat, creating an army of Pig Heads to wage war against Bardolf Greed.</p>","background":"An ancient god-like creature, a huge pig-like being embedded in the rock below Whitehaven. It has been trapped for millennia, and its long inactivity has made it catatonic - there is nothing that can truly wake it. Only pain can stir it slightly. The mine collapse caused by its stirring left Arthur Browne trapped underground, where he discovered the God's head protruding from the north wall of a natural cave. Arthur found that the God's flesh regenerates quickly and confers incredible powers when eaten, including the ability to transform into monstrous pig-headed forms. The God's flesh is now being distributed by Frank Browne through the slaughterhouse, mixed with common meat, creating an army of Pig Heads to wage war against Bardolf Greed."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":6},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":6600000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"NF3uPZKJNQH3mt40","name":"Azzurra De Baciocchi - The Spirit of the Witch","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"T1rSuZEH6o26hrxK","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Azzurra De Baciocchi - The Spirit of the Witch","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the spirit of an old and powerful witch. My powers allow me to summon the souls of the dead and bind them to my will.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor-principal.azzurra-de-baciocchi-the-spirit-of-the-witch","owner":"Azzurra De Baciocchi - The Spirit of the Witch","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"I am the spirit of an old and powerful witch. My powers allow me to summon the souls of the dead and bind them to my will.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"UvByVI1vNaPIPTTv","name":"Ancient Spirit","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Azzurra De Baciocchi - The Spirit of the Witch","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>Azzurra's body is immaterial and can only be damaged by magic. Azzurra can interact with the world by evoking the souls of the dead, choosing between various effects. 1. Poltergeist: Throw up to 3 objects at once. The force with which the objects are thrown is such that they can cause a Wound. 2. Cacophony of the Dead: Frighten everyone with the agonized voices of the damned. Anyone who hears the cacophony must pass a Defense Check or lose 2 Soma points. 3. Possession: Take possession of a target's body and cause them to perform a single action, albeit not a self-destructive one. Azzurra must change the spirits' effect with each action and must use all three before she can use an effect again.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"don1.azzurra-de-baciocchi-the-spirit-of-the-witch","owner":"Azzurra De Baciocchi - The Spirit of the Witch","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"SGY01ijY2YAU13Df","flags":{"broken-tales":{"legacyBackup":"Broken Ones.db","legacySlug":"azzurra-de-baciocchi-the-spirit-of-the-witch","source":"E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","collection":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","needsSpanishTranslation":true}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Legacy Broken One","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>The former noble owner of Villa Cilesterino, Azzurra was burned at the stake in 1513 for witchcraft - accused of sacrificing young women in search of eternal youth. Her spirit still haunts the abandoned villa. When Geppetto and Antonio fled to her manor, she deceived them by animating their mannequins with her powers and convincing them their research was working. Azzurra needs Carlo's fairy magic to bring herself back to life. She has created a magical brazier in the Secret Laboratory where Carlo is to be burned in a ritual requiring innocent blood.</p><p>Agenda: To come back to life thanks to Carlo's power</p><p>Notes: Commands 4 Marionettes and Medoro the bear. Can sense anyone on her property. Will not hesitate to confront intruders. The entire Villa Cilesterino is under her supernatural influence.</p>","background":"The former noble owner of Villa Cilesterino, Azzurra was burned at the stake in 1513 for witchcraft - accused of sacrificing young women in search of eternal youth. Her spirit still haunts the abandoned villa. When Geppetto and Antonio fled to her manor, she deceived them by animating their mannequins with her powers and convincing them their research was working. Azzurra needs Carlo's fairy magic to bring herself back to life. She has created a magical brazier in the Secret Laboratory where Carlo is to be burned in a ritual requiring innocent blood."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"To come back to life thanks to Carlo's power","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":6700000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Whl0YIkQKYs9ZC68","name":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","type":"threat","img":"icons/magic/nature/root-vine-caduceus-healing.webp","items":[{"_id":"03JKCcZ7aQshU304","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>I was born with a facial deformity and society rejected me</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor-principal.margareta-westen-the-good-witch","owner":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"I was born with a facial deformity and society rejected me","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"hgddn27mJrFRtiBt","name":"Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>I use my magic and fortune to create a haven for outcasts</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor1.margareta-westen-the-good-witch","owner":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"I use my magic and fortune to create a haven for outcasts","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"FOijZUUJSyVVafAG","name":"Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>I ease suffering wherever I can find it</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor2.margareta-westen-the-good-witch","owner":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"I ease suffering wherever I can find it","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"IEURVY3WdXW5Ugpl","name":"Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>My compassion makes me vulnerable to those who would harm me</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor3.margareta-westen-the-good-witch","owner":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"My compassion makes me vulnerable to those who would harm me","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"9z8Z7kjobbWGGeHr","name":"Witch - Emotion Manipulation","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>Margareta can perform a Check to alter the emotional state of anyone she can see. She can make them feel calm, afraid, angry, or loving. This lasts for one Scene. Victims can resist with a Check against her Opposition Level (7). She uses this primarily to ease the pain and shame of outcasts, helping them find peace with their conditions.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"don1.margareta-westen-the-good-witch","owner":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7In74Pf5CjeWVEtj","name":"Witch - Telekinesis","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>Margareta can move objects with her mind. She can lift and throw items weighing up to 200 pounds. In combat, she can use this to disarm opponents, create barriers from environmental objects, or hurl items as weapons (treating this as a normal attack with her OL). She uses this to provide for her village's needs and defend them when necessary.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"don2.margareta-westen-the-good-witch","owner":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":600000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"SGY01ijY2YAU13Df","flags":{"broken-tales":{"legacyBackup":"Broken Ones.db","legacySlug":"margareta-westen-the-good-witch","source":"E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","collection":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","needsSpanishTranslation":true}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Legacy Broken One","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>Margareta Westen is a wealthy noblewoman who was born with a facial deformity. Society rejected her despite her wealth and noble birth, treating her as a monster because of her appearance. Rather than becoming bitter, Margareta used her magic and her fortune to create a haven in the village of Gelb where the rejected could live in peace and dignity. She is the Good Witch of the Yellow Village, holder of the western piece of the Compass Rose. Margareta is genuinely kind and maternal, using emotion manipulation magic to ease the pain of outcasts and telekinesis to provide for their needs. She welcomes the Hunters warmly and explains her mission: to provide a safe haven for those rejected by society. When OZena comes to kill her and steal her Compass Rose piece, Margareta shows compassion even to her would-be assassin—she recognizes that Dorothea is suffering and has been manipulated. Margareta knows that OZena murdered Johanne two weeks ago and understands that Dr. Henkle is the true villain manipulating Dorothea from Smaragd. Her compassion is both her greatest strength and her fatal weakness—she hesitates to harm even those who threaten her. If she survives, she warns the Hunters about Helga in Rot and the danger of the incomplete Compass Rose. If she dies, the village of Gelb falls into despair.</p><p>Agenda: Protect my village and the outcasts who live here / Use my magic to ease suffering / Stop OZena before she kills more witches / Guard the western piece of the Compass Rose</p><p>Notes: Margareta is OZena's second target (Johanne was first). She holds the YELLOW/WEST piece of Compass Rose. She knows: Compass Rose split 4 ways, Johanne murdered, OZena manipulated by Henkle, Henkle in Smaragd. Compassion is weakness—hesitates to harm even attackers. If killed, Gelb falls into despair, outcasts terrified. If survives, warns about Helga in Rot, may give Hunters her Compass piece. Voice: Warm, maternal, slight German accent. Mannerisms: Touches people gently, maintains eye contact despite deformity, smiles kindly. Only 1 Wound but OL 7 makes her formidable with magic.</p>","background":"Margareta Westen is a wealthy noblewoman who was born with a facial deformity. Society rejected her despite her wealth and noble birth, treating her as a monster because of her appearance. Rather than becoming bitter, Margareta used her magic and her fortune to create a haven in the village of Gelb where the rejected could live in peace and dignity. She is the Good Witch of the Yellow Village, holder of the western piece of the Compass Rose. Margareta is genuinely kind and maternal, using emotion manipulation magic to ease the pain of outcasts and telekinesis to provide for their needs. She welcomes the Hunters warmly and explains her mission: to provide a safe haven for those rejected by society. When OZena comes to kill her and steal her Compass Rose piece, Margareta shows compassion even to her would-be assassin—she recognizes that Dorothea is suffering and has been manipulated. Margareta knows that OZena murdered Johanne two weeks ago and understands that Dr. Henkle is the true villain manipulating Dorothea from Smaragd. Her compassion is both her greatest strength and her fatal weakness—she hesitates to harm even those who threaten her. If she survives, she warns the Hunters about Helga in Rot and the danger of the incomplete Compass Rose. If she dies, the village of Gelb falls into despair."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":3,"max":3},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Protect my village and the outcasts who live here / Use my magic to ease suffering / Stop OZena before she kills more witches / Guard the western piece of the Compass Rose","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":6800000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"yT5rtMobHiVOAxyB","name":"Dr. Norman Henkle - The Powerful Wizard","type":"threat","img":"icons/magic/time/clock-face-tan.webp","items":[{"_id":"f6JZHJhwJ0bkK8wR","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dr. Norman Henkle - The Powerful Wizard","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a brilliant researcher from 1900s, appearing as a wizard in 1780</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor-principal.dr-norman-henkle-the-powerful-wizard","owner":"Dr. Norman Henkle - The Powerful Wizard","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"I am a brilliant researcher from 1900s, appearing as a wizard in 1780","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7qgne4wnMyky4uv6","name":"Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dr. Norman Henkle - The Powerful Wizard","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>My future knowledge makes me a god among primitives</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor1.dr-norman-henkle-the-powerful-wizard","owner":"Dr. Norman Henkle - The Powerful Wizard","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"My future knowledge makes me a god among primitives","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"YSApQTYTywJdVnpi","name":"Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dr. Norman Henkle - The Powerful Wizard","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>I will escape this era at any cost</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor2.dr-norman-henkle-the-powerful-wizard","owner":"Dr. Norman Henkle - The Powerful Wizard","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"I will escape this era at any cost","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"SPLVgVEgWsbUoyG8","name":"Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dr. Norman Henkle - The Powerful Wizard","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>Everyone is a tool to be used and discarded</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor3.dr-norman-henkle-the-powerful-wizard","owner":"Dr. Norman Henkle - The Powerful Wizard","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"Everyone is a tool to be used and discarded","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"6CCYl9jLT2Awz7r2","name":"Hot-Air Balloon","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dr. Norman Henkle - The Powerful Wizard","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>Henkle has constructed a hot-air balloon using future knowledge as his escape vehicle. **Time Tokens:** During the Scenario, place 1 Time Token on this Gift each time: a combat encounter occurs in Smaragd (max 1 per Scene), Hunters waste time lost in the Labyrinth, or Henkle successfully delays/distracts Hunters. **Ready to Launch:** When 3 Time Tokens accumulate, the balloon is fully inflated and ready. Henkle can board and launch as a single action. **Escape:** Once airborne, extremely difficult to stop—requires creative methods (shooting balloon, magic, climbing tether). If he escapes, activates Compass Rose while airborne.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"don1.dr-norman-henkle-the-powerful-wizard","owner":"Dr. Norman Henkle - The Powerful Wizard","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"HGTCsDvE7lSEkVVQ","name":"Silver Tongue","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Dr. Norman Henkle - The Powerful Wizard","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>Henkle is a master manipulator who has convinced entire villages to follow him. **Deception Mastery:** When attempting to deceive, persuade, or manipulate, his Opposition Level increases by +2 (becomes 7). **NPC Vulnerability:** Any NPC who isn't a Hunter must make a Check against OL 7 to resist believing his lies. He's particularly effective at finding what people want and promising it. **Weakness - Plagiarist:** His genius is mostly stolen. If confronted by someone with true expertise in a topic he's claiming mastery of, his façade crumbles and his OL drops to 3 for that Exchange.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"don2.dr-norman-henkle-the-powerful-wizard","owner":"Dr. Norman Henkle - The Powerful Wizard","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":600000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"SGY01ijY2YAU13Df","flags":{"broken-tales":{"legacyBackup":"Broken Ones.db","legacySlug":"dr-norman-henkle-the-powerful-wizard","source":"E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","collection":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","needsSpanishTranslation":true}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Legacy Broken One","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>Dr. Norman Henkle is a brilliant researcher from the early 1900s who was transported to 1780 through mysterious circumstances (orchestrated by the One Who Plots in the Shadows). In this primitive era, his future knowledge makes him appear to be a powerful wizard. He appears as a charming man in his 40s, dressed in anachronistic clothing mixing 1900s and 1780s fashion. He carries himself with absolute confidence and speaks with a silver tongue that has convinced countless people to follow him. When he arrived in Smaragd with his patients (Dorothea, Lowe, Hirnloser, and Dose), he used his knowledge of penicillin (150 years before its actual discovery) to cure an epidemic, and the grateful villagers made him their leader. He discovered the magical wishing well and learned to manipulate it, transforming Smaragd into his fortress. He manipulated Dorothea into murdering the other witches to collect Compass Rose pieces, planning to use the incomplete artifact to escape—either returning to his time as a powerful wizard or conquering both eras. His genius is mostly stolen—surface knowledge of many subjects but deep understanding of none. He's a master manipulator but completely amoral, seeing everyone (including his patients) as tools. His ultimate plan is to activate the Compass Rose while in his hot-air balloon, believing he can control his destination. He doesn't care that the incomplete artifact will tear reality and throw people randomly through time.</p><p>Agenda: Activate the Compass Rose and escape this primitive era / Protect my stolen research and knowledge / Eliminate anyone who threatens my plans / Maintain my image as a benevolent wizard until I can escape</p><p>Notes: Henkle doesn't want to fight—he wants to escape. He offers deals constantly: join him, let him go, trade a cure for passage. His primary goal is buying time for the balloon to launch (track Time Tokens). If cornered, becomes desperate and vicious, all charm vanishing. He attempts suicide rather than face capture. Voice: Smooth, charming, American accent. Mannerisms: Constantly smiling (doesn't reach eyes), grand gestures, touches people to establish connection, checks escape routes constantly. If defeated, his research on time travel and the wishing well is incredibly valuable to the Order.</p>","background":"Dr. Norman Henkle is a brilliant researcher from the early 1900s who was transported to 1780 through mysterious circumstances (orchestrated by the One Who Plots in the Shadows). In this primitive era, his future knowledge makes him appear to be a powerful wizard. He appears as a charming man in his 40s, dressed in anachronistic clothing mixing 1900s and 1780s fashion. He carries himself with absolute confidence and speaks with a silver tongue that has convinced countless people to follow him. When he arrived in Smaragd with his patients (Dorothea, Lowe, Hirnloser, and Dose), he used his knowledge of penicillin (150 years before its actual discovery) to cure an epidemic, and the grateful villagers made him their leader. He discovered the magical wishing well and learned to manipulate it, transforming Smaragd into his fortress. He manipulated Dorothea into murdering the other witches to collect Compass Rose pieces, planning to use the incomplete artifact to escape—either returning to his time as a powerful wizard or conquering both eras. His genius is mostly stolen—surface knowledge of many subjects but deep understanding of none. He's a master manipulator but completely amoral, seeing everyone (including his patients) as tools. His ultimate plan is to activate the Compass Rose while in his hot-air balloon, believing he can control his destination. He doesn't care that the incomplete artifact will tear reality and throw people randomly through time."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":2,"max":2},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Activate the Compass Rose and escape this primitive era / Protect my stolen research and knowledge / Eliminate anyone who threatens my plans / Maintain my image as a benevolent wizard until I can escape","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":6900000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"W3VXQckhOcL8wRkW","name":"Helga - The Red Witch","type":"threat","img":"icons/magic/blood/drops-drip-sprinkle-red.webp","items":[{"_id":"IgXTFSPGQXEwQcAe","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Helga - The Red Witch","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a blood witch, centuries old but kept young by magic</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor-principal.helga-the-red-witch","owner":"Helga - The Red Witch","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"I am a blood witch, centuries old but kept young by magic","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"sOpNCYxEYPGfftQO","name":"Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Helga - The Red Witch","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>I guard the southern piece of the Compass Rose</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor1.helga-the-red-witch","owner":"Helga - The Red Witch","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"I guard the southern piece of the Compass Rose","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"38l9OWsha64CpySa","name":"Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Helga - The Red Witch","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>I punish those who threaten my domain</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor2.helga-the-red-witch","owner":"Helga - The Red Witch","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"I punish those who threaten my domain","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"8pNPHSx1GlLSEFQs","name":"Descriptor 4","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Helga - The Red Witch","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>My power comes from blood willingly given—or forcibly taken</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor3.helga-the-red-witch","owner":"Helga - The Red Witch","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"My power comes from blood willingly given—or forcibly taken","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"YshHIEQR9ckChVzx","name":"Blood Magic","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Helga - The Red Witch","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>Helga is a master of blood magic with three primary abilities. **Blood Control:** Can manipulate any blood she can see—make wounds bleed more profusely (inflict 1 additional Wound), turn spilled blood into sharp projectiles, or create barriers of hardened blood. **Blood Puppet:** Once per Scene, take control of any creature with an open wound within 30 feet. Victim must make a Check against her OL to resist; if they fail, they're under her control for one Exchange. **Blood Healing:** Drain blood from nearby sources (servants, animals, pooled blood) to heal herself, restoring 1 Wound by completely draining one human servant.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"don1.helga-the-red-witch","owner":"Helga - The Red Witch","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"fJEeZcRDbb7K0qXS","name":"Blood Witch","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Helga - The Red Witch","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>Helga has sustained her life for centuries through blood magic. When she would be reduced to 0 Wounds, she instead: drains blood from all nearby sources, regenerates 1 Wound immediately, ages visibly (gains wrinkles, gray hair, etc.), and can do this once per Scene. When killed permanently, Helga rapidly ages centuries in moments, crumbling to dust. **Vulnerability:** The complete Infusion of Purity (with elderberry) negates all blood magic for one Scene when splashed on her. Without her magic, she's just an ordinary (very old) woman.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"don2.helga-the-red-witch","owner":"Helga - The Red Witch","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":600000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"SGY01ijY2YAU13Df","flags":{"broken-tales":{"legacyBackup":"Broken Ones.db","legacySlug":"helga-the-red-witch","source":"E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","collection":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","needsSpanishTranslation":true}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Legacy Broken One","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>Helga is a blood witch, centuries old but kept young by her dark magic. She appears as a striking woman in her 40s with long red hair and eyes that seem to glow with inner fire. She wears elaborate red robes and is always covered in blood—whether her own or others' is unclear. Helga guards the southern piece of the Compass Rose and rules the village of Rot through blood magic, maintaining a cult of mind-controlled servants. She started centuries ago as a guardian like Margareta, sworn to protect her piece of the Rose, but was corrupted by the power of blood magic. Now she's a tyrant who takes blood willingly given or forcibly taken to sustain her unnatural life. When OZena attempted to infiltrate Rot and steal the Compass piece, Helga captured her and prepared a blood sacrifice ritual for the next full moon. Helga sees herself as dispensing justice—OZena murdered Johanne and Margareta, so she must pay in blood. But Helga's centuries of cruelty have made her more monster than guardian. She can control blood itself, making wounds bleed more, turning blood into weapons, and even taking control of anyone with an open wound. If killed, she drains blood from nearby sources to regenerate, visibly aging each time. Her greatest weakness is the complete Infusion of Purity with elderberry—it negates her blood magic for one Scene, revealing her true ancient age.</p><p>Agenda: Protect my piece of the Compass Rose / Maintain my cult and power base / Punish OZena for murdering my sister witches / Stay young and powerful forever</p><p>Notes: Helga won't negotiate unless: (1) the Hunters have evidence of Henkle's manipulation, (2) they use the Infusion of Purity to break her blood magic, or (3) they appeal to her original purpose as a guardian. If combat begins, she's incredibly powerful—controlling blood, taking over wounded opponents, and regenerating when killed. If her magic fails, she ages rapidly into a withered old woman. If spared and freed from blood magic's corruption, she may reveal important truths about Henkle's plans in Smaragd and the true purpose of the Compass Rose. Voice: Commanding and imperious with an ancient accent. Mannerisms: Gestures dramatically, blood swirls around her when angry.</p>","background":"Helga is a blood witch, centuries old but kept young by her dark magic. She appears as a striking woman in her 40s with long red hair and eyes that seem to glow with inner fire. She wears elaborate red robes and is always covered in blood—whether her own or others' is unclear. Helga guards the southern piece of the Compass Rose and rules the village of Rot through blood magic, maintaining a cult of mind-controlled servants. She started centuries ago as a guardian like Margareta, sworn to protect her piece of the Rose, but was corrupted by the power of blood magic. Now she's a tyrant who takes blood willingly given or forcibly taken to sustain her unnatural life. When OZena attempted to infiltrate Rot and steal the Compass piece, Helga captured her and prepared a blood sacrifice ritual for the next full moon. Helga sees herself as dispensing justice—OZena murdered Johanne and Margareta, so she must pay in blood. But Helga's centuries of cruelty have made her more monster than guardian. She can control blood itself, making wounds bleed more, turning blood into weapons, and even taking control of anyone with an open wound. If killed, she drains blood from nearby sources to regenerate, visibly aging each time. Her greatest weakness is the complete Infusion of Purity with elderberry—it negates her blood magic for one Scene, revealing her true ancient age."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":3,"max":3},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Protect my piece of the Compass Rose / Maintain my cult and power base / Punish OZena for murdering my sister witches / Stay young and powerful forever","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":7000000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"fSKwtHnsvogAvv8G","name":"Yvonne - The Spirit Who Longs for Revenge","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"3ONnRLrJ5y00u1jp","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Yvonne - The Spirit Who Longs for Revenge","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a restless spirit who can manipulate fire.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor-principal.yvonne-the-spirit-who-longs-for-revenge","owner":"Yvonne - The Spirit Who Longs for Revenge","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"I am a restless spirit who can manipulate fire.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"IC7g8DocYeLxKrij","name":"Spirit","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Yvonne - The Spirit Who Longs for Revenge","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>Yvonne is in a spirit form and can only truly be damaged by magic. The touch of a Spirit absorbs life energy and inflicts 1 Wound. Physical protection and barriers cannot help against this Gift. If the Spirit is harmed by non-magical means, she still will suffer a Wound. However, when Yvonne has no Wounds left, she disappears and rematerializes immediately. In doing so, all her Wounds are healed, except those inflicted by magical means. Once per Scene, Yvonne can call 3 Restless Spirits to her who will obey her will.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"don1.yvonne-the-spirit-who-longs-for-revenge","owner":"Yvonne - The Spirit Who Longs for Revenge","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"eDz43ij6Tq15alOr","name":"Soul of Fire","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Yvonne - The Spirit Who Longs for Revenge","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>Yvonne can manipulate fire at will. This Gift only affects a fire that is already lit. Manipulating fire, for Yvonne, is considered an additional action. The fire inflicts 1 Wound and if the Defense Check is an Outcome with a Cost, the target will continue to burn. During the following Exchange, if not put out, the fire will inflict 1 additional Wound. Thanks to her power, Yvonne can multiply the width and size of a flame by up to ten times.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"don2.yvonne-the-spirit-who-longs-for-revenge","owner":"Yvonne - The Spirit Who Longs for Revenge","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"SGY01ijY2YAU13Df","flags":{"broken-tales":{"legacyBackup":"Broken Ones.db","legacySlug":"yvonne-the-spirit-who-longs-for-revenge","source":"E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","collection":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","needsSpanishTranslation":true}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Legacy Broken One","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>A ragged little orphan who sold candles to survive on the streets of Paris. Scorned by all, even by the poor. Found compassion only in Father Adrien who offered her shelter. One evening she discovered Adrien's secret absinthe laboratory. Adrien strangled her unconscious, set her on fire, and threw her charred body in the catacombs. Many poor people witnessed the scene but stayed silent to keep Adrien's favor. Reborn as a vengeful spirit, Yvonne now torments those who were silent at her murder with maddening laughter and vicious whispers, then sets them ablaze. Saving Adrien for her grand finale - plans to burn all of Paris by igniting the Cemetery of the Innocents during the passage of comet Morituris on December 31st. During the day, remains near the place where she burned. Her body was found with only teeth intact, locked in a deathly grin. A small candle near her ashes remains miraculously untouched by flames.</p><p>Agenda: Get revenge on Adrien and all those who ignored my death / Set Paris ablaze with the fires of the dead</p><p>Notes: Tragic villain driven by righteous vengeance. Willing to negotiate but will not give up revenge on Adrien. Can be reasoned with if Hunters show compassion. Only one person (Olivier) remains on her list before Adrien.</p>","background":"A ragged little orphan who sold candles to survive on the streets of Paris. Scorned by all, even by the poor. Found compassion only in Father Adrien who offered her shelter. One evening she discovered Adrien's secret absinthe laboratory. Adrien strangled her unconscious, set her on fire, and threw her charred body in the catacombs. Many poor people witnessed the scene but stayed silent to keep Adrien's favor. Reborn as a vengeful spirit, Yvonne now torments those who were silent at her murder with maddening laughter and vicious whispers, then sets them ablaze. Saving Adrien for her grand finale - plans to burn all of Paris by igniting the Cemetery of the Innocents during the passage of comet Morituris on December 31st. During the day, remains near the place where she burned. Her body was found with only teeth intact, locked in a deathly grin. A small candle near her ashes remains miraculously untouched by flames."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Get revenge on Adrien and all those who ignored my death / Set Paris ablaze with the fires of the dead","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":7100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"s3Vp1q0hnSmUziQr","name":"Enar - The Eternal Soldier","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"J8ymKAdhcCFdtZ5H","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Enar - The Eternal Soldier","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an immortal being, the result of all the hatred I harbored in my exile into the abyss</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor-principal.enar-the-eternal-soldier","owner":"Enar - The Eternal Soldier","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"I am an immortal being, the result of all the hatred I harbored in my exile into the abyss","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"RbtmogvKygs8bi6N","name":"Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Enar - The Eternal Soldier","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>I have the strength of five men and my body feels no pain</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor1.enar-the-eternal-soldier","owner":"Enar - The Eternal Soldier","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"I have the strength of five men and my body feels no pain","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"io6SVmEe0jkuiOaL","name":"The Eternal Soldier","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Enar - The Eternal Soldier","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>When Enar suffers his final Wound, his body becomes seawater and soaks into the ground. The following day, Enar completely regenerates himself at the bottom of the sea, where his heart is. Only by recovering the heart and destroying it can Enar be permanently eliminated.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"don1.enar-the-eternal-soldier","owner":"Enar - The Eternal Soldier","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"5dOoTAHYqtfdyHSO","name":"Rage of the Sea","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Enar - The Eternal Soldier","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>Thanks to magic granted by the Sea Fairy, Enar can always choose an additional effect: 1. Algae Whip: A string of algae stretches from Enar's body and can perform a second independent action. 2. Wave: Enar's body becomes seawater, allowing him to slip away and cover 30 feet. 3. Shells: 3 large seashells are shot at 3 different targets (OL Medium 5 each).</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"don2.enar-the-eternal-soldier","owner":"Enar - The Eternal Soldier","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"SGY01ijY2YAU13Df","flags":{"broken-tales":{"legacyBackup":"Broken Ones.db","legacySlug":"enar-the-eternal-soldier","source":"E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","collection":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","needsSpanishTranslation":true}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Legacy Broken One","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>Six years ago, Enar was a soldier in love with dancer Satu. Commander Andersen, consumed by jealousy, raped Satu and falsely accused Enar of abandoning his post. As punishment, Enar was chained to rocks and left to drown in the sea. The injustice and hatred transformed him into an immortal monster. A Sea Fairy granted him powers to seek revenge. Enar systematically hunts down and kills his former companions. His heart rests at the bottom of the sea—destroy it to kill him permanently.</p><p>Agenda: Take revenge on Andersen, but not before I have eliminated all my former companions / After eliminating Andersen and his people, I want to meld with Satu so that our bodies and souls are united for eternity</p><p>Notes: MAIN ANTAGONIST. 4 Wounds, OL Hard 7, regenerates daily unless heart is destroyed. Can act twice per turn with Algae Whip or use Wave/Shells. When at 2 Wounds, Erik enters—Enar realizes Erik is Andersen's son and targets the child. Recognizes shells from the cliff where his heart lies.</p>","background":"Six years ago, Enar was a soldier in love with dancer Satu. Commander Andersen, consumed by jealousy, raped Satu and falsely accused Enar of abandoning his post. As punishment, Enar was chained to rocks and left to drown in the sea. The injustice and hatred transformed him into an immortal monster. A Sea Fairy granted him powers to seek revenge. Enar systematically hunts down and kills his former companions. His heart rests at the bottom of the sea—destroy it to kill him permanently."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Take revenge on Andersen, but not before I have eliminated all my former companions / After eliminating Andersen and his people, I want to meld with Satu so that our bodies and souls are united for eternity","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":7200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"iUnar3zrwjQcc3Wd","name":"Princess Tuvstarr - The Child Princess","type":"threat","img":"icons/equipment/head/crown-jeweled-gold-pink.webp","items":[{"_id":"Ndt4EfwNvsBhUEU4","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Princess Tuvstarr - The Child Princess","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a pure and innocent soul</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor-principal.princess-tuvstarr-the-child-princess","owner":"Princess Tuvstarr - The Child Princess","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"I am a pure and innocent soul","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"QXJhhdtobkjKOb3P","name":"Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Princess Tuvstarr - The Child Princess","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>I just want a world without suffering</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor1.princess-tuvstarr-the-child-princess","owner":"Princess Tuvstarr - The Child Princess","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"I just want a world without suffering","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Lm0Q5wglI5eNpzQh","name":"Creative Will","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Princess Tuvstarr - The Child Princess","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>Tuvstarr has the power to create anything she wants in the Dream World. She can make a bird appear out of nowhere or make an apple tree grow from nothing to bearing fruit in a couple of seconds. She can deflect a river, make sunlight warmer, shape clouds, and make small fish glow around her when swimming in a river. Each new creation draws life from the real world, making it more corrupt and darker. Tuvstarr can use her power to defend herself by literally manipulating the whole world. If Tuvstarr is killed in this world, she will transform into colorful butterflies to regenerate herself at her castle. Although Tuvstarr has virtually infinite power, her innocence means that even if threatened, she will never try to kill a living being. Rather, the Princess will try to hurt and scare any threats and, in the worst case, drive them away.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"don1.princess-tuvstarr-the-child-princess","owner":"Princess Tuvstarr - The Child Princess","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"gtYsMhjdnqnGAsG3","name":"Pure Innocence","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Princess Tuvstarr - The Child Princess","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>Tuvstarr radiates innocence and beauty. Whoever meets her will fall under her spell. She is always friendly, and her voice is clear and beautiful, with the sharpness of ice breaking on a winter pond. Those who interact with Tuvstarr must make a Defense Check or be fascinated by her. For the rest of the Scene, the bewitched subject will not take any action that could harm Tuvstarr and, furthermore, will defend her at the cost of their life from any threats. Seeing how the world outside the pond is rotting will make a bewitched subject instantly come to their senses.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"don2.princess-tuvstarr-the-child-princess","owner":"Princess Tuvstarr - The Child Princess","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"SGY01ijY2YAU13Df","flags":{"broken-tales":{"legacyBackup":"Broken Ones.db","legacySlug":"princess-tuvstarr-the-child-princess","source":"E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","collection":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","needsSpanishTranslation":true}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Legacy Broken One","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>A child princess who learned of a pond deep in the woods where wishes can come true. She asked Skutt the moose to lead her there, trading her crown to the Fairies and her dress to the Hulder for safe passage. At the black pond, she plunged her heart and soul in, desiring a perfect world where everything is bright and good. That's what she found on the other side - a perfect dream where she is happy, fields are always green, and idealized constructs of her parents smile at her. But the Dream World needs balance, and so reality became dark and twisted: the sun set in eternal darkness, the forest corrupted, animals got sick, and the soil rotted. She wanders naked and full of life in her dream kingdom, creating things with her power. She has only vague memories of the real world, as if that were the dream. There is something about the black pond that makes her uncomfortable or even scares her, but she cannot 'remove' it as it is the gateway between worlds. She will ask visitors to stay in her kingdom forever, just like the Gallant Knight did.</p><p>Agenda: I want to stay forever in my perfect world. I have been here for so long that I have forgotten what my life was like before</p>","background":"A child princess who learned of a pond deep in the woods where wishes can come true. She asked Skutt the moose to lead her there, trading her crown to the Fairies and her dress to the Hulder for safe passage. At the black pond, she plunged her heart and soul in, desiring a perfect world where everything is bright and good. That's what she found on the other side - a perfect dream where she is happy, fields are always green, and idealized constructs of her parents smile at her. But the Dream World needs balance, and so reality became dark and twisted: the sun set in eternal darkness, the forest corrupted, animals got sick, and the soil rotted. She wanders naked and full of life in her dream kingdom, creating things with her power. She has only vague memories of the real world, as if that were the dream. There is something about the black pond that makes her uncomfortable or even scares her, but she cannot 'remove' it as it is the gateway between worlds. She will ask visitors to stay in her kingdom forever, just like the Gallant Knight did."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I want to stay forever in my perfect world. I have been here for so long that I have forgotten what my life was like before","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":7300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"E153TTeRl6ymzUg3","name":"The Hulder - Corrupted Forest Spirit","type":"threat","img":"icons/creatures/unholy/spirit-undead-ghost-blue.webp","items":[{"_id":"S0bQ9U5H4ixl2oxu","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Hulder - Corrupted Forest Spirit","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an ancient forest spirit</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor-principal.the-hulder-corrupted-forest-spirit","owner":"The Hulder - Corrupted Forest Spirit","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"I am an ancient forest spirit","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"oMZijRx7OTh7jkNP","name":"Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Hulder - Corrupted Forest Spirit","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>I have eaten so many living things that I have become fat and swollen</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor1.the-hulder-corrupted-forest-spirit","owner":"The Hulder - Corrupted Forest Spirit","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"I have eaten so many living things that I have become fat and swollen","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"G9iZyIAYN4Lg88ej","name":"Descriptor 3","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Hulder - Corrupted Forest Spirit","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>The pieces of the animals and people I have devoured are dripping from my slobbering lips</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor2.the-hulder-corrupted-forest-spirit","owner":"The Hulder - Corrupted Forest Spirit","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"The pieces of the animals and people I have devoured are dripping from my slobbering lips","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"BjxWULPGxRXd70SA","name":"Corrupted Spirit","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Hulder - Corrupted Forest Spirit","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>The Hulder has a feminine form, thin but her skin is spongy and slimy. Her breath smells of rot. She doesn't realize what a grotesque monster she has become, as in her mind she is still beautiful and seductive. When she suffers 1 Wound, the Hulder vomits a cloud of foul vapor that reeks of rot. All the subjects hit by the cloud suffer 1 Wound in turn. The effect of this Gift can be avoided with a Defense Check.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"don1.the-hulder-corrupted-forest-spirit","owner":"The Hulder - Corrupted Forest Spirit","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"2JVL0ZnN2OpCin7E","name":"Swollen with Flesh and Blood","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Hulder - Corrupted Forest Spirit","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>If killed, the Hulder will emit a long, heart-breaking cry that will echo in the woods, and all the dead she has eaten will scream in agony in a cacophonous chorus. Anyone who hears the cry loses 2 Soma and receives 1 Penalty on any action for the rest of the Scene.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"don2.the-hulder-corrupted-forest-spirit","owner":"The Hulder - Corrupted Forest Spirit","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056761,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"SGY01ijY2YAU13Df","flags":{"broken-tales":{"legacyBackup":"Broken Ones.db","legacySlug":"the-hulder-corrupted-forest-spirit","source":"E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","collection":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","needsSpanishTranslation":true}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Legacy Broken One","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>A spiritual forest entity with feminine traits that once lived in symbiosis with trees but is now corrupt and repulsive. When Princess Tuvstarr traded her white dress for passage through the woods, the Hulder took the thin fabric and immediately felt unlike anything before. With the dress, she felt strong and beautiful, but also prey to a voracious hunger. Now the dress is nothing more than a dirty piece of cloth tied over her eyes like a blindfold. The Hulder obsessively repeats how beautiful, graceful and lovely she is, unaware of the grotesque monster she has become. A trail of blood and slime marks her path. Her sense of smell is almost non-existent, but she charges furiously at any noise. The best way to defeat her is to tear the dress from her eyes near a reflective surface - when she sees her true reflection, she will scream in agony and crawl away to throw up everything she ate, returning to her original form filled with shame and guilt.</p><p>Agenda: Devour everything I meet</p>","background":"A spiritual forest entity with feminine traits that once lived in symbiosis with trees but is now corrupt and repulsive. When Princess Tuvstarr traded her white dress for passage through the woods, the Hulder took the thin fabric and immediately felt unlike anything before. With the dress, she felt strong and beautiful, but also prey to a voracious hunger. Now the dress is nothing more than a dirty piece of cloth tied over her eyes like a blindfold. The Hulder obsessively repeats how beautiful, graceful and lovely she is, unaware of the grotesque monster she has become. A trail of blood and slime marks her path. Her sense of smell is almost non-existent, but she charges furiously at any noise. The best way to defeat her is to tear the dress from her eyes near a reflective surface - when she sees her true reflection, she will scream in agony and crawl away to throw up everything she ate, returning to her original form filled with shame and guilt."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Devour everything I meet","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":7400000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056762,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"l390DLgvGWw4cHgc","name":"Alice Liddell - The Director","type":"threat","img":"icons/environment/people/cleric-orange.webp","items":[{"_id":"s810ijTTvIAKx5Lm","name":"Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alice Liddell - The Director","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the director of Wonder</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor-principal.alice-liddell-the-director","owner":"Alice Liddell - The Director","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"I am the director of Wonder","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056762,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"VhiZafD4jAfW3q6Z","name":"Descriptor 2","type":"descriptor","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/descriptor-improvement.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alice Liddell - The Director","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>Thanks to the power of madness, I can enter people's minds to heal them</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"descriptor1.alice-liddell-the-director","owner":"Alice Liddell - The Director","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","positive":"Thanks to the power of madness, I can enter people's minds to heal them","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056762,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"HK5E1A7QIOF9vKEh","name":"Alice from Other Worlds","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Alice Liddell - The Director","source":"Broken Ones.db","category":"brokenOne","legacy":true}},"system":{"description":"<p>As an action, Alice can attempt to possess the body of a person or animal by looking into their eyes. Hunters can make a Defense Check to prevent this. Alice can both act through the body she controls and continue to use her Gifts and Descriptors. The possession ends when Alice's body suffers 1 Wound. Alice cannot control more than 3 common subjects or a single Hunter at the same time.</p>","notes":"Restored from E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","key":"don1.alice-liddell-the-director","owner":"Alice Liddell - The Director","category":"brokenOne","source":"The Broken Ones","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056762,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":"SGY01ijY2YAU13Df","flags":{"broken-tales":{"legacyBackup":"Broken Ones.db","legacySlug":"alice-liddell-the-director","source":"E:/respaldos/Broken Ones.db","collection":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","needsSpanishTranslation":true}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Legacy Broken One","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>Alice Liddell, daughter of an English aristocrat in great favor with the Crown, developed a complex mental illness as a child, suffering from visions and delusions about a fantasy world. 'Treated' in secret with drugs and experimental therapies, she learned to appear sane and eventually graduated with a degree in medicine at age twenty-seven. The culmination of her career is Wonder, a 'hospital' for wealthy families' children. However, inside Wonder, Alice has created a world of sheer madness where patients must follow her perverse ideas to be 'cured.' Her lucid madness has gained such strength from patients' suffering that she can now shape reality itself. Wonder has become a building out of space and time, where doors lead anywhere unless you know the right words. Alice controls a trained lynx named Cheshire and has imprisoned the inventor Hatta Carter to maintain her impossible asylum.</p><p>Agenda: Safeguard what I have built within Wonder and all the incredible discoveries that the magic of madness can give to mankind / Solve every problem by transforming it into a Patient to be treated</p>","background":"Alice Liddell, daughter of an English aristocrat in great favor with the Crown, developed a complex mental illness as a child, suffering from visions and delusions about a fantasy world. 'Treated' in secret with drugs and experimental therapies, she learned to appear sane and eventually graduated with a degree in medicine at age twenty-seven. The culmination of her career is Wonder, a 'hospital' for wealthy families' children. However, inside Wonder, Alice has created a world of sheer madness where patients must follow her perverse ideas to be 'cured.' Her lucid madness has gained such strength from patients' suffering that she can now shape reality itself. Wonder has become a building out of space and time, where doors lead anywhere unless you know the right words. Alice controls a trained lynx named Cheshire and has imprisoned the inventor Hatta Carter to maintain her impossible asylum."},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Safeguard what I have built within Wonder and all the incredible discoveries that the magic of madness can give to mankind / Solve every problem by transforming it into a Patient to be treated","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":7500000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.73","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1784595056762,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
